  {"a":"gangplank","b":"aatrox","win":["Skill","Skill","Aatrox","Skill","Skill","Aatrox","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Neither of you wants a brawl here — his Qs are single-cast and his passive only heals when he lands hits, so drop a Powder Keg on the wave and Parrrley it for chip while you keep him off your minions."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"His three-cast Q is up and he can W chain-pull you into the third sweetspot knockup — your kegs are on a long cooldown at this level, so this is his cleanest gap-close-and-all-in window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His Eclipse/Stridebreaker spike plus passive heal-on-hit out-sustains your Sheen-keg burst in a committed extended trade — poke and disengage, don't stand and brawl."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"A chained Powder Keg detonation into empowered Parrrley bursts him faster than his passive and lifesteal can heal, and Cannon Barrage zones his R all-in from outside chain-pull range."}],"wants":{"you":["Detonate a Powder Keg with Parrrley from max range so he eats the slow-and-poke without walking into his W chain-pull range","Use Remove Scurvy to cleanse the slow/root chip off his combo and heal back what his Qs cost you, then peel out before his passive stacks heals","Stall to 2+ items where a full keg chain bursts him faster than his drain passive and lifesteal can top him back up"],"foe":["Land the third-cast Q sweetspot on the outer edge to knock you up, then W chain-pull you in for the full drain combo","Drag you into a prolonged trade so passive heal-on-hit and Stridebreaker lifesteal out-sustain your keg poke","Catch your Powder Kegs on cooldown and commit R for the combat-stat all-in before you can detonate and slow him off"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are a race between two weak laners, but Aatrox's combo comes online first. Drop a Powder Keg on the wave and farm with Parrrley from range — never sit at the outer edge of his third-cast Q, where the sweetspot knocks you up into a W chain-pull and a full drain. Do not greed auto-trades: his passive heals on every hit he lands, so short keg-Parrrley poke from a distance is your only safe damage. Save Remove Scurvy for the slow and root off his combo (note it can NOT cleanse his airborne knockup — only his own passive right-clicks that off), and respect that at 3 he can gap-close and commit.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stabilize as your second keg point lands and you can Parrrley-detonate barrels for real poke he has to walk through to farm. He still wins the committed extended trade — his drain Qs and passive heal undo your damage if you stand in it — so trade in bursts behind a keg and disengage, never brawl to zero. At 6 your Cannon Barrage zones his R all-in and covers your barrel resets, but it does not out-duel his combat-stat ult outright, so use it to deny his engage, not to chase him down.","late":"This is where you take over. With Sheen/Essence Reaver online, a full Powder Keg chain into empowered Parrrley bursts him faster than his passive and Stridebreaker lifesteal can heal it back, and you do it from outside W chain-pull range. Keep a keg between you so every engage costs him a slow he has to eat, use Remove Scurvy to wipe the slow/root off his combo and heal, and drop Cannon Barrage to split his all-in. He has no answer to chained keg detonations once you are itemized — close on your terms, not his.","whys":["You are both bottom-tier level 1s — drop a keg and Parrrley it for safe chip instead of trading autos into a passive that heals every hit he lands.","Still even at 2: your single keg pokes, but his Qs already threaten the third-cast sweetspot, so hold range and respect his W chain-pull setup.","His full three-cast Q plus W chain-pull lands while your kegs sit on a long cooldown — his cleanest gap-close all-in, so play tight to the wave.","Your second keg point lets you Parrrley-poke him as he walks up to farm, evening a lane his drain Qs still win in a long brawl.","Cannon Barrage adds zoning and resets cover but does not out-duel his R combat stats — it is even, a deny button, not a kill button.","His Eclipse/Stridebreaker spike and passive heal-on-hit out-sustain your Sheen-keg burst in a committed trade — bait the all-in, don't brawl it.","Chained keg detonations into empowered Parrrley burst him before his passive heals, and you do it from outside W range — you scale clean past him."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"akali","win":["Gangplank","Skill","Skill","Skill","Akali","Akali","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Parrrley-poke her every time she steps in for a last-hit -- she's energy-gated and has to melee the wave, so she bleeds HP for CS while you bank gold and Silver Serpents toward your first keg."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R double-cast turns a poked-down you into a free kill: she dashes in with the first cast, and if you're under the execute threshold the second cast finishes you through your barrels."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Her Gunblade/Lich Bane spike lands before your keg build comes fully online -- this is her cleanest window to shroud your Parrrley, dash in on E, and burst you between barrel cooldowns."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Your chained Powder Keg detonations plus Parrrley burst delete her squishy frame from range -- if you deny her Twilight Shroud resets, she dies before her combo lands."}],"wants":{"you":["Land Parrrley pokes while she walks up for energy-gated CS, banking gold and Silver Serpents toward your keg spike","Pre-place a Powder Keg on your side of the wave so a chained detonation punishes her E-shuriken dash-in","Hold Remove Scurvy for the missing-HP heal and her Q slow -- the heal lets you survive her level-6 burst into your scaling"],"foe":["Hit level 6 and chain R's two dashes plus the execute to all-in you over your barrels","Drop Twilight Shroud to go untargetable -- it eats your turret, your Parrrley, and your keg detonation if you fire into it","Roam mid/bot off a shroud reset and snowball her AP item spikes unanswered"]},"early":"Akali is energy-gated and has to walk into melee range to last-hit, so every time she steps up I tag her with Parrrley -- she pays HP for CS while I bank gold and Serpents toward my first keg. Her Twilight Shroud isn't worth burning on cooldown yet and her E-shuriken is her only gap-closer pre-6, so a barrel pre-placed on my side of the wave punishes any dash-in. I don't greed full trades into her; she out-damages me in a raw melee scrap, so I poke with Q, deny her CS, and refuse to be the one who walks up.","mid":"This is the dangerous patch. At 6 her R's two dashes plus the execute turn a poked-down me into a kill, and Twilight Shroud goes fully untargetable -- it eats my Parrrley and survives a keg detonation if I fire into the cloud. I respect her shroud window completely: bait it out, then trade. I keep Remove Scurvy up for the missing-HP heal so I can survive her burst, and I never sit in lane low while her ult is available. If she catches me on a barrel cooldown, I'm dead.","late":"Once my keg build is online the math flips hard. Chained Powder Keg detonations plus Parrrley burst delete her squishy frame from range, and Cannon Barrage zones her out of any fight she wants to flank. The one rule: don't fire a Parrrley or detonation blind into Twilight Shroud -- she's untargetable inside it, so wait for her to commit out, then chain the barrels. If I keep her honest and deny the shroud reset, she can't survive a full keg chain.","whys":["She's energy-gated and must walk into melee to last-hit, so Parrrley pokes her for free while she farms -- I bank gold and Serpents off the harass.","Her E-shuriken dash is her only commit tool pre-6 and shroud isn't worth burning yet -- pre-place a barrel and the trade stays even.","Full kit on both sides but no ult yet -- I poke with Q and kegs, she answers in melee, and neither can hard-commit without losing the wave.","We trade around her shroud and my barrel cooldowns -- bank small leads, don't overstay, and keep Remove Scurvy ready to heal through her engage.","At 6 her R's two dashes plus the execute let her all-in over my barrels -- if I'm poked low she finishes me through Cannon Barrage.","Her first AP item spike lands before my keg build does -- she can shroud my poke, dash in on E, and burst me on a barrel cooldown this window.","Two items on, chained keg detonations plus Parrrley burst delete her frame from range -- deny her the Twilight Shroud reset and she dies before her combo finishes."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"akshan","win":["Gangplank","Akshan","Akshan","Skill","Akshan","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Akshan's second Avengerang point is his sharpest early window — the boomerang hits you on the way out AND back from out of your auto range, chipping you while your single low-HP keg sits on a long cooldown and a barrel he can free-shoot to deny it."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Comeuppance (R) plus Heroic Swing mobility let him pick a sidelane fight or dodge your Cannon Barrage entirely — your ult zones a region but never out-duels an Akshan swinging in and out on E."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver is your flip — empowered Parrrley detonates a chained keg for the burst a no-resist squishy can't survive past his passive shield."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Two items of crit and your chained keg explosions one-shot him through the Dirty Fighting shield, and global Cannon Barrage pressures whichever sidelane he tries to roam to."}],"wants":{"you":["Last-hit with the tip of Parrrley so the boomerang's out-and-back arc can't free-poke you while your keg charges","Reach Sheen and detonate a full chained keg combo on him — he has no defensive cooldown, only a passive third-hit shield, so one clean chain bursts him","Place E barrels on his terrain swing-anchors so a Heroic Swing brings him INTO the blast instead of letting him kite around it"],"foe":["Out-poke you with the Avengerang double-hit and Dirty Fighting third-hit damage before your keg line comes online","Use Heroic Swing to grapple off lane terrain, kite around your barrels, and reset trades you can't chase","Wait for Comeuppance and roam — kill the right target to revive a teammate and snowball a lane he can't hard-kill"]},"early":"Akshan's early poke is the real threat. Avengerang (Q) bounces out and back so it tags you twice from outside your auto range, and his Dirty Fighting passive adds a chunk on the third hit plus a small shield, all while my single keg sits on a long cooldown with tiny HP he can just shoot to deny it. At level 1 I'm fine — neither of us wants a raw level-1 fight and I can Parrrley a last hit from range. But once he lands his second Q point he out-pokes me through levels 2-3, so don't walk up to place a keg inside his auto range. Farm with the tip of Parrrley, eat a little chip, and don't burn E on a barrel he'll just free-shoot.","mid":"Levels 4-5 even out as I get a second E point and can start landing Parrrley-into-keg poke that actually hurts a no-resist squishy. The trap: Heroic Swing (E) lets him grapple off terrain and kite around my barrels, so a keg I detonate often catches air if I telegraph it. At 6 he edges back ahead — Comeuppance and his swing mobility let him pick a sidelane skirmish or simply swing out of my Cannon Barrage, which zones a region but won't win a duel. Place kegs on HIS swing anchors so the grapple drags him INTO the blast, and don't chase him through the swing.","late":"Once I hit Sheen/Essence Reaver and my keg build comes online I flip this. Empowered Parrrley detonating a full chained barrel bursts him hard — he has no pool, no cleanse-heal, only a passive third-hit shield that one clean keg chain blows straight through. By two items I own it: chained explosions plus global Cannon Barrage mean I delete him in a teamfight and pressure his side lane from across the map. He doesn't out-scale me like a Kayle or Vlad would, so my whole job is just surviving his early Avengerang poke to get here.","whys":["Neither of you wants a raw level-1 fight and your ranged Parrrley grabs a last hit without stepping into his Avengerang range.","His second Avengerang point lands and the boomerang's out-and-back arc chips you twice while your lone keg sits on a long cooldown with HP he can free-shoot.","He out-pokes you outright at 3 — Avengerang double-hit plus the Dirty Fighting third-hit beats a keg you can't safely detonate into him yet.","You get your second E point and Parrrley-into-keg poke comes online, so the chip war flattens to even through 4-5.","Comeuppance plus Heroic Swing let him pick a sidelane fight or swing out of your Cannon Barrage, which zones ground but never out-duels him.","Sheen/Essence Reaver empowers Parrrley to detonate a chained keg and burst a no-resist squishy straight through his passive shield.","Two items of chained keg explosions plus global Cannon Barrage one-shot him, and unlike a true scaler he can't reclaim this window."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"ambessa","win":["Gangplank","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Ambessa","Ambessa","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1","text":"Drop a keg behind the melee minions and Parrrley it as she walks up to last-hit — free chip before her dash recasts have the points to dive on you and chain CC."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your second E point cuts the keg cooldown enough to keep a barrel up every wave — Q-detonate it on her the instant she's spent her second dash and can't recast away from the slow."},{"when":"Lvl 6-1st item","text":"Her power spike: Public Execution plus her double-dash combo out-trades your raw stats before your keg build is online, and the ult suppresses through your W cleanse window — don't stand in barrel-setup range with her dashes up."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Essence Reaver into the keg build flips it back — a full chained-keg detonation bursts her before she finishes weaving her dash combo onto you."}],"wants":{"you":["Land Parrrley-into-keg chip whenever she's spent her dash recasts and bank the gold and Silver Serpents off the trade","Keep the wave on your side so she has to dash into your barrel zone to farm","Survive to Essence Reaver and a stocked keg chain, then burst her in one chained detonation"],"foe":["Catch you mid barrel-setup with her double-dash combo and chain her W damage and CC","Weave her dashes around your Parrrley and keg-pops so your poke whiffs","Hit her level 6 Public Execution spike and all-in before your keg build comes online"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are about not getting clipped while I set barrels. My kegs have long cooldowns and low HP here, so she can free-hit a barrel to deny it or dash on me the moment I walk up to place one. Don't body-block to set up a chain — drop a keg behind the wave and Parrrley it from range for chip, then back off. Her early all-in leans on her dash recasts; if she's already burned them I can step up, otherwise I'm last-hitting at Q range and refusing to feed her a chain-CC combo.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are my best laning window — a second E point keeps a barrel up almost every wave, so I Q-detonate kegs on her whenever her second dash is spent and heal any return poke off W (Remove Scurvy also cleanses if she lands her CC, though it can't break Public Execution's suppress once it's locked on). But level 6 swings to her: Public Execution plus the full double-dash combo out-trades my raw stats before my keg build exists, and my Cannon Barrage zones but doesn't win the straight duel. So at 6 I stop forcing and only trade once her dashes are down.","late":"Once Essence Reaver and the keg build land, this is mine again. A stocked chain of barrels Q-popped in sequence bursts her before she finishes weaving her dash combo, and W cleanses the lockdown she needs to stick to me (just not her R-suppress mid-cast). She scales into a solid bruiser, but she's a fighter, not a hyperscaler — she doesn't reclaim the 2+ items window the way a Vayne or Kayle does, so I keep poking, keep my kegs stocked, and add Cannon Barrage pressure across the map.","whys":["Parrrley-into-keg chip costs her HP and pays me gold and Silver Serpents, and at level 1 her dash recasts can't punish a barrel I place behind the wave.","Even window — my first barrel zones her wave positioning but she can dash a keg-pop or free-hit the barrel to deny it, so neither of us owns it yet.","Full kit is online but so is her double-dash combo, and a single chain catches me mid-setup — it comes down to who respects the other's cooldown.","Second E point keeps a barrel up every wave — I Q-detonate on her when her second dash is spent and heal the return with W.","Her spike: Public Execution plus the double-dash-and-CC combo out-trades my stats before my keg build exists, and my Cannon Barrage zones but won't win the duel.","She out-trades my raw stats in the first-item window — her dash combo bursts me before Essence Reaver and a full keg chain come online.","Essence Reaver into the keg build flips it back — a chained detonation bursts her and W cleanses the CC she needs to stick, and she's no hyperscaler who reclaims this."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"aurora","win":["Skill","Skill","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Aurora's Twofold Hex recast chunks you for missing-health damage, and she can W (Across the Veil) onto a keg to free-hit it invisible while your barrels sit on long cooldowns and low base HP."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her Between Worlds ult walls the lane into the spirit realm and slows you, and she flies through it untargetable; with W invisibility to dodge your keg detonations, this is her hardest snowball window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver online: an empowered Parrrley that detonates a chained Powder Keg finally out-bursts her poke and flips the trade pattern."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Full keg chains plus global Cannon Barrage burst her squishy AP frame and let you zone every objective and punish her side-lane roams from across the map."}],"wants":{"you":["Last-hit at max Parrrley range and pre-place a Powder Keg you can detonate the instant she steps up to recast Twofold Hex on you","Survive to your first-item Sheen spike, then wait out her W dash and burst her with a Q-detonated keg chain when she has no invisibility up","Use Cannon Barrage to deny her roams and zone objectives once your kegs out-damage her poke"],"foe":["Land Twofold Hex and recast it for missing-health damage to poke you off the wave before your barrels are a threat","W (Across the Veil) onto your kegs to deny them invisible, and save W to dash away and reset distance after every trade","Use her R spirit-realm zone to wall you in, slow you, and fly through untargetable, snowballing levels 3-6"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are a knife-fight I can lose. My barrels have long cooldowns and low base HP, so Aurora will W (Across the Veil) onto a keg to free-hit it invisible and deny it, then chip me with Twofold Hex and its missing-health recast. Do NOT walk up to throw a Parrrley I can't follow up — last-hit at max Q range and eat a little poke rather than feed her a Hex recast for free. Remember she has no hard CC to lock me, so her damage is all poke: respect the range, not a non-existent root, and don't trade into her invisibility window.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are her snowball window and I have to respect it. Her Twofold Hex poke and W dash let her chip me and reset distance every trade, and at 6 her Between Worlds ult walls the lane into the spirit realm, slows me, and she flies through it untargetable while I can't kite out. Her W invisibility also dodges my keg detonations on demand. Play for cs and pre-placed kegs here; don't all-in into a full-CD barrel set. Save W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse her R slow and heal, then walk away even rather than dying for a bad trade.","late":"Once my first item lands, the lane flips. A Sheen-empowered Parrrley detonating a chained Powder Keg starts actually bursting her squishy AP frame, and by two items a full keg chain one-shots her. Bait out her W (Across the Veil) — that dash-into-invisibility is her only real escape and her keg-denial tool — then detonate the keg the instant she lands with no W up. Cannon Barrage punishes her roams and locks down objectives. I scale into the monster here; just don't throw the won game by face-checking her poke before my kegs are placed.","whys":["Her Twofold Hex and my barrels are both weak at level 1 — last-hit clean and don't burn a keg she can just W onto and free-hit to deny.","Her Hex recast deals real missing-health poke and she has no all-in tools yet — farm at Parrrley range and trade nothing into her dash.","Her Twofold Hex poke out-trades me while my kegs sit on long cooldowns and she denies them with W invisibility — concede the wave.","Levels 4-5 she pokes me off the lane with Hex and resets with W, and my barrels still aren't a duel threat — survive and farm.","Her Between Worlds ult walls me into the spirit realm and slows me while she flies through untargetable, and W dodges my keg detonations — respect her hardest all-in.","My Sheen spike lands: an empowered Parrrley detonating a chained keg finally out-bursts her poke — bait the W dash and punish.","Full keg chains plus global Cannon Barrage one-shot her squishy AP frame — I out-scale and own every objective fight now."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"camille","win":["Skill","Camille","Camille","Camille","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Camille's window: E hookshot stun into Precision Protocol's empowered second cast (true damage on the timed re-hit) plus Tactical Sweep's outer-edge true damage chunks you before a single barrel detonates, and your Powder Keg's long early cooldown means you can't chain a punish back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage adds map and skirmish pressure but doesn't win the straight 1v1, so the duel sits even unless she E-walls in for a forced isolation; neither of you cleanly commits without jungle help."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Trinity Force into your keg setup flips the tempo: empowered Parrrley detonating a chained barrel set bursts and slows her faster than Tactical Sweep's heal can refund, and right-click-cancelling her E stun denies the engage."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Watch the clock: once Camille finishes a second item her R isolation picks and true-damage burst outscale your duel, so close the game on your mid-game keg tempo before her full build comes online."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 last-hitting at the tip of Parrrley range so her E-hookshot all-in finds no free kill on your low base HP","Reach your Sheen/Trinity spike where empowered Q detonates a full keg chain and bursts her through Tactical Sweep's heal","Use W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse her E stun mid-combo, or right-click-cancel the stun, then out-heal the trade off missing HP"],"foe":["Land E-hookshot stun into the empowered Precision Protocol re-cast plus Tactical Sweep's outer true-damage cone while your barrels are on cooldown","Use her E wall-dash to reset and re-engage so you never get to kite the all-in cleanly with kegs","Stall to 2+ items, then catch you with R isolation near a wall to force a 1v1 her item lead and true damage win"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Camille — your Powder Keg has a long early cooldown with no chain online yet, your base HP is low enough for her to free-hit, and you have no real waveclear, so a single E-hookshot stun into Precision Protocol's empowered second cast (true damage on the timed re-hit) and Tactical Sweep's outer-edge true damage chunks you before a keg can come up. Last-hit at the tip of Parrrley range and never step up to drop a barrel she can simply walk onto and pop with you next to it. Hold W (Remove Scurvy) for her E — cleansing the stun mid-combo, or right-click-cancelling it, is your only real out here.","mid":"Levels 4-5 she still edges you because her all-in cooldowns refresh faster than your keg chain, but at 6 it evens out: Cannon Barrage zones and pressures the lane but doesn't win the straight duel, so neither of you can cleanly commit without a jungler. Start landing Parrrley-into-keg poke when she walks up to farm, and W-cleanse her E so her hookshot engage finds nothing to follow up. Do not fight near walls — her E wall-dash lets her reset the all-in and chase straight through your slow-zone kite.","late":"Once your Sheen/Trinity Force and full keg setup are online your mid-game tempo takes over — empowered Parrrley detonating a chained barrel set bursts and slows her faster than Tactical Sweep's heal can refund, and global Cannon Barrage gives you cross-map pressure she can't match. Press that window hard, because this is a race: Camille is the scaler, and once she finishes a second item her true-damage burst and R isolation reclaim the duel. The trap that kills you all game is her R — it locks you into a forced 1v1, so check her flank and never get caught alone near a wall before a fight opens.","whys":["Both of you are weak at level 1 — your barrel has a long cooldown and no chain yet, so just deny her last-hits and set the wave up rather than trading.","At 2 her E-hookshot stun into the empowered Precision Protocol re-cast lands before a single keg can detonate, so she wins the short trade outright.","Level 3 gives her the full E-Q-W combo with Tactical Sweep's true damage while your barrels still can't chain — last-hit safe and hold W for her stun.","Her all-in cooldowns refresh faster than your keg chain at 4-5, so she keeps the trade edge until your Parrrley-keg poke comes online.","Cannon Barrage zones and adds dive threat but doesn't win the 1v1, so the duel sits even at 6 unless she E-walls in for an isolation.","Sheen/Trinity empowers Parrrley to detonate a full keg chain — that burst beats Tactical Sweep's heal and flips the lane tempo to you.","Your mid-game keg detonations plus global R give you the tempo edge right after first item — cash it in fast, because she reclaims the duel once she hits two items."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"cassiopeia","win":["Gangplank","Skill","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1","text":"Cassiopeia has only Noxious Blast (Q), a slow skillshot, and no Miasma or Twin Fang yet — walk up, Parrrley her for the gold and chunk, and drop your first Powder Keg for waveclear while a single poison tick can't trade back."},{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Her window: once Miasma (W) is ranked she grounds you so you can't kite the cloud, and Twin Fang (E) refunds its cooldown off every poisoned tick — she out-DPSes you and your kegs die in one auto before they ever detonate."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Cassio's first-item spike (Lost Chapter / Lich Bane) lets her Twin Fang chain ramp hard, but your Sheen-empowered Parrrley detonating a Powder Keg is a real burst answer — the lane stays razor-thin, not a free win for either side."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Cassiopeia out-scales you: by two-plus items her grounding, poison ramp, and Petrifying Gaze let her kite your slowed keg zone and delete you before a barrel chain lands — your edge is the early kill, not the late duel."}],"wants":{"you":["Cash in Parrrley last-hits and a free first Powder Keg at level 1 while Cassiopeia only has one slow Noxious Blast skillshot to answer with","Hold Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse Petrifying Gaze (R) and heal off the poison — denying the grounded-stun-into-Twin-Fang chain that kills you","Hit your Sheen spike and trade with empowered Parrrley-into-chained-Powder-Keg before her Twin Fang ramp and two-item scaling take the lane"],"foe":["Land Miasma (W) to ground you so you can't reposition out of the poison cloud or sidestep a barrel detonation","Refund-chain Twin Fang (E) off every poison tick to out-DPS you through levels 3-6 before your kegs come online","Pin you with Petrifying Gaze (R) while you're grounded and ramp poison, then kite your slowed keg zone once she has two items"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours. Cassiopeia has only Noxious Blast (Q), a slow skillshot, and no Miasma or Twin Fang yet, so she can't punish you for stepping up. Parrrley her for the gold ping and a chunk, set your first Powder Keg for waveclear, and farm while her lone poison tick does nothing. The trap is greed: don't keep trading past level 2, because the moment Miasma and the Twin Fang refund chain come online she ramps DPS faster than your low-HP barrels can answer. Keep kegs placed for waveclear and zoning, not as bait she can free-auto, and respect that her no-boots passive move speed lets her hold the spacing.","mid":"Levels 3 through 6 belong to her, so play it honestly. Once she ranks Miasma (W) she grounds and slows you — that strips your repositioning and pins you in the poison cloud while Twin Fang (E) refunds its cooldown off every tick and out-DPSes you before a single keg detonates. Your barrels have long cooldowns and die to one of her autos, so don't set them where she can pop them, and don't walk into Noxious Blast range to throw a keg-Parrrley you can't follow up. Save Remove Scurvy (W) for her level-6 Petrifying Gaze — it stuns you only if you're facing her, but eating that lockdown while grounded is how you die, so cleanse it and heal the poison. Farm with Parrrley from max range, give ground, and wait for your item.","late":"This is the knife's edge. Your Sheen spike is real — an empowered Parrrley detonating a chained Powder Keg bursts a Cassiopeia who builds zero armor or magic resist, and the early-game gold lead from free Parrrley farm is what wins this lane. But be honest about the clock: she out-scales you, so by two-plus items her grounding, poison ramp, and Petrifying Gaze let her kite your slowed keg zone and delete you before a barrel chain lands. Set kegs around terrain so she can't pop them clean, bait the Miasma ground, cleanse it with W if she lands it, and blow her up at first item rather than waiting. Cannon Barrage (R) zones her off objectives and lets you collapse cross-map. Close it before she's three items deep, because then her range and poison out-trade even your barrels.","whys":["She has only a slow Noxious Blast skillshot and no Miasma or Twin Fang yet, so you Parrrley for the gold and set a free Powder Keg while her lone poison tick can't punish the step-up.","At level 2 she gets Miasma online but you still have one keg on a long cooldown — it's a genuine coin-flip on whether your Parrrley poke or her grounding-into-Twin-Fang lands first.","Her Miasma ground plus the Twin Fang cooldown refund off poison pins you in the cloud and out-DPSes you before your barrels are worth anything.","Ranked Q and W let her ground your retreat and chain near-continuous Twin Fang while your kegs die to one auto — she wins every extended trade in this window.","Petrifying Gaze stuns you if you're facing her while you're grounded and her poison ramps; hold Remove Scurvy to cleanse it, but the duel still goes to her at first item as her Twin Fang scaling kicks in.","Your Sheen spike is the answer — empowered Parrrley detonating a chained Powder Keg bursts a no-resistance Cassiopeia, and your early gold lead from free farm is how you take this lane.","Set barrels around terrain, bait the Miasma, and cleanse her R with Remove Scurvy — burst her in the explosion window now, because past three items she out-scales you and kites your slowed kegs."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"chogath","win":["Skill","Gangplank","Cho'Gath","Cho'Gath","Cho'Gath","Cho'Gath","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Your second Parrrley point lets you poke from outside his Q (Rupture) cast range and chip his thin early HP bar before Feast kills start padding it."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Feast (R) comes online: a flat true-damage execute that ignores your W heal and your armor, so a Q-knockup into Feast can finish you out of any low trade."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen empowers Parrrley and your keg pops, but his Feast-and-item HP pool now soaks single-keg poke faster than one item lets you burst it."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Cho keeps scaling — each Feast kill is permanent max HP, and his true-damage Feast plus tank items mean even your chained kegs can't out-trade his bar in an extended fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke from outside Rupture (Q) range with Parrrley-into-keg and never sit at the HP where Feast (R) can true-damage execute you","Hold W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse his Rupture knockup and heal the Feral Scream-into-AA follow-up rather than burning it early","Snowball the lane early and roam with Cannon Barrage before Cho's Feast stacks and tank items make him unkillable"],"foe":["Land Rupture (Q) to knock you up, then Feral Scream (W) silence so you can't Parrrley-detonate or cleanse before he commits","Farm safely and bank Feast (R) kills on minions and big monsters to balloon his permanent max HP out of your poke range","Reach 2+ items where his true-damage Feast and tank stats let him walk through your keg chain and one-shot you in a teamfight"]},"early":"Level 1 is a wash — neither of you wants the trade, so just last-hit while you both look for the first Powder Keg setup. From level 2 your second Parrrley lets you start chipping him: float a keg behind the wave, Q-pop it as he steps up to farm, and punish his thin early HP bar before any Feast kills pad it. Stay outside his Q (Rupture) cast range while your barrels are down — eating the knockup hands him a free Feral Scream silence and a melee trade — and keep W (Remove Scurvy) for the moment he lands Rupture so you cleanse the knockup and heal the follow-up.","mid":"This is Cho's window, and it pivots on his level 6. Feast (R) is a flat true-damage execute that ignores your W heal, your armor, and your sustain, so the cardinal rule is never sit at execute HP — if you trade down low, his Rupture-into-silence-into-Feast finishes you no matter how much you cleanse. Keep poking from keg range, but respect that his Feral Scream (W) silence shuts off your Parrrley-detonate and your cleanse mid-combo if he lands Q first. Farm the lane even and let his Feast cooldown dictate when you step up; your single-item kegs can't break a Cho who's banked even one or two stacks of permanent HP.","late":"Cho only gets harder to kill — every Feast stack is permanent max HP, and stacked with tank items plus his true-damage R he out-scales your keg burst in a straight 1v1. Your edge late is the map, not the duel: Cannon Barrage zones him off objectives and sieges where his immobility hurts, and a clean Parrrley-keg chain can still burst squishier targets around him. Don't force solo all-ins into his Rupture once he's stacked — make him eat the keg explosion at range, bait or wait out Feast, and use your global pressure rather than trying to out-trade a wall of HP.","whys":["Neither of you wants the level-1 trade — he hoards mana for Q-Rupture, you have no keg chain yet, so it's a pure last-hit standoff.","Your second Parrrley lets you poke his thin early HP bar from outside Rupture range before any Feast kills pad it — the early window is yours.","Cho out-sustains your single-keg poke once he banks a Feast stack; his Q knockup plus melee trade lets him farm through the chip.","His Feral Scream (W) silence and Rupture (Q) knockup can lock you out of detonating or cleansing mid-pattern, swinging the trade his way.","Feast (R) is a flat true-damage execute that ignores your W heal and armor — at 6 he can finish you out of any low-HP trade.","Your Sheen spike helps, but his Feast-and-item HP pool is tankier than one item of keg burst can break, so he holds the lane.","Cannon Barrage's global pressure lets you reclaim tempo on the map — roaming and sieging where his immobility hurts beats dueling his HP wall."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"darius","win":["Darius","Darius","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Darius E-pulls you in the moment you step up for a melee CS and lands a full-blade Q that heals off you while stacking Hemorrhage bleed — this is his hardest window and your kegs aren't online to answer."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen from a Trinity/Essence Reaver path comes online: an empowered Parrrley plus a chained Powder Keg detonation finally lets you burst him from outside E-pull range without ever trading autos."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage zones his all-in and saves you from a gank, but it doesn't win the straight duel — use it to deny his Noxian Guillotine reset, not to fight him head-on."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Chained keg detonations clear the wave instantly and zone him off CS; you out-range his entire kit and only fear a fed Darius landing one clean Apprehend."}],"wants":{"you":["Last-hit with Parrrley from max range so you never stand inside his Apprehend (E) pull radius","Drop Powder Kegs between you and Darius and detonate them with Q to farm and poke from range without melee trading","Save Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse his E pull and Hemorrhage slow plus heal the bleed, then disengage to scale"],"foe":["Land Apprehend (E) to drag you in, then hit the outer blade of Q to heal off you and pile on Hemorrhage stacks","Force short melee trades at levels 1-3 before your barrels and first item come online","Stack 5 Hemorrhage bleeds and execute with Noxian Guillotine (R) to snowball and reset before you scale"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are his, full stop — you have no waveclear and your Powder Kegs have long cooldowns and low HP he can free-hit to deny, so do NOT contest CS in melee range. The thing that ends you is his Apprehend (E): if he pulls you in, he lands the outer blade of his Q to heal off you and starts stacking Hemorrhage. Last-hit with Parrrley only, sit a keg-length behind your minions, and accept that you lose every short trade here. Hold Remove Scurvy (W) for the moment he commits the E, not before.","mid":"Levels 4-6 you stabilize into even — more points in Q and E let you start the Parrrley-into-keg poke that he has to walk through to farm, and that range is the whole point of the lane. Drop a barrel on your side of the wave and pop it with Q so he eats the AoE slow and damage without ever pulling you. At 6 your Cannon Barrage is for zoning his all-in and denying his Guillotine reset, not a head-on duel — he still wins the melee scrum, so make him choose between farming and eating barrels.","late":"This is where the 53.97% comes from. By two items your chained keg detonations zone him completely off the wave and burst him from outside Apprehend range — he simply cannot touch you unless he lands a clean E, and your W cleanses exactly that. Keep kegs between you at all times, never give him a flat path to pull, and let empowered Parrrley plus the barrel chain do the work. The only thing that flips it back is a Darius who got fed off your early levels and one-shots you with a single E into bleed-stacked Guillotine, so deny that snowball and the lane is yours.","whys":["Darius walks you down at level 1 — he E-pulls and lands a full Q to heal off you while you have no waveclear or barrel pressure to answer.","Still his: a level-2 Apprehend into a healing Q plus early Hemorrhage stacks beats anything your single keg can do back.","It evens out — Parrrley range and a second keg let you last-hit and poke without stepping into his pull, so neither side gets a clean kill.","Skill window: you poke with Q-into-keg from range while he tries to land a pull; whoever respects the other's cooldown wins the trade.","Cannon Barrage zones his all-in and denies his Guillotine reset, but it doesn't out-duel him, so the stage stays a coin-flip on positioning.","Your Sheen-and-keg spike lets you burst him from outside E range — but a fed Darius still kills you through one pull, so it stays genuinely even.","Yours now: chained keg detonations clear the wave and zone him off CS from beyond Apprehend range, and W cleanses the one E he needs to fight you."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"drmundo","win":["Gangplank","Skill","Dr. Mundo","Dr. Mundo","Skill","Dr. Mundo","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1","text":"Parrrley out-ranges his Infected Cleaver, so you get a free pistol last-hit and a barrel placed before his passive regen even ramps — the one window you out-stat him."},{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Mundo's spike: low-cooldown Q percent-HP cleaves out-poke your single-keg chip, his passive heals it back, and he can walk up and free-hit your low-HP keg to deny the detonation."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage gives you the global play he can't match — zone his jungler off a dive or shove and bomb a sidelane while you can't out-duel a drain-tank yourself."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver Parrrley plus a full chained Powder Keg detonation finally out-bursts his regen in one combo — but only if you kill him before Maximum Dosage heals it all back."}],"wants":{"you":["Free-hit your level 1 Parrrley and place a barrel before his passive regen ramps up","Reach the Sheen/keg build so a full chained Powder Keg detonation bursts past his heal in one window","Use Cannon Barrage for cross-map plays and to deny his dives while you farm and scale safely"],"foe":["Spam low-cooldown Q cleavers to percent-HP poke you and shove you off your barrel setup","Walk up and free-hit your low-HP kegs with autos so the chain never detonates","Stall to 2-3 items where Maximum Dosage and percent-HP cleavers make him impossible to one-combo"]},"early":"Mundo is one of the few melees you actually out-stat at level 1 — Parrrley out-ranges his Infected Cleaver, so chip him and drop a barrel before his passive regen ramps. The catch: his Q is percent-HP poke that ignores your low durability, and from level 3 his Q-spam plus passive heal out-sustains your single-keg chip. Don't trade autos into him, and never set up a slow barrel he can just walk up and free-hit to deny the detonation — bait his cleaver, then last-hit safely with Q.","mid":"This is his window, not yours. With his Q on a low cooldown he percent-HP pokes you while his passive heals every bit of your barrel chip, and his E adds bonus damage to his autos so walking up to detonate kegs costs you the trade. At 6 your Cannon Barrage isn't a duel button against a drain-tank — use it to zone his jungler off a dive or to shove and bomb a sidelane while you farm, because one keg won't kill a champ who heals through it. Hold your barrel chain for when his Q is on cooldown.","late":"If you reach 2+ items with the Sheen/keg build, you flip it: empowered Parrrley plus a full chained Powder Keg detonation finally bursts faster than his regen can answer — but you must blow him up BEFORE Maximum Dosage. If his R is up, you cannot kill him in lane, so play it as a teamfight: stack barrels on chokes, zone with the chain, and let Cannon Barrage pick off his squishier teammates instead of dumping everything into an unkillable Mundo.","whys":["Parrrley out-ranges his Infected Cleaver and you free-hit a barrel before his passive regen even ramps — the one early window you out-stat him.","He starts spamming percent-HP Q cleavers that ignore your low durability, but you still chip back with ranged Parrrley last-hits — roughly even.","His low-cooldown Q-spam plus passive heal out-sustains your single-keg chip, and he free-hits your low-HP barrels to deny the chain.","His percent-HP Infected Cleaver out-pokes you and his regen erases your barrel chip faster than you can stack a chain — his strongest lane window.","Cannon Barrage gives you a global play he can't answer, but it doesn't win the 1v1 against a drain-tank, so the stage nets out even.","Even at first items his percent-HP cleavers plus regen still beat your first keg spike one-for-one — you can't one-combo him yet.","With Sheen/Essence Reaver Parrrley a full chained keg detonation finally bursts past his regen — just kill him before Maximum Dosage heals it back."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"fiora","win":["Fiora","Fiora","Skill","Gangplank","Fiora","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Fiora Q-dashes onto you and procs a passive Vital for percent-max-HP true damage while your barrels (E) are on a long cooldown and easy to free-hit and deny — concede the auto trades."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her Grand Challenge all-in: she Q-dashes in, can Riposte (W) your Parrrley or keg-detonation auto to stun you mid-combo, and the ult forces four Vitals you cannot kite — Cannon Barrage zones but does not win the straight duel, so respect it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver is the flip: an empowered Parrrley plus a full chained Powder Keg detonation bursts her from outside her Q-dash range before she can stack a Vital on you."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Chained keg detonations plus global Cannon Barrage let you zone every objective and one-shot — the only caveat is a fed, fully-scaled Fiora reclaiming the 1v1 splitpush if the game drags."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 by last-hitting with Parrrley (Q) at range — never place a keg (E) she can free-hit to deny, and don't trade autos into her Vitals","Detonate Powder Kegs with Parrrley from max range so she eats the blast and slow from outside her Q-dash and Riposte range","Bait her Riposte with a fake step or throwaway Parrrley, then commit the real keg chain on its cooldown"],"foe":["Land Riposte (W) on your Parrrley or keg-detonation auto to stun you and deny the chain","Q-dash onto you while your barrels are on cooldown and stack passive Vitals for true damage","Out-trade your weak early lane and snowball before your first-item keg spike comes online"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are hers — accept it. She Q-dashes onto you and her Vitals chunk percent-max-HP true damage while my barrels sit on a long cooldown with low base HP, so do NOT place a keg she can free-hit to deny. Last-hit with Parrrley from range, eat a little, and never trade autos into her — if she sticks to me she wins every short exchange before I have a keg pattern. Remember W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses her Riposte stun and heals off missing HP, so save it for when she commits a real all-in, not for poke.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are my stabilizer: a second point in Parrrley/Powder Keg means I can land Parrrley-into-keg poke and detonate barrels from outside her Q-dash range, so she has to walk into my zone to farm. The whole trade revolves around her Riposte — if I detonate a keg or throw Parrrley while it is up, she parries it, stuns me, and the trade flips. Bait the Riposte with a fake step or a throwaway Q, then commit the real keg chain on its cooldown. At 6 her Grand Challenge plus Q-dash all-in beats my Cannon Barrage in a straight duel, so don't greed level-6 fights without the wave or jungler.","late":"Once my first item lands (Sheen/Essence Reaver into the keg build) this flips for good — an empowered Parrrley plus a full Powder Keg chain bursts her before she ever stacks a Vital, and I detonate from range she can't cleanly dash through. By 2+ items I own it: chained kegs one-shot and global Cannon Barrage zones her off every objective. The one honest caveat is that Fiora is also a scaler — if I let her get fed and the game drags, a fully-online Fiora can Riposte my key cast and out-duel the 1v1, so close the lead and don't let her splitpush me late.","whys":["She Q-dashes onto me and procs Vitals for true damage while my barrels are on a long cooldown and free to deny — I just last-hit with Parrrley and concede the trade.","Her level-2 Q-dash plus passive Vital out-trades me before I have a keg pattern; I farm at range and don't contest autos.","Even here — my full kit is online for keg-poke, but her Riposte can still parry my detonation and stun me, so neither of us cleanly owns the short trade.","With a second keg point I poke Parrrley-into-barrel from outside her Q-dash range and bait Riposte before committing — she must walk into my zone to farm.","Her Grand Challenge plus Q-dash all-in forces Vitals I can't kite, and Cannon Barrage doesn't win the straight duel — I respect her level-6 spike.","Sheen/Essence Reaver empowers Parrrley and my full keg chain bursts her from range before she lands a Vital — the matchup flips here.","Chained keg detonations and global Cannon Barrage let me zone and one-shot her — I only lose this back if a fed, fully-scaled Fiora Ripostes my key cast late."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"galio","win":["Skill","Galio","Galio","Galio","Galio","Galio","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1","text":"Free-hit his keg before it matures and Parrrley his minions for poke, but Galio's Colossal Smash passive auto and Winds of War (Q) tornado out-range and out-trade your single Q this early."},{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Galio's window: Winds of War (Q) zoning plus his Colossal Smash passive auto chunk you, and a Justice Punch (E) into Durand's Shield (W) taunt can drag you onto your own keg while your barrels are still on cooldown."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen or Essence Reaver onto the keg setup starts to flip it — empowered Parrrley plus a chained-barrel detonation finally pressures through the MR he stacks against your kit."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Your power peak: chained Powder Keg explosions plus global Cannon Barrage (R) pressure outscale a tanky Galio whose Justice Punch / Durand's Shield burst can no longer kill you."}],"wants":{"you":["Last-hit at Parrrley (Q) range and free-hit his keg-equivalent, but respect Winds of War (Q) and his Colossal Smash passive auto until your barrels come online","Survive to your Sheen/Essence Reaver keg spike, then detonate a chained-barrel chain to pressure through the MR he stacks against you","Scale to 2+ items where chained kegs plus global Cannon Barrage (R) make his tank body and fading burst irrelevant"],"foe":["Poke with Winds of War (Q) and walk you down with Colossal Smash passive autos while your kegs sit on cooldown","Land Justice Punch (E) into a Durand's Shield (W) taunt to drag you onto your own keg or set up a jungler collapse","Stack magic resist to blunt your keg burst and stall the lane until his global Hero's Entrance (R) decides a fight elsewhere"]},"early":"Galio's early phase is the real one here — his Colossal Smash passive auto and Winds of War (Q) tornado out-poke and out-trade your single Parrrley at level 1, and your barrels have long cooldowns and low HP he can free-hit to deny. Don't try to fight him early: last-hit at Q range and place kegs where his Q can't cheaply pop them. The one thing in your favor — Remove Scurvy (W) cleanses his taunt and heals, so a landed Justice Punch (E) into Durand's Shield (W) isn't the death sentence it is for most melees, and you can also right-click-cancel the taunt with his passive.","mid":"This is his window, not yours. Durand's Shield (W) channels damage reduction and releases a taunt, and if he Justice-Punches (E) you in and taunts you onto a matured barrel you eat the chip and the CC anyway. Don't waste a full chain into his W channel — bait it, hold your detonation, and cleanse the taunt with Remove Scurvy (W) if he lands it. At 6 his Hero's Entrance (R) is a global roaming threat more than a lane duel-winner; ping it for your team and play for your own item spike instead of trading into his.","late":"Now you take over. Once Sheen/Essence Reaver and a second item land, empowered Parrrley plus a chained-keg chain pressures through the magic resist he stacked faster than his Justice Punch / Durand's Shield burst can answer, and he has no kill pressure left on you. He's an AP tank — once he can't blow you up through your W cleanse, he's just a frontline you zone with barrels and global Cannon Barrage (R). Force the sidelane, chain your kegs, and let your scaling and global R pressure decide it.","whys":["You can free-hit his keg-equivalent and Parrrley for gold, but his Colossal Smash passive auto plus Winds of War (Q) out-trade your single Q — last-hit and don't fight to keep it even.","Galio gets Winds of War (Q) zoning and his passive autos online while your barrels are still on long cooldown — short trades go his way here.","Durand's Shield (W) damage reduction blunts your keg detonation while his Winds of War poke chunks you; you can't win a straight trade pre-item.","He out-sustains your pre-item poke and can Justice Punch (E) into a Durand's Shield (W) taunt to drag you onto a matured barrel for the chip and the CC — concede and farm.","Cannon Barrage (R) adds zoning but doesn't out-duel his E-into-W-taunt plus Winds of War burst at this stage, so the window stays his.","The magic resist he stacks against your kit still eats your first-item keg burst on a duel — respect Durand's Shield and don't all-in into the W channel yet.","Sheen/Essence Reaver onto chained kegs plus global Cannon Barrage (R) outscales a kill-less tank Galio — this is where the lane flips to you."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"gnar","win":["Gnar","Skill","Gangplank","Gnar","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Mini-Gnar out-ranges you: Boomerang Throw (Q) pokes from outside Parrrley range and his Hyper passive (every 3rd hit on the same target = bonus damage + slow) chunks you if you walk up to last-hit. Eat the poke and farm safe — your kegs aren't online to fight back yet."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"With a second Parrrley and Powder Keg point you place a barrel and Q-detonate it from range, chunking mini-Gnar without stepping into boomerang range — your first real window to win trades."},{"when":"Mega transform","text":"Gnar's biggest swing: a full Rage Bar turns him into mega-Gnar with GNAR! (R), which throws you and stuns if you hit a wall — plus a big tankiness spike. If he catches your all-in here he flips the trade, so don't commit while the bar is near full."},{"when":"1st item (Sheen)","text":"Your Sheen-line spike flips it for good: Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation bursts mini-Gnar before mega comes back, and he can't kite a barrel chain that's already pre-placed on him."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the level 1-3 boomerang phase by farming with Parrrley range, then start placing kegs at 4-5 to Q-detonate from outside his Q so you trade without eating Hyper procs","Track his Rage Bar and hold W (Remove Scurvy) for the moment he transforms — cleanse the GNAR! wall-stun and heal back the poke instead of wasting it on the boomerang","Hit your Sheen/Essence Reaver keg spike and chain-detonate pre-placed barrels to burst him down while he's stuck in fragile mini form"],"foe":["Stay in mini form and kite with Boomerang Throw (Q) plus Hyper move speed, poking you down and refusing to give you a clean keg-detonation trade","Fill the Rage Bar and catch your all-in with the GNAR! (R) wall-crash stun, then burst you during the stun while your W is on cooldown","Use his early range and Hyper procs to deny you CS under tower and stall you off your first-item keg spike"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to mini-Gnar. Boomerang Throw (Q) out-ranges your Parrrley, and if you walk up to last-hit he stacks his Hyper passive — every third hit on you deals bonus damage and slows, so the short trades go his way. Don't try to fight here: your Powder Kegs have long cooldowns and aren't online to punish him yet. Last-hit at max Parrrley range, accept some boomerang poke, and watch his Rage Bar — you do NOT want to be caught in an all-in when it fills into mega.","mid":"At 4-5 you stabilize. A second Parrrley and Powder Keg point let you place a barrel and Q-detonate it from range, chunking mini-Gnar without stepping into his boomerang. The one danger is the transform: when the Rage Bar fills, GNAR! (R) throws you and stuns if you hit a wall, and mega-Gnar gets a real tankiness spike — so save W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse that stun and heal the poke rather than burning it early. Bait the mega timer: trade hard while he's fragile mini, back off the instant the bar caps.","late":"Once your keg build comes online this is your lane. A Sheen-line proc on Parrrley plus a chained barrel detonation bursts fragile mini-Gnar faster than he can kite away, and Cannon Barrage (R) zones him off objectives across the map. He stays relevant in teamfights with the GNAR! stun, but in the straight 1v1 side lane you out-range and out-scale him — pre-place keg chains against walls so he can't dash out, and never facecheck while his Rage Bar is full and a wall is behind you.","whys":["Mini-Gnar's Boomerang Throw (Q) out-ranges your Parrrley and his Hyper passive (bonus damage + slow on every 3rd hit) punishes you if you walk up — the early short trades go to him.","He keeps kiting with boomerang plus Hyper move speed while your kegs are still on long cooldowns; you can't punish yet, so this stays a farm-and-skill standoff.","Your second Parrrley and Powder Keg point let you place a barrel and Q-detonate it from outside his Q — first real window where you out-trade mini-Gnar.","Mega-Gnar's GNAR! (R) can throw you into a wall for a stun plus his tankiness spike; if he catches your commit here he flips it, so the transform window is his.","Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation bursts him while he's stuck in fragile mini form — your first-item spike takes the lane over.","Pre-placed keg chains on walls remove his kite, and a Sheen proc plus barrel burst out-damages a squishy mini-Gnar before mega returns.","At 2+ items your chained kegs and global Cannon Barrage out-range and out-scale a kiting Gnar in the 1v1 — pin him to a wall and detonate."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"gragas","win":["Gragas","Gragas","Skill","Gangplank","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Gragas throws Barrel Roll (Q) to poke and slow you for free while your single early Powder Keg has low HP and dies to one of his autos if you place it carelessly."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Second Q and E points let you Parrrley-detonate chained kegs from range, out-poking his Barrel Roll lobs before he can Body Slam (E) in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver online: empowered Parrrley plus a full keg chain bursts him faster than his W (Drunken Rage) damage reduction can tank."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Explosive Cask (R) can knock you into his tower or punt you off your own keg cluster, and Body Slam (E) stuns on collision — respect the displacement when he hits 6 before you do."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive his level 1-3 Barrel Roll poke without feeding free barrel-denies, then reach your Parrrley-into-keg poke at 4-5","Detonate chained Powder Kegs with Parrrley from outside his Body Slam range so he eats burst without trading back","Stack your first item and use the keg-chain burst to win every all-in while his W damage reduction is on cooldown"],"foe":["Lob Barrel Roll to poke you down levels 1-3 and walk up to free-hit your low-HP single keg, denying the barrel you need to scale","Body Slam (E) in, drink W to tank your keg burst, then Explosive Cask (R) to punt you toward his tower or off your kegs","Use Drunken Rage sustain and his E-Q stun-and-poke combo to win short trades before your barrels chain"]},"early":"Gragas owns these levels and you know it. His Barrel Roll (Q) lobs free poke and a slow over the wall while you can only last-hit, and he can walk up to auto your single low-HP Powder Keg off the map, denying the barrel you need to scale. Do not place a keg where he can casually pop it; hold E for waveclear or to threaten his all-in. Last-hit with the tip of Parrrley, eat the Q chip, and refuse to trade autos into his W (Drunken Rage) damage-reduction-and-sustain window — that drink heals him through anything short. Your job here is just to not die and not get barrels denied.","mid":"This is where the lane flips. At 4-5 your second Q and E points let you land Parrrley-into-keg poke from outside his Body Slam (E) range, so he takes chip every time he walks up to farm while you stay safe behind the barrel slow. The danger is his level-6 Explosive Cask: if he hits 6 first he can Body Slam in and R-knock you into his tower or punt you off your own keg cluster, so respect the displacement and don't over-extend on a chain. Bait his E engage, sidestep the cask, then detonate your keg chain on top of him as he commits and burns W.","late":"You take over hard from your first item on. Sheen or Essence Reaver into the keg build means empowered Parrrley plus a full chained detonation bursts him through his W damage reduction, and he has no scaling answer the way Vladimir or Kayle would — he's an even-AP brawler, not a hyperscaler. Keep him out of your barrel cluster with the chained slow, sidestep his Body Slam, and use Cannon Barrage to zone teamfights or pressure other lanes. Just never let his Explosive Cask punt you into a wall while your kegs are on cooldown.","whys":["Gragas lobs Barrel Roll (Q) for free poke and a slow at level 1 and can auto your single low-HP keg to deny it — you have no answer yet.","Still his window: his Drunken Rage (W) drink out-sustains your chip and tanks any auto trade you try before your barrels chain.","You get a second point and can start Parrrley poke, but his E-Q stun-and-poke combo keeps short trades genuinely even here.","Your Parrrley-into-keg poke from outside Body Slam range now out-damages his Barrel Roll and punishes him for walking up to farm.","His Explosive Cask can punt you out of your keg cluster and Cannon Barrage isn't a duel spike — coordinated displacement decides it, so it's even.","Sheen/Essence Reaver empowers Parrrley and your keg chain bursts him through W damage reduction — force every all-in.","He's an even-AP brawler with no hyperscaling, so your chained keg detonations and global R own him through the late game."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"garen","win":["Garen","Garen","Skill","Garen","Skill","Skill","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Garen's Decisive Strike silences you for 1.5s and runs you down with bonus move speed and a big empowered strike — with only one low-HP keg up, never trade into a fresh Q."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"A second Parrrley and your second Powder Keg point let you place a barrel he must path through, then detonate it from range so he eats the AoE slow before he reaches you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen or Essence Reaver makes your next Parrrley a Spellblade nuke; that empowered shot into a chained keg blast finally out-trades his Q-strike-into-Judgment-spin."},{"when":"Late","text":"At 2+ items a full chained keg detonation chunks him through Courage's damage reduction before his Demacian Justice execute threshold is reached, and Cannon Barrage zones him off you in fights."}],"wants":{"you":["Place a Powder Keg on his approach path and pop it with Parrrley so Garen takes the explosion slow walking up to Judgment-spin you","Hold Remove Scurvy for his Decisive Strike silence-and-slow, then heal the chip back once his Q-strike combo is spent","Stall to your Sheen/Essence Reaver keg spike and 2+ items, where empowered Parrrley plus chained barrels out-bursts his Q+E+R all-in"],"foe":["Open with Decisive Strike to silence your Parrrley and slow you, then close with bonus move speed and Judgment-spin while your keg is on cooldown","Pop Courage for damage reduction and tenacity to eat your keg burst, then break off into brush to regen untargeted","Wait for you below the Demacian Justice missing-HP line, then Q-flash in for the true-damage execute before Remove Scurvy can save you"]},"early":"Garen owns these first levels, not me. His Decisive Strike silences my Parrrley for 1.5s, slows me, and lands a chunky empowered hit, and his passive regen means whatever poke I do land just heals off when he ducks into brush. My first keg has a long cooldown and low HP, so he can pre-detonate it with an auto to deny it, or just bonus-speed walk me down through the silence. Last-hit with the tip of Parrrley, never throw a keg I can't pop before he commits, and save Remove Scurvy for the silence-and-slow rather than greeding it for the heal.","mid":"By levels 4-5 I stabilize. A second Parrrley and a second Powder Keg point let me set a barrel on his path and make him eat the AoE slow every time he steps up to Judgment-spin. He still edges the level-4 window because a fresh Decisive Strike out-trades me if I commit into it, so I only poke when his Q is on cooldown. Level 6 is a coinflip: Cannon Barrage zones him off the wave and threatens a dive, but it doesn't win the straight duel against Courage's damage reduction, so I use it for waves and skirmishes, not to fight him head-on.","late":"This is where I take over. Once Sheen or Essence Reaver comes online, my next Parrrley is a Spellblade nuke, and that empowered shot into a chained Powder Keg blast finally out-bursts his Q-strike-into-spin combo. By 2+ items a full keg chain chunks him through Courage before his Demacian Justice execute threshold is even reachable. He has no range and no answer to barrels detonating from across the lane — keep him eating chip, deny him brush time to regen untargeted, and drop Cannon Barrage on him the moment he tries to spin in.","whys":["Garen's Decisive Strike silences my Parrrley and slows me while his passive regen heals my poke — at level 1 with one low-HP keg I have no answer to his bonus-speed walk-up.","He hits level 2 with the Q silence plus early Judgment ranks and can all-in through my single barrel before I get a clean detonation off, so I concede this and farm safe.","My second keg lets me start placing barriers on his path, but a fresh Decisive Strike still out-trades me on commit, leaving the level-3 window genuinely even.","Garen edges level 4 — his Q-strike into spin beats my trade whenever Decisive Strike is up, so I only poke when it's on cooldown.","Cannon Barrage zones and threatens a dive but doesn't beat Courage's damage reduction in a straight duel, so the level-6 fight is a coinflip.","My Sheen/Essence Reaver keg spike trades roughly with his Spellblade-spin burst — empowered Parrrley starts to bite, but Courage still soaks one explosion, keeping it even.","At 2+ items a chained keg detonation chunks him past Courage before his missing-HP Demacian Justice can connect, and he has no range to escape the barrels — I own the late game."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"graves","win":["Graves","Graves","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Graves out-bursts you with double-shell shotgun autos and free-hits your low-HP Powder Kegs to deny them before they ever detonate."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your second Q and E point land real Parrrley-into-keg poke, so you can finally chip him when he walks up to last-hit."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Collateral Damage window is the danger spike — the R cone plus Quickdraw dash and a Smoke Screen blind let him all-in you, while your Cannon Barrage only zones."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen or Essence Reaver into a full keg chain is where you flip the lane — empowered Parrrley plus chained detonations finally out-damage his shotgun."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 with cannon Q last-hits and place kegs out of his auto range so he cannot free-hit them","Reach your first item so empowered Parrrley plus a chained Powder Keg detonation out-bursts his shotgun trade","Use Remove Scurvy to cleanse his Smoke Screen blind and his End of the Line slow, then heal the burst back"],"foe":["Free-hit your Powder Kegs with shotgun autos to deny your detonation before it sets up","Burst you in short trades levels 1-3 with double-shell shotgun autos and disengage on his Quickdraw dash","Drop Smoke Screen on you to blind your Parrrley and Q-poke, then collapse with Collateral Damage when you are zoned off the wave"]},"early":"Graves owns these levels and you cannot fight it head-on — his double-shell shotgun autos out-burst your single Parrrley, and worse, he just walks up and free-hits your Powder Kegs to pop them before they ever detonate, denying your whole kit. Do not place a keg in his auto range expecting value; set them at the edge of your control just to zone and CS with cannon Q last-hits. Respect that his Smoke Screen blinds your Parrrley, so save your trades for when it is on cooldown.","mid":"Now you stabilize. With a second Q and E point you can land Parrrley into a keg detonation when he steps up to farm, chipping him without committing to a brawl you would lose. At 6 stay disciplined — his Collateral Damage cone, Quickdraw dash, and Smoke Screen make HIS ultimate window the all-in, not yours; your Cannon Barrage only zones and skirmishes, it does not win the duel. Hold Remove Scurvy to cleanse his End of the Line slow and the Smoke Screen blind, heal the poke back, and keep farming toward your item spike.","late":"This is where you take over — once Sheen or Essence Reaver is online, empowered Parrrley plus a chained Powder Keg explosion finally out-damages his shotgun, and by two-plus items your keg burst one-shots him through his ADC durability while Cannon Barrage pressures the whole map. He does not out-scale you the way a Kayle or Vladimir does, so you reclaim the matchup outright. Just punish every time he over-extends without his Quickdraw dash up, and use your global R to swing fights across the map.","whys":["Graves out-bursts your single Parrrley with double-shell shotgun autos and free-hits your low-HP kegs to deny them before they detonate.","His shotgun autos win every short trade while your barrels are on long cooldown and one keg does nothing alone.","Your second Q point lets you start landing Parrrley-into-keg poke, so the lane levels off into an even farm fight.","You can poke him with Q-into-keg when he walks up, but he answers with shotgun burst and a Smoke Screen blind — it stays a skill matchup.","His Collateral Damage plus Quickdraw dash plus Smoke Screen all-in is real, but your Remove Scurvy cleanse and heal keep it even since your Cannon Barrage only zones.","Sheen or Essence Reaver makes empowered Parrrley plus a full keg chain out-burst his shotgun, flipping the lane to you.","By two-plus items your chained keg detonations one-shot him through his ADC durability and he does not hyperscale past you like Kayle does."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"gwen","win":["Gwen","Skill","Gangplank","Gwen","Gangplank","Gwen","Gwen"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Skip 'n Slash (E) dashes her onto you with empowered, attack-speed autos while Snip Snip (Q) true-damages your HP bar; she just stands in Hallowed Mist (W) so your Parrrley and keg detonation hit the cloud, not her."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage (R) carpets the tile her mist sits on — the AoE makes her vacate the cloud or eat sustained artillery, so this is your one window to zone her off the wave or a Grub while she's pinned."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver empowers Parrrley to one-shot-detonate a full keg chain, but it only lands the instant she steps OUT of mist or finishes an E dash — mistime it and she resets E and dances out untouched."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, Needlework (R) and Thousand-Cuts true damage out-sustain your Trial-by-Fire DoT; she E-resets through your barrel zone and pops mist on your big keg-chain burst, and her scaling simply outruns your kit."}],"wants":{"you":["Detonate the keg chain with empowered Parrrley the exact frame Hallowed Mist drops or her Skip 'n Slash dash ends — that's the only time she's targetable in the open","Use Cannon Barrage to flush her off the mist tile and zone her from farm, Grubs, or a recall instead of trying to out-trade her in melee","Win the Level 6 and first-item windows into a side-lane lead, then split-push with R pressure rather than dueling her scaling at 2+ items"],"foe":["Sit in Hallowed Mist to go untargetable and let your Parrrley and barrel detonations waste themselves on the cloud","Snip Snip with Q true damage and Skip 'n Slash resets to shred your HP and heal off Thousand Cuts regardless of your resists","Stall the lane even and reach her two-item Needlework powerspike, where her max-HP damage and E kiting beat your keg burst"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are hers and you have to accept it — your barrels (E) have long cooldowns and little HP, and Gwen just Skip 'n Slashes (E) onto you, snips you with true-damage Q, and drops Hallowed Mist (W) so your Parrrley and keg detonation hit the smoke instead of her. Don't fish for short trades; last-hit at max Parrrley range and pre-place a single barrel between you and the wave purely to discourage her dash-in. Remove Scurvy (W) is dead weight as a cleanse here — she has no hard CC — so save it purely as a missing-HP heal for when her snips and Thousand-Cuts autos chunk you below half.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize with a second keg/Parrrley point, but Hallowed Mist is the whole problem: it has a long cooldown, so this window is about baiting the mist out — on a wave or a committed dash — then Parrrley-detonating the keg chain the moment she's forced to step out of it. Level 6 is your real spike: Cannon Barrage carpets the exact tile her mist sits on, and since the artillery is an AoE she has to move through, she can't turtle in the cloud while your barrels and R zone her off the wave or a Grub. Force every skirmish here on her mist cooldown, not before.","late":"This is where you lose if it goes long. Gwen is a hard scaler: two items deep her Q true damage cuts through every point of MR you bought, her Thousand-Cuts healing out-sustains your Trial-by-Fire DoT, Skip 'n Slash resets let her dance in and out of your barrel zone, and Hallowed Mist eats your one big keg-chain burst every fight. Your job is to have already converted the Level 6 and first-item windows into a side-lane lead you can pressure with Cannon Barrage. If it's even at three items, don't duel her over a barrel she can just mist or E through — group, use R to swing other fights globally, and let your team collapse on her instead of soloing the scaler.","whys":["She Skip 'n Slashes in, snips with true-damage Q, and drops Hallowed Mist so your low-HP barrels and Parrrley waste on the cloud — your worst stretch of the lane.","You get your second keg point and a barrel down, but she can still mist or E-reset out of any trade you start, so the window is a genuine toss-up.","Cannon Barrage carpets her mist tile — the AoE forces her out of the cloud while your kegs and artillery zone her off farm and Grubs; your cleanest, only-clear stage.","Even with Sheen/Essence Reaver, your empowered keg chain only connects when she's OUT of mist or mid-dash — she can dodge the one detonation, so she still edges the window.","Your first big Parrrley-detonation spike lets you actually punish a mistimed mist cooldown and threaten a kill on the wave, the rare moment you out-burst her.","Her Hallowed Mist and Skip 'n Slash spacing contest every barrel you place; without your burst up she kites the keg zone and heals through your poke.","Two items in, her Q true damage ignores your stacked MR, Needlework and E-resets kite the barrel zone, and mist eats your burst — the scaler simply reclaims the lane."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"heimerdinger","win":["Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"His Q turret garrison walls you off the minions and his W rockets chip you every time you walk up to last-hit — this is his window, so farm with max-range Parrrley (Q) and never melee into the turret line."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"With a second E point your barrels come up faster: place a Powder Keg next to his turret line and Parrrley-detonate it — the chained slow zone lets you shove and trade through his garrison instead of getting frozen out."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His E stun grenade into W rocket dump is his all-in — if it lands, W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses the stun and heals the missing HP, then drop Cannon Barrage on the turret nest to deny his zone."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Sheen/Essence Reaver spike makes empowered Parrrley delete fresh turrets and start a keg chain that bursts him — your clearest favour window before his rocket-belt items come online."}],"wants":{"you":["Last-hit with max-range Parrrley (Q) so you never step into his turret-plus-W-rocket crossfire to farm","Drop a Powder Keg (E) by his turret line and Parrrley-detonate it to chain-slow him and shove through the garrison, denying the freeze","Save Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse his E stun grenade after it lands and out-heal the rocket poke in his level-6 all-in"],"foe":["Build a Q turret garrison on the wave so you can never walk up to a minion or a barrel safely","Land the E stun grenade into a W rocket volley to burst you while your W cleanse is down","Keep the turret nest alive to freeze near his tower and starve you of the gold you need to scale"]},"early":"Heimerdinger owns these levels and you have to respect it. His Q turret garrison and W rockets wall you off the minions, and with no item spike yet your barrels are on long cooldowns and low HP that he can free-hit to deny — never place an E keg inside turret range, the garrison just shoots it before it matters. Last-hit only with max-range Parrrley (Q) so you stay out of the turret-plus-rocket crossfire, and watch for his E: it is a skillshot stun grenade, not point-and-click, so sidestep it and his poke-to-all-in falls apart.","mid":"Once you hit a second E point and your barrels come up faster, this evens out. Drop a Powder Keg right beside his turret line and Parrrley-detonate it — the chained slow zone lets you finally shove him off the freeze and trade through the garrison instead of getting zoned by it. At 6 do not walk into his nest dry: if his E grenade stun lands into a rocket volley, react with Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse the stun and heal the chunk, then Cannon Barrage the turret cluster to break his zone. It is a farm-and-trade-for-tempo phase, not a kill phase.","late":"This is a scaler-vs-scaler race and it stays roughly even. Your first-item Sheen/Essence Reaver spike lets empowered Parrrley delete his fresh turrets and start a keg chain that bursts him — force those windows and use global Cannon Barrage to pressure other lanes while he is stuck babysitting a turret nest. But he scales just as hard: a fed Heimer with rocket-belt items and his ult upgrade out-DPSes you in a straight siege, so never face-tank the nest — flank, detonate kegs from the side, and let your team soak the turrets while you split-push and carry the rest of the map.","whys":["His Q turret garrison and W rockets zone you off every minion while your barrels are on long early cooldowns he can free-hit — last-hit at max Parrrley range only.","He stacks a second turret and chips you with rockets the instant you walk up; with no item spike your barrels die before they pay off, so concede CS and dodge the E grenade.","It evens out as your second E point speeds up barrels — Parrrley-detonate a keg by his line to chain-slow and shove off the freeze; neither side kills here.","Your keg-and-Parrrley poke trades evenly with his rocket chip now that you can shove the wave off his freeze instead of being garrisoned out.","His E stun into rocket burst is real, but Remove Scurvy cleanses the stun and heals the poke and Cannon Barrage answers the nest, so the level-6 all-in lands about even.","Your Sheen/Essence Reaver spike makes empowered Parrrley delete fresh turrets and start a bursting keg chain — your clearest favour window before his rocket-belt items come online.","He scales as hard as you: a fed Heimer's upgraded ult turret and rocket items out-siege you 1v1, so flank the nest and carry the map instead of dueling it."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"illaoi","win":["Gangplank","Skill","Illaoi","Illaoi","Skill","Skill","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1","text":"She has no E and only a stray passive tentacle or two — last-hit with Parrrley from range, keg the wave for free, and never melee her where a tentacle can W-slam you."},{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Her E (Test of Spirit) is the kill button: it rips a spirit vessel you must run from, and every tentacle near it slams the vessel to chunk the real you — stay out of E cast range when you go for CS."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R (Leap of Faith) slams down a full ring of fresh tentacles at once; my Cannon Barrage answers it by carpeting that ring so she can't stand in her own field to swing them."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"My chained Powder Kegs plus on-hit Parrrley let me detonate from outside tentacle slam range — I poke the field down and never give her a vessel to grab."}],"wants":{"you":["Place Powder Kegs at max range and pop them with Parrrley so I burst her without stepping into tentacle-slam or E range","Save Remove Scurvy and right-click-cancel to break free the moment she lands E, then walk the vessel out of tentacle range before it gets slammed","Scale to 2+ items where keg chains and Cannon Barrage let me fight and zone her field from fully outside it"],"foe":["Land E (Test of Spirit) to tear out my spirit vessel and force me off my own farm while her tentacles batter it","Bait me into melee inside her tentacles at Lvl 3-6 where each one W-slams for huge sustained AoE and feeds her sustain","Hit R (Leap of Faith) to drop a full ring of tentacles at once and chunk me before my kegs are online"]},"early":"Level 1 is mine — she has no E yet and only a stray passive tentacle, so I last-hit with Parrrley at range and chip her for free without ever stepping into a slam. The second she hits 3 it inverts: her E rips out a spirit vessel I have to chase or flee from, and any tentacle near it pounds the vessel to damage the real me. Do NOT trade in melee here. Drop a Powder Keg at max distance, detonate it with Q, and pull straight back before a tentacle winds up. The cardinal sin in this lane is eating E next to a cluster of her tentacles — that's not a trade, that's a death.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are her strongest window — her tentacle count is climbing, her E is a live kill threat, and my kegs still sit on long cooldowns and low HP she can free-hit to deny. So I farm with Parrrley and flatly refuse the field fight. If she does land E on me, I burn Remove Scurvy and right-click to break the pull, then walk the vessel out of tentacle range so nothing can slam it. At 6 my Cannon Barrage finally answers her R — when she leaps in and erupts a fresh ring of tentacles, I drop Barrage on that ring so she can't sit in her own field to swing them, and the skirmish evens back out.","late":"This is where I take over. By 2+ items my Parrrley hits hard on-hit and my keg chain detonates from outside tentacle-slam range — I poke her field down without ever entering it or handing her a vessel to grab, the one thing she can't punish. She's immobile and badly exposed the moment she's pulled off her tentacles, so I use Cannon Barrage to deny her the field in fights and burst her with chained kegs from distance. Just never facecheck a fresh ring of tentacles, and never all-in while her E is up — let the barrels do the work from range and the lane is mine.","whys":["She has no E and barely any tentacles at level 1 — I last-hit and poke with Parrrley from range before she can punish anything.","Her tentacles and E are coming online, but with one keg up I can still trade from distance — it's a genuine coin-flip on who lands their setup first.","Her E (Test of Spirit) rips out a spirit vessel and her tentacles batter it; my kegs are still long-cooldown and free-hit deniable, so the field fight is hers.","Levels 4-5 her tentacle field is dense and slams me for huge AoE while my barrels still can't burst — I'm conceding and just farming Parrrley.","My Cannon Barrage carpets the tentacle ring her R drops so it can't pin me — the skirmish flattens back to even.","My first-item Parrrley spike lets me chip the field from range, but her tentacle sustain heals it back — it stays a wash.","By 2+ items my on-hit Parrrley and chained kegs detonate from outside tentacle range, and she's helpless the instant she's pulled off her field."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"irelia","win":["Irelia","Irelia","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Irelia's window: she Q-resets off minions onto you while your Powder Kegs (E) have a long cooldown and low HP, so she walks up and free-hits the barrel dead before you can detonate it for a trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"She places her two E blades and dashes through for the stun to commit an all-in, but your W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses the stun on the spot and heals off missing HP, blanking the combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Sheen spike is the swing: empowered Parrrley detonating a chained Powder Keg out-bursts what her W shield can eat, so walk-up keg poke finally trades in your favour."},{"when":"Late","text":"Cannon Barrage (R) zones her off the side wave and contests her resets in fights; keep a keg between you so every Q-dash she takes eats the detonation slow."}],"wants":{"you":["Hold W (Remove Scurvy) for her E stun, not her Q poke — cleansing the all-in and healing off missing HP is what keeps this lane even","Last-hit with Parrrley from max range early and pre-place a keg so a Parrrley detonation slows her the instant she Q-dashes in","Survive to your Sheen first-item spike, where a chained-keg Parrrley detonation out-bursts her W shield"],"foe":["Q-reset through the minion wave or off you to close the gap before your kegs are armed and free-hit the barrel to deny it","Land her two-blade E dash-stun while your W is on cooldown to lock in an all-in","Snowball her weak-side levels 1-3 lead and scale her Q-resets into teamfight pick potential"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are hers and you should play to lose them quietly. Your Powder Kegs have a long cooldown and low HP, so if you drop one to poke she just walks up and free-hits the barrel dead, then Q-resets off the minion wave onto you while her passive shred chunks your armour. Don't try to fight here — you can't out-trade her sustained Q resets at level 1. Last-hit with Parrrley from max range, keep W up, and concede a little CS rather than feeding her an early kill and a reset snowball.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stabilize as you get a second keg charge and can start Parrrley-into-keg poke when she steps up to farm. The key discipline: do NOT burn W (Remove Scurvy) on her Q poke — save it for her E. When she places her two blades and dashes through to stun and all-in, cleanse it with W and heal off your missing HP, and the whole combo evaporates. At 6 your Cannon Barrage adds zoning and dive threat but won't win the straight duel, so use it to cut her dash angles, not to brawl her head-on.","late":"Your first-item Sheen spike is where the lane tips your way: an empowered Parrrley detonating a chained Powder Keg out-bursts what her W shield can absorb, and at two items chained keg detonations punish any Q-dash she takes without W and E up. She's still a snowball and splitpush threat, so use Cannon Barrage to zone her off side waves and contest her resets in fights, and keep a keg planted between you so every dash she takes eats the slow. That's how a slight Gangplank edge holds instead of slipping back to even.","whys":["Your Powder Kegs have a long cooldown and low HP she free-hits to deny, and she Q-resets off minions onto you before you can arm and detonate one.","She stacks passive shred and Q-resets through the wave while you have no waveclear and can't trade back at early levels.","You get a second keg charge — Parrrley-into-keg poke arms when she walks up, and the lane stops being a free kill for her.","Hold W for her two-blade E dash-stun, not her Q poke — cleansing the all-in and healing off missing HP keeps the lane neutral.","Your Sheen spike empowers Parrrley to detonate a chained keg for burst her W shield can't fully eat, swinging walk-up trades to you.","Cannon Barrage zones her off side waves and chained keg detonations punish her dashes, giving Gangplank the slight late edge that fits 51.98%.","Her resets and splitpush keep her relevant, so even with your item spikes the lane never tips far from even."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"jax","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Jax"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Jax's window: with E (Counter Strike) up he ignores your Parrrley autos and can walk onto a fresh keg to auto it down before it arms, then Q-leaps you when your barrel is gone."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your spike: a second keg charge lets you set up a chain and detonate it with Parrrley from range — Counter Strike dodges the basic attack, not the AoE keg blast, so you poke him for free."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Sheen-line online: an empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation chunks him through Counter Strike as long as you bait his E first and pop the kegs after it ends."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Jax reclaims it: Trinity Force plus his E-stun and R resists let him eat one keg and Q-W-E all-in you in a straight bruiser fight, so never 1v1 him without a barrel chain ready."}],"wants":{"you":["Set up a keg chain and detonate it with Parrrley from range — Counter Strike dodges the auto, not the AoE blast","Bait his E first, wait out the Counter Strike window, then commit your keg chain once it expires","Hold W (Remove Scurvy) for his E reactivation — cleanse the stun and heal off the missing HP to flip his all-in"],"foe":["Walk onto a fresh keg and auto it down before it arms, then E your retaliation autos","Hold Counter Strike for your commit so the basic attacks whiff, then Q-leap and stun-reset you","Stack Trinity Force and force the 2-item bruiser fight where his E-stun and R resists out-trade your pistol"]},"early":"Jax's early game is about denying your kegs and punishing the gap. He can walk onto a freshly placed Powder Keg and auto it down before it arms, and his Q-leap closes on you whenever your barrel is dead and your E is on cooldown. Don't place a keg he can free-hit, and never throw a Parrrley into his auto range while Counter Strike is up — he dodges the shot and every auto around it, then reactivates for the stun. Last-hit with Parrrley at max range, eat a little poke, and respect that levels 1-3 you have almost no all-in and his leap is always looming.","mid":"This is where you stabilize and flip it. With a second keg charge you can build a chain and detonate it with Parrrley from range — and that matters because Counter Strike only dodges the basic attacks he's standing in, not the AoE keg explosion. Bait the E: poke until he burns Counter Strike, then unload your chain the moment it expires. If he commits Q-W-E anyway, hold W (Remove Scurvy) for the reactivation stun — cleanse it, heal off your missing health, and his engage becomes your free reset. Keep two charges banked so a kill is never more than one Parrrley away.","late":"Be honest: Jax reclaims this once items come online. Trinity Force plus his Counter Strike stun and Grandmaster's Might resistances mean he can eat a single keg and still win a clean 1v1, so never fight him without a full barrel chain set up. Your edge is range and zoning — detonate kegs to keep him off you, and use global Cannon Barrage (R) to swing skirmishes elsewhere or cover a splitpush rather than dueling the duelist. Force your fights before he hits two items, then make the game about your reach, not his trade.","whys":["Both are weak at level 1, but his auto out-damages your Parrrley and he can free-hit your lone fresh keg before it arms — neither truly owns it.","Even stage — his Q-leap threatens you, but you have no keg chain yet to punish, so it stays a farm-and-poke standoff.","Still a wash: Counter Strike dodges your Parrrley autos, yet you have no all-in to make him pay, so neither side commits.","You get a second keg charge and detonate the chain with Parrrley from range — Counter Strike can't dodge the AoE blast, so you out-poke him.","Cannon Barrage adds zoning and punishes his Q-leap, while his R is mostly defensive resists with no extra single-target poke at 6.","An empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation bursts him through Counter Strike once you've baited the E out first.","Jax out-scales you: Trinity Force, the E-stun reset, and Grandmaster's Might resists win a straight 1v1, so zone with kegs and never duel him."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"jayce","win":["Jayce","Jayce","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Jayce's window: he sits in cannon stance and fires Shock Blast through his Acceleration Gate for boosted range/damage, chipping you while your single Powder Keg sits on a long cooldown and gives you no poke back."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your second Parrrley and Powder Keg points come online — you start landing Q-detonated keg poke, and Remove Scurvy heals the missing HP his gated Shock Blasts piled on."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen plus a barrel: an empowered Parrrley detonating a keg out-bursts his Q-gate poke combo, and if he steps to hammer stance to Thundering-Blow you, you cleanse and trade up."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"A chained two-keg detonation off Parrrley one-shots his squishy frame, and Cannon Barrage zones his splitpush — you own the lane and answer the map he tries to roam."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive 1-3 by last-hitting at max Parrrley range and never standing in his gated Shock Blast line","Reach your level 4-5 Q+keg poke and cleanse his accumulated chip with Remove Scurvy","Hit your Sheen+keg spike and force all-ins where a chained barrel detonation bursts his low HP pool"],"foe":["Poke you off the wave with gated Shock Blast before your kegs and waveclear come online","Punish a greedy barrel grab — if you walk into hammer range he Thundering-Blows you back into autos","Keep the lane long-range and roam/splitpush before your item spike flips it"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are his, plainly — your one Powder Keg has a long cooldown and tiny HP, so you have no poke to answer his cannon-stance Shock Blast fired through the Acceleration Gate for bonus range and damage. Do NOT walk up to place or grab a barrel inside that gated Q line, and don't over-extend to hammer range or he swaps to Thundering Blow and knocks you back into free autos. Last-hit at the tip of Parrrley, eat the chip, and refuse to give him a kill window while your kegs are down.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are where you climb back — a second Parrrley and Powder Keg point let you start landing Q-detonated keg poke, and Remove Scurvy cleanses any slow and heals the missing HP his gated Shock Blasts piled on. Hold W until you actually need the heal, not on reflex, since its value scales with missing health. At 6 Cannon Barrage doesn't win the 1v1 outright, but it zones him off the wave and answers his roams, and by now you trade even-to-up whenever he steps into keg range.","late":"Once Sheen lands you flip it for good — an empowered Parrrley detonating a chained keg out-bursts anything his Q-gate poke combo threatens, and by two items a two-barrel chain simply one-shots his squishy frame. He has no scaling answer the way a Kayle or Vladimir would; Jayce is a lane-bully who falls off, so your only job is to not feed the early lead away before your items online. Use Cannon Barrage to shut down his splitpush and collapse on him cross-map.","whys":["His cannon-stance Shock Blast through the Acceleration Gate out-pokes you while your single keg sits on a long cooldown with no waveclear.","If you over-step for a barrel he punishes with hammer-stance Thundering Blow before your second ability point gives any answer.","You stabilize as Parrrley-into-keg poke comes online and Remove Scurvy heals his gated Shock Blast chip back off.","Your level 4-5 Q+keg poke trades up and the W cleanse undoes the harass he stacked levels 1-3.","Cannon Barrage zones him off the wave and contests his roams, tipping the level-6 window your way.","Your Sheen+keg spike: an empowered Parrrley detonating a chained barrel finally out-bursts his Q-gate poke.","A two-keg chain one-shots his squishy frame and global Cannon Barrage shuts down the splitpush he has no scaling to fall back on."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"karma","win":["Karma","Karma","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Her Q (Inner Flame) out-ranges Parrrley and free-pokes you while your barrels sit on a long early cooldown and die to one of her autos — you cannot trade back yet."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Second E point: barrels recharge faster and Parrrley-detonates a keg from outside her Q range, so the poke war finally swings to you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver plus a chained keg detonation bursts a squishy enchanter whose only defense is an E shield and Focused Resolve self-root tether."},{"when":"Lvl 6+","text":"Cannon Barrage zones her shield-and-run pattern — drop it on her escape path and the slow holds her in your keg chain with no W tether to peel."}],"wants":{"you":["Soak her Q poke through levels 1-3, then flip the lane at 4-5 once Parrrley+keg out-ranges her Inner Flame","Save W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse her Focused Resolve tether-root and heal the poke back, not for chip damage","Reach Sheen/Essence Reaver and zone her off the wave with chained barrel detonations she has no health bar to survive"],"foe":["Free-poke you to half with Q (Inner Flame) every wave before your barrels and W come online","Land Focused Resolve (W) tether to lock you for a Soulflare (RQ) detonation or a jungle gank","Shield-and-kite with E move speed and scale into a poke/peel teamfight enchanter where she never has to duel you"]},"early":"Karma owns these first levels — her Q (Inner Flame) out-ranges Parrrley, and at level 1-3 your barrels have long cooldowns and so little HP she can pop them with a single auto to deny your poke, so don't try to trade. The CC to respect is her W (Focused Resolve) tether-root, not the Soulflare detonation people fear — hold your W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse that tether and heal the chip rather than burning it on poke. Last-hit with the tip of Parrrley, eat the Q, and wait: she has no all-in to punish a passive lane, only poke.","mid":"This is where it flips. With a second E point your barrels recharge faster, and Parrrley-detonating a keg reaches from outside her Q range, so you start winning the poke war she used to win for free. Make her commit Focused Resolve or her Mantra detonation first — once that CC is down she only has an E shield and move speed, and a chained keg into empowered Parrrley shreds a champion with an enchanter's health bar. At 6, drop Cannon Barrage on her shield-and-run lane so when she Inspires (E) away she runs through the artillery and your keg slow.","late":"You take over completely. Karma stays a relevant poke-and-peel enchanter for her team, but in a straight side-lane 1v1 she cannot survive chained Powder Keg detonations off a Sheen/Essence Reaver build — one full barrel chain plus empowered Parrrley deletes her health bar. Her only outs are E move speed and a Focused Resolve tether your W cleanses, so the moment she shows for a wave you blow her up. Use global Cannon Barrage to pressure other lanes while you free-farm — this lane is yours from first item onward.","whys":["Her Q (Inner Flame) out-ranges all your tools and your level 1-3 barrels are too slow and fragile to trade back — soak it and farm.","She free-pokes with Q and can lock you with Focused Resolve (W) into a Soulflare detonation while you still have no waveclear or poke answer — concede the level.","You reach a second E point and can start Parrrley-into-keg poke, but she still pokes back evenly here — it is a genuine coinflip.","Your Parrrley+keg combo now reaches from outside her Q range, so you out-trade the poke war she used to win for free.","Cannon Barrage zones her shield-and-run pattern and catches her on her escape path once her Focused Resolve tether is on cooldown.","Sheen/Essence Reaver plus a chained keg detonation bursts a no-escape enchanter, and your W cleanses her one tether-root — you flip the lane.","Chained Powder Keg detonations and global ult pressure own a squishy Karma all game; she can only poke for her team, never duel you."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"kassadin","win":["Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Kassadin"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Kassadin is one of the weakest early laners alive: no Riftwalk, short-range Null Sphere (Q) as his only poke, and he has to walk into Parrrley range to last-hit. Free-hit him with Q every time he steps up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen plus a Powder Keg (E): a Sheen-empowered Parrrley that detonates a barrel chips a huge chunk through his low base HP before he has the items to fight back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Riftwalk (R) comes online so he can finally blink away from your barrel zone, but it's an escape tool here, not a kill tool. Keep shoving and deny him the safe farm his whole game depends on."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Kassadin's scaling takes over: Rod of Ages and Rylai's online, low-cooldown Riftwalks let him blink onto you through the kegs and burst you down. The lane flips to him, so close it before this point."}],"wants":{"you":["Free-hit him with Parrrley every time he walks up to last-hit pre-6 and bleed his low HP bar","Land Parrrley-into-Powder-Keg poke to shove him under turret and starve his farm and stacks","Build a CS and plate lead and end before his Riftwalk and AP items come online around 2 items"],"foe":["Soak Q last-hits from max range and farm safely until items bail him out of the early kill window","Reach level 6 Riftwalk and stack mana/items so his blinks come up faster and hit harder","Survive lane to 2+ items, then Riftwalk in through your barrels and burst you down"]},"early":"Kassadin is one of the worst early laners in the game and Gangplank punishes that hard. Pre-6 he has no Riftwalk to escape, his only ranged tool is a short-range, point-and-click Null Sphere (Q) that you out-range with Parrrley, and his magic-shield passive is dead weight against your physical Q. Open by free-hitting him with Parrrley every time he steps up to last-hit; his only answer is to give up CS and back off. Don't burn your full barrel setup yet, kegs are expensive and fragile this early, so just chip with Q and keep his health bleeding. Respect his Null Sphere only when he's all-in range, since the silence locks you out of casting W or E during the window.","mid":"This is your window to bury him. With a second point in E and your keg chain set up, you start landing Parrrley-into-Powder-Keg, and that chip damage crushes a champion who only wants to farm passively and stack mana. At 6 his Riftwalk lets him blink out of your zone, but it doesn't let him out-trade you, he can blink away, not blink in and win. Set a keg, force him to either eat poke or burn his blink to dodge, and detonate as he repositions. Note that his Q silence stops you from casting W or E mid-trade, so pre-cleanse with W before you commit rather than relying on it after the silence lands. Keep shoving so he soaks turret aggro and falls behind the gold curve his whole gameplan depends on.","late":"Be honest with yourself: this is a race and Kassadin wins the long one. Once he hits 2 or more items his Riftwalks come up fast enough to blink straight through your barrel chain, his passive shrugs off magic burst, and he one-shots squishies including you. Your global Cannon Barrage (R) still pressures the map, so the plan is to have already won, turn your early CS and plate lead into towers, group, and close objectives before he comes online. If it goes long, stop dueling him solo: use R to zone and peel from range, let your frontline soak his Riftwalk, and barrel from the back instead of trading blows.","whys":["Kassadin is one of the weakest level-1 champions in the game while Gangplank out-ranges his short Null Sphere with Parrrley, so free-hit him off every last-hit.","He still has no Riftwalk escape and his magic shield is useless against physical Parrrley, so walk up and harass him off CS for free.","Your Parrrley out-ranges his point-and-click Q and he can't punish the chip, so keep his low HP bar bleeding while your kegs are setting up.","Parrrley-into-Powder-Keg poke comes online and crushes a champ who only wants to farm and stack mana, so force trades he can't sustain through.","Riftwalk lets him escape your keg zone at 6 but not out-duel you, so bait the blink, detonate the keg as he repositions, and keep shoving.","Your Sheen plus Powder-Keg detonation spike bursts through his low base HP before his AP items matter, so close the lane on this window.","Kassadin out-scales hard once he reaches 2+ items: low-cooldown Riftwalks blink past your barrels and one-shot you, so play safe and let your team handle him."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"kayle","win":["Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Skill","Kayle","Kayle"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Kayle is a melee creep with no waveclear and no escape — pelt her with Parrrley every time she walks up to last-hit and free-hit her under tower, but respect your own paper durability and don't auto-trade into a topside jungler."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Kayle gets her R invuln AND attack range at 6, so she's no longer a free target up close; use Cannon Barrage to zone her off CS and set up a jungler dive, not to win a straight duel."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen + your keg build is your kill window: an empowered Parrrley into a chained Powder Keg detonation can burst Kayle before her level-11 ranged form comes fully online."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Kayle's takeover — at 11 and 16 with items her ranged DPS kites your barrels from outside detonation range and her R invuln eats your whole keg-chain combo; the lane and the game flip to her."}],"wants":{"you":["Deny Kayle CS and XP at levels 1-5 with Parrrley harass while she's a melee creep, slowing her path to the 6/11/16 spikes","Hit Sheen plus your first keg-build item and burst her in the mid-game before her ranged form scales out of reach","Use Cannon Barrage zoning and jungler dives to set her behind, then close the game out before she comes fully online late"],"foe":["Survive the early Parrrley poke and farm safely to her level-11 ranged form and her power items","Reach level 6 for the R invuln window and added range that blank your keg-chain burst and dive","Out-scale you into the late game where her ranged DPS kites your barrels and her R invuln resets her health bar"]},"early":"Kayle is one of the most helpless level-1 to level-5 laners in the game — a melee creep with no waveclear and no escape, so this is where you bully. Hit her with Parrrley every time she walks up to last-hit, and free-hit her when she's stuck auto-ing the wave under tower. The catch: your own base durability is paper this early and your barrels are on long cooldowns, so don't get baited into tower-diving her or auto-trading when her jungler could be topside — your goal is denying her CS and XP, not dying for a kill you don't need.","mid":"This is your whole game plan. Once you get a second Q/E point and your Sheen comes online, your Parrrley-into-Powder-Keg poke and burst out-damage anything pre-11 Kayle can do, so keep her off the wave and deny her the levels that turn her into a ranged carry. Remember she gets R invuln and attack range at 6, so she's no longer a free target up close — use Cannon Barrage to zone her off CS and set up a jungler dive rather than to flip a coin into a straight duel. Every level and item you deny here is one Kayle doesn't have when she takes over.","late":"Be honest with yourself: this is Kayle's game once she's online. At 11 and 16 with items, her ranged form kites your Powder Kegs from outside detonation range, and her R invulnerability simply eats your entire keg-chain burst — you can dump your whole rotation and she walks away untouched. You out-scale most of the roster, but Kayle out-scales YOU. Your only path is that the lead you built at levels 1-5 snowballs your team into ending before she's full; if it goes long, use your global Cannon Barrage to help cross-map, peel for your carries, and let your team handle her, because you will not solo her once she's itemized.","whys":["Kayle's melee level-1 is weak and you can pelt her with Parrrley, but neither of you has a kill threat yet — Gangplank's pistol harass edges a melee creep who can't waveclear or punish back.","Your second Q point lets you chunk her with Parrrley every time she steps up to CS, denying the levels she desperately needs while she has no answer.","Parrrley-into-keg poke out-trades a melee Kayle who has no waveclear and no way to punish your barrel setup, so you own this window outright.","Kayle gets R invuln and range at 6, but Cannon Barrage still lets you zone her off the wave and enable a jungler dive — Gangplank keeps the lead by starving her levels at the exact moment she needs them.","Roughly even — your Sheen + first keg item can burst her, but at 6+ her R invuln and new attack range mean your all-in is a coin flip rather than a clean kill, so neither side clearly owns it.","Kayle's level-11 ranged form starts kiting your barrels from outside detonation range, and her sustained DPS now out-damages your poke-and-burst pattern.","She out-scales you outright: ranged-form DPS kites your barrels from range and her R invulnerability blanks your entire keg-chain combo, so the late game is hers."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"kennen","win":["Kennen","Kennen","Kennen","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Kennen's window: his Q (Thundering Shuriken) pokes for free and each hit stacks a Mark of the Storm, while your kegs (E) sit on long cooldowns and can be free-hit and destroyed before they're armed — and his energy means he never runs out of poke."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your extra Q (Parrrley) and E points come online — Parrrley-detonated keg poke from range starts matching his shuriken, so you stop bleeding free trades."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen (Sheen/Trinity/Essence Reaver) into the keg build flips it: empowered Parrrley plus a chained Powder Keg detonation bursts a squishy Kennen before his energy poke can answer."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His threat: Slicing Maelstrom (R) is an AoE that stacks marks fast and stuns on the third — perfect dive setup, but right-click-cancel/W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses the stun the instant it lands."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 at high HP, last-hitting at max Parrrley range so his shuriken poke and Mark of the Storm stacks never set up a stun","Reach your first-item Sheen+keg spike and burst him with empowered Parrrley into a chained Powder Keg detonation","Hold W (Remove Scurvy) — or right-click-cancel — to wipe his Slicing Maelstrom stun and deny every jungle dive at 6"],"foe":["Land Q (Thundering Shuriken) and weave autos to stack three Marks of the Storm and stun you before your kegs come online","Kite with passive move speed and energy poke so you never connect a keg-detonated Parrrley trade","Hit a multi-mark Slicing Maelstrom stun to set up a dive while your W is on cooldown"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are his, flat out. Kennen pokes with Q (Thundering Shuriken) for free and every hit stacks a Mark of the Storm, his energy never dries up, and your Powder Kegs sit on long cooldowns with low HP he can simply auto to destroy before they're useful. Don't walk into shuriken range to set up a keg you can't detonate yet — last-hit at the tip of Parrrley, eat minimal poke, and DO NOT let three Marks of the Storm land (that's the stun). Hold your W; save it to cleanse his ult, not a single shuriken.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize: extra points in Parrrley and Powder Keg let you detonate a keg with Q from range and finally trade back instead of just bleeding. At 6 respect his Slicing Maelstrom — it tags you with marks fast and stuns for a dive, so keep W (or a right-click cancel) ready to clear it and don't get caught arming a keg near your tower with his jungler missing. This stage is roughly even; you're not all-inning yet, you're surviving to your Sheen spike.","late":"Your first-item Sheen+keg spike flips the lane and the late game is yours: empowered Parrrley plus a full chained Powder Keg detonation bursts a squishy Kennen far faster than his energy poke can chip you, and your global Cannon Barrage out-pressures his teamfight ult on the map. He has no scaling answer — once you're online he can't out-trade chained kegs, so close the lane and look for cross-map R plays. Just never facecheck a brush into a three-mark Slicing Maelstrom stun.","whys":["His Q (Thundering Shuriken) pokes for free while your kegs sit on long cooldowns and can be auto-destroyed before they arm — last-hit at Parrrley range and don't trade.","He stacks Marks of the Storm and keeps poking on energy with no mana cost; you have no keg pressure yet to punish him.","Three Marks of the Storm stun you and his shuriken out-ranges your keg setup — stay at max Parrrley distance and refuse the short trade.","Your extra Parrrley and Powder Keg points let keg-detonated poke match his shuriken, so the free-trade bleed stops and the lane levels off.","Slicing Maelstrom (R) adds a multi-mark stun dive threat, but it doesn't win the straight duel — W or right-click-cancel clears it and it stays even.","Sheen into the keg build flips it: empowered Parrrley plus a chained Powder Keg detonation bursts a squishy Kennen before his poke can answer.","You out-scale a lane-bully Kennen hard — chained kegs and global Cannon Barrage own the duel and the map, so close before he can group."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"kled","win":["Kled","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Kled"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Mounted Kled's Bear Trap on a Rope pull plus Violent Tendencies attack-speed autos chunk you before a single Powder Keg exists — his hardest window, give him the wave and don't get yanked."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your second Q and E points let you Parrrley a keg from outside Bear Trap range and chip Skaarl's HP so a dismount commit isn't a free kill on you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen or Essence Reaver online — empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation finally out-bursts a remounted Kled in a short trade before his Violent Tendencies windows up."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Kled reclaims the duel: easy mount restacking from Courage, Violent Tendencies bonus on-hit and his bruiser items let him survive your keg combo and all-in through it."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 by last-hitting with the tip of Parrrley and never standing in pull range of a free Bear Trap","Reach your level 4-5 keg poke and burn Skaarl's HP so dismounting Kled in a trade stops being a free kill on you","Hit your Sheen or Essence Reaver first-item spike and force the all-in while his Violent Tendencies and remount are on cooldown"],"foe":["Land Bear Trap on a Rope to reel you in, then Violent Tendencies-auto you down before your kegs are placed","Trade hard levels 1-3 while your barrels are on long cooldowns and easy to deny by free-hitting them","Bait out Remove Scurvy with a fake pull, then re-engage with Bear Trap and ult-charge once your cleanse is gone"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are Kled's lane to lose, not yours. Mounted Kled's Bear Trap on a Rope yanks you in and his Violent Tendencies attack-speed autos chunk you before you have a single Powder Keg down, so do not sit in pull range of a barrel he can free-hit to deny — last-hit with the tip of Parrrley and eat a little poke. Hold Remove Scurvy (W) for the grab, not for chip: cleansing the Bear Trap pull is your one tool that turns his all-in into a whiff. If you force him off Skaarl (dismount), he loses his steroid and gets slower, so deny his Courage stacks and just farm to your spikes.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where I claw the lane back to even. With a second Q and E point I can Parrrley a keg from outside Bear Trap range and grind down Skaarl's HP so a dismount commit isn't a free kill on me. Cannon Barrage at 6 is zoning and skirmish pressure, not a duel button — drop it to cut his mount path, peel a gank, or deny his ult-charge engage, not to win a straight 1v1. Bait his Bear Trap, cleanse the pull with Remove Scurvy, then punish the long grab cooldown with a chained keg detonation while he's stuck out of position.","late":"My first-item Sheen or Essence Reaver into the keg build is the one window I'm clearly ahead — empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg explosion out-bursts a remounted Kled in a short fight, so force the all-in there while his Bear Trap and Violent Tendencies are down. After that he out-scales the duel: cheap Courage restacking from minions, Violent Tendencies on-hit and bruiser tankiness let him eat the keg combo and re-mount, so stop dueling at 2+ items and use Cannon Barrage to splitpush pressure and swing other lanes instead of feeding him a clean re-engage.","whys":["Kled is a level-1 skirmish bully and you are one of the weakest early tops — his Bear Trap pull and Violent Tendencies autos chunk you before a single Powder Keg exists.","It evens out: you can farm with the tip of Parrrley while holding Remove Scurvy to cleanse his Bear Trap pull and deny the all-in.","Neither of you spikes here — you stabilize on barrels while he relies on re-landing his grab, so short trades are a coin flip.","Your second Q and E points let you Parrrley kegs from outside Bear Trap range, matching his raw skirmish pressure on Skaarl's HP.","Cannon Barrage adds zoning and gank pressure but doesn't win the duel, and his ult-charge engage answers it — roughly even.","Your Sheen or Essence Reaver first-item spike out-bursts a remounted Kled in a short trade while his Bear Trap and Violent Tendencies are on cooldown.","Kled out-scales: cheap Courage re-mounting, Violent Tendencies on-hit and bruiser tankiness let him reclaim the all-in once both have items."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"ksante","win":["Skill","K'Sante","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","K'Sante"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"K'Sante's early is his window — his W gives him a charged shield-dash and his Q is a slam that knocks up only at max charge, so he can walk you down and free-hit your low-HP kegs before you have a second E point to chain them."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage doesn't win the duel, but dropping R on the wave denies his all-in and zones him off your kegs while you stack farm — your global also lets you leave lane and swing a fight elsewhere."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Sheen spike (Sheen/Essence Reaver) into a full keg chain is your flip — empowered Parrrley detonating two chained barrels finally out-bursts K'Sante before he completes his first tank item if you set up before he engages."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"K'Sante's R reforms him into a melee bruiser, strips his own resists for damage, and knocks you through a wall to isolate the 1v1 — fully itemized he reclaims the duel, so treat him as a teamfight target, not a sidelane fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Place E barrels off to the side and detonate with Parrrley from range so his W shield-dash and Q slam can't reach you mid-setup","Save W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse his Q knockup or the R wall-knockback, then heal off your missing HP and walk out","Survive to your Sheen spike and force chained-keg trades while his W shield is on cooldown"],"foe":["Charge W for the shield and dash, then Q-slam to knock you up and lock you for a free trade before your barrels are chained","Walk up and free-hit your Powder Kegs to pop them early and deny the chain that powers your burst","Stall to 2+ items where his All Out R, resist-stripping, and wall-knockback let him out-duel you outright"]},"early":"K'Sante's early is the part that scares you — his passive Dauntless Instinct adds bonus damage on his abilities and his W charges a shield he dashes with, so he can walk up and free-hit your kegs before you can chain them. Don't place a single barrel where his W-dash or Q can reach it; set them off to the side and only pop them with Parrrley from max range so he can't body-block the explosion. Last-hit with Q and accept that levels 1-3 are his window, not yours. Hold W (Remove Scurvy) for when he lands the Q knockup, not for chip — it cleanses the lockdown that sets up his whole all-in and heals you off your missing health.","mid":"Levels 4-6 you stabilize as your second E point comes up and you can finally chain two kegs — start landing Parrrley-into-keg poke whenever he steps up to farm, because his only lane sustain is base regen and his W shield. At 6, Cannon Barrage isn't a duel button against a tank, so use it to zone him off the wave and deny his W-dash engage rather than to finish. Bait his W shield on a fake keg, then commit the real chain while it's down — that's the only mid-game window where your burst beats his shield-and-dash.","late":"This is where you have to be honest: K'Sante is a hard scaler and fully itemized he reclaims the duel. His R (All Out) reforms him into a high-damage melee bruiser, strips his own armor and MR to convert into damage, and knocks you through a wall to isolate a 1v1 where his dashes and shield outlast your barrel cooldowns. Don't splitpush into him expecting to win the sidelane — your scaling is real, but his catches yours in a straight fight. Play the map instead: global Cannon Barrage to swing other lanes, and in fights drop your chained kegs on his backline while your team peels his R isolation off you.","whys":["You're both weak level 1, but his on-ability bonus damage and W shield-dash let him win short trades while your only tool is a single Parrrley — set up kegs safely and don't trade autos.","His W shield-dash plus Q knockup let him walk you down and free-hit your low-HP kegs before you have a second E point to chain them — concede this stage.","You get a second Q/E point and can start Parrrley-into-keg poke, but his W shield and base sustain keep the lane genuinely even.","Your chained-keg poke answers his walk-ups while W cleanses the Q knockup — neither of you can fully commit, so it stays a skill lane.","Cannon Barrage zones him off the wave and denies his W-dash engage, but it won't win the duel into a tank, so this stays even.","Your Sheen spike into a full keg chain finally out-bursts K'Sante before his first tank item if you bait his W shield first.","Fully itemized his All Out R strips his resists for damage and walls you off to isolate you, and his shield-and-dash outlast your barrel cooldowns — he reclaims the duel, so fight him with your team."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"lillia","win":["Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Lillia's whole kit is range — passive Dream Dust, Q sweeps, E Swirlseed poke — so this is her only real window. Last-hit at Parrrley range and don't walk into her dash poke or she chips you for free."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Remove Scurvy answers her ult: when Lilting Lullaby's drowsy ticks toward sleep, W cleanses it and heals off your missing HP, deleting the only hard CC she has to land a gank or pick on you."},{"when":"1st item (Sheen)","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver makes every Parrrley a chunk, and a Powder Keg chain detonated by Q bursts her low-armor AP frame before her Dream Dust DOT and dash can kite the damage off."},{"when":"Late","text":"She's a roam/teamfight skirmisher, not a side-lane duelist — keg detonations slow and two-tap her, and Cannon Barrage zones her off Dragon/Baron and punishes how slowly she clears when she can't keep dashing."}],"wants":{"you":["Land Parrrley whenever she steps up to last-hit — she has no point-and-click or ranged answer back, and chip plus barrel poke beats her sustain","Hold Remove Scurvy for her R: cleanse the drowsy before it puts you to sleep, heal off missing HP, and her whole gank/pick combo whiffs","Pre-place a Powder Keg before she dashes in, then Q-detonate it so the slow catches her out of her own kite window"],"foe":["Use her dash and passive movement speed to kite your autos and let your barrels expire before you can detonate them","Stack Dream Dust DOT and Swirlseed/Q poke from max range, refusing to ever walk into Parrrley","Land R while your W is on cooldown, then dash back in to combo you for free while you're asleep"]},"early":"\"Levels 1-2 are the only window she really gets, and even then it's close — Parrrley out-ranges her, so punish her every time she walks up to last-hit. Don't chase her movement speed across the lane; she'll kite your autos with her dash and bleed you with Dream Dust DOT. Sit on the wave, hit her with Q when she comes for CS, and don't let her free-hit your low-HP barrels before you can use them. She has no point-and-click and no gap-closer that catches you — she only out-trades if you over-walk into her poke.\"","mid":"\"This is where you take over. With your second Q and a keg point you start landing Parrrley-into-keg poke, and she has to walk into a slow she can't dodge to farm. At 6 her R looks scary, but Remove Scurvy is the answer — let the drowsy tick, then W to cleanse it instantly and heal off missing HP, and she's burned her whole combo for nothing. Bait her dash, drop a barrel where she lands, and Q-detonate to slow her out of the kite. She cannot duel you if you don't chase blindly into her poke.\"","late":"\"You own the late game outright — she's a roaming skirmisher, not a 1v1 threat, and chained keg detonations two-tap her squishy AP frame the moment she's in range. Cannon Barrage zones her off Dragon and Baron and punishes how slowly she clears a side lane when she's not dashing. Keep W up for her R in fights and she has no way to lock you down. Her only out is avoiding you entirely and snowballing elsewhere — so don't let her free-roam, group your kegs, and close the game before she's relevant.\"","whys":["She's a slippery early laner with Dream Dust DOT and dash kite, and you're a weak early too — so last-hit at Parrrley range and don't over-walk into her poke during her only window.","Parrrley out-ranges every tool she has and she has no point-and-click answer — chunk her each time she steps up for CS.","Your second Q point lets you poke her down faster than Dream Dust sustains, and she has no gap-closer that out-trades your pistol-and-keg chip.","Once she has to walk into your kegs to farm, your barrel poke beats her kite — she can't free-hit the kegs to deny them without eating Parrrley.","Her R sleep is her only hard CC, and Remove Scurvy cleanses it and heals off missing HP — so you flip her 6 spike into a wasted combo.","Sheen/Essence Reaver Parrrley plus a full keg chain bursts her low-armor AP frame before Dream Dust DOT and her dash can recover the trade.","Chained keg detonations two-tap her and Cannon Barrage zones her off objectives — she's a roamer, not a duelist who can answer your scaling."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"lucian","win":["Lucian","Lucian","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Lucian's Lightslinger double-shot (after any Q/W cast) plus his Q poke chunks you before you have a second E for waveclear, and a single auto pops your low-HP barrels to deny the detonation."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"With a second Q and E rank you start landing Parrrley-into-keg poke, which evens the lane because Lucian has to walk into chip range to last-hit the wave."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen or Essence Reaver online: an empowered Parrrley detonating a chained keg slows and bursts a squishy Lucian, flipping short trades to Gangplank."},{"when":"Lvl 6+","text":"Lucian's main out is Relentless Pursuit (E) — he saves the dash to leave your keg's slow radius and walk out of Cannon Barrage, so bait the dash before you commit the chain."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach a second E rank so keg-into-Parrrley poke matches his range and he can't free last-hit","Get Sheen or Essence Reaver online so an empowered Q detonation bursts him in one chain","Place kegs to chain-slow him into Cannon Barrage once his Relentless Pursuit dash is down"],"foe":["Auto your low-HP Powder Kegs on sight to deny the detonation before your setup lands","Poke you down with Lightslinger double-shot plus Q in the levels 1-3 window before your waveclear","Hold Relentless Pursuit (E) to dash out of keg slows and kite your Cannon Barrage"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are his. Lucian's Lightslinger double-shot fires after every Q or W cast, so he out-trades your raw autos, and a single shot pops your Powder Kegs while they sit at low HP to deny your whole setup. Don't try to trade back into his range — last-hit at max Parrrley distance and accept the chip. Hold your E kegs until you actually need them for the wave, because a barrel he free-hits is a detonation and a cooldown you don't get back.","mid":"This is where you stabilize. With a second Q and E rank you can run the real Gangplank pattern — drop a keg, Parrrley it to detonate the slowing AoE, and chip him every time he steps up to farm. He still out-ranges your raw autos, so make the kegs do the work and never face-tank his double-shot to land a Q. At 6 your Cannon Barrage adds zoning and dive pressure but won't win a straight duel alone, so use it to deny his farm or set up your jungler, not to coinflip an all-in.","late":"Once your Sheen or Essence Reaver lands, the lane tilts your way — an empowered Parrrley into a chained keg explosion slows and bursts a squishy Lucian, and your global Cannon Barrage zones him off objectives. The one thing to respect is Relentless Pursuit: he saves the E dash to slip out of your detonation radius and reposition, so bait it with a keg slow before you commit the full chain. Land that and he has no escape from the explosion or your ultimate.","whys":["Lucian's Lightslinger double-shot procs off his Q/W casts and out-trades your autos, and one shot pops your low-HP barrels before any detonation comes online.","He out-ranges your raw autos in the levels 1-3 window and can deny kegs on cooldown — last-hit at max Parrrley range instead of stepping into his double-shot.","Your second Q rank lets you poke back with Parrrley, but he can still kite with E and trade even, so the window comes down to positioning.","With a second E rank your keg-into-Parrrley poke matches his range, so trades level out as Lucian has to walk into chip range to last-hit.","Cannon Barrage adds zoning and dive pressure but doesn't win the straight duel, so the lane stays even outside coordinated plays or jungle setups.","Sheen or Essence Reaver makes an empowered Parrrley detonate a keg chain for burst that one-shots a squishy Lucian.","Chained keg slows plus global Cannon Barrage let Gangplank zone and burst him down once items are online, and his scaling outpaces Lucian's lane lead."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"malphite","win":["Malphite","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Malphite owns the opener: his Q (Seismic Shard) slows you and steals your move speed so you can't sidestep, and his W-empowered autos out-trade your single Parrrley before you have a keg down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Respect his R (Unstoppable Force): it's a dash-charge knock-up, not point-and-click, so you CAN flash or juke it — but if it lands it locks you for a jungle dive. Don't get pinned against a wall."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen (Sheen/Triforce or Essence Reaver line) comes online: Parrrley-empowered keg detonations start chunking through his armor stack and let you trade-and-leave from barrel range."},{"when":"Late","text":"Chained Powder Keg explosions plus a global Cannon Barrage outscale a tank who built only armor against you — and his W passive sustain doesn't matter once your keg burst is up."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely at Parrrley range through levels 1-3 while his Q slow zones you off melee minions — don't walk up to contest a CS he can punish","Hit your Sheen spike, then poke with Parrrley-detonated kegs so the chain explosion chunks through his armor without committing to a melee fight","Dodge or flash his R rather than relying on W — the displacement knock-up itself can't be cleansed mid-air; save W to heal and cleanse the Q slow that sets up his follow-up"],"foe":["Land Q to slow and sap your move speed, then walk up and W-auto trade while your kegs are on cooldown","Reach level 6 and charge R as an unstoppable engage or to pin you for a jungle dive — ideally into a wall so you can't juke","Build pure armor (Sunfire, Thornmail) to blunt your physical Parrrley and keg burst while his W passive heals the chip"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Malphite. His Q (Seismic Shard) slows you and steals your move speed, so you can't dodge his follow-up auto or reach melee minions cleanly, and his W-empowered autos beat your lone Parrrley before you have a keg placed. Don't try to fight: last-hit with Parrrley from range, eat a little Q poke, and never stand on top of your own Powder Keg where he can free-hit and pop it early. The good news is his Q is mana-hungry and he's a slow waveclearer, so deny him the easy poke, hold your ground, and farm toward your item spike.","mid":"This is a holding pattern until your first item, not a takeover. With a second keg point you can start Parrrley-into-keg poke from range, but he stacks armor against your physical damage and his W passive heals the chip, so don't expect to win trades yet. The real swing is level 6: his R (Unstoppable Force) is a dash-charge knock-up — it is NOT point-and-click, so you can flash or juke it, but if it lands he pins you for an all-in, especially with his jungler nearby. Respect that window, hold W to heal and cleanse the Q slow that sets it up, and bait or wait out his R before you commit.","late":"Now the lane tilts your way. Once Sheen (and the Essence Reaver/Trinity build behind it) is online, Parrrley detonating a full chained keg explosion finally bursts through his armor stacking, and your global Cannon Barrage gives you cross-map pressure a tank simply doesn't have. He stays a teamfight engage threat with his R, so play around it — bait it or wait it out — but in a straight 1v1 and on the map your scaling keg carry pattern beats a tank who built only armor against your physical damage.","whys":["Malphite's Q slows you and steals your move speed off melee last-hits, and his W-empowered autos out-trade your lone Parrrley before a keg is down.","He keeps walking you down with Q-into-W-auto while your kegs sit on long cooldowns — it stays skill-dependent: farm at Parrrley range and don't over-extend.","It's even mid-lane: your second keg point lets you start poking, but his armor and W passive sustain blunt the chip so neither side can commit cleanly.","Level 6 is a coin-flip on execution — his R is a dodgeable dash-charge, not point-and-click, so if you flash or juke it the all-in fizzles; if it lands you're pinned.","Sheen flips the trade: empowered Parrrley plus a full keg chain finally bursts through his armor, and you start winning the poke war he can't answer.","You out-scale a pure-armor tank with chained keg detonations that shred physical resistances and a global Cannon Barrage for cross-map pressure.","In a straight 1v1 and on the map your late keg-carry pattern beats a tank who built the wrong resistance against you — his R keeps him a teamfight threat, but the lane is yours."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"maokai","win":["Maokai","Maokai","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Maokai's saplings (E) and his auto-attacks free-pop your low-HP Powder Kegs before they arm, gutting your kit, and his W root dash sets up the first all-in or gank — your worst window."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"A second E point plus Parrrley-into-keg poke lets you start chipping him from outside his Q-knockback and W-root range without committing to a trade."},{"when":"1st item (Sheen)","text":"Sheen from Sheen/Trinity/Essence Reaver online: an empowered Parrrley detonating a full keg chain finally out-damages his sapling sustain and passive twig heal."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His threat is W-rooting you into a jungler collapse — your Cannon Barrage (R) zones the dive but won't free you mid-root, so save Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse the root, not for poke."}],"wants":{"you":["Hold Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse his W root and Q knockback, then heal the chip back off missing HP","Reach your Sheen first-item spike so empowered Parrrley plus a keg chain out-burns his sapling and passive sustain","Place kegs at max range and behind minions so his saplings and auto-attacks can't pop them before they arm"],"foe":["Land the W root dash to lock you for an all-in or jungler collapse before you can cleanse with W","Float saplings (E) onto your unarmed kegs to detonate your whole setup for free","Out-sustain your early poke with his passive twig heal plus sapling regen and trade evenly into mid game"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are Maokai's, not from burst but because his saplings (E) and auto-attacks free-pop your Powder Kegs before they arm, gutting your whole kit. His W is a targeted root dash that locks you for a jungle collapse, and his Q knocks you off your barrel setup. Don't place a keg where a sapling or his autos can reach it, hold W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse the root rather than waste it on poke, and farm with the tip of Parrrley from max range.","mid":"Levels 4-6 even out as your second E point lets you Parrrley-into-keg poke from outside his Q-knockback and W-root range — chip him while his saplings sit on cooldown. His passive twig heal plus sapling regen means raw poke won't kill him, so the lane is patience: bait his W root, cleanse it with your own W and heal off missing HP, then walk away even. At 6 your Cannon Barrage zones a dive or covers a roam but isn't a duel button here, so use R to deter his jungler rather than to fight him 1v1.","late":"Once your Sheen item lands the lane tips your way: an empowered Parrrley detonating a full keg chain finally out-damages everything Maokai can heal back, and he has no dash or shield to dodge a max-range keg. He stays relevant as a teamfight tank with that W root onto your carries, but in a straight sidelane 1v1 you out-scale him — just respect that his job is to lock someone for his team, so keep Remove Scurvy up to cleanse the root every fight.","whys":["Maokai's saplings and auto-attacks free-deny your low-HP kegs at level 1, and you have no waveclear or poke to answer his root-dash setup yet.","His W root dash plus Q knockback can chain you into a jungler collapse before you have a second E point, and you can't trade through his early sustain.","Once your second E point lands you poke from outside his Q/W range, but his sapling and twig-heal sustain erase the chip — neither side can commit, so it's even.","You out-range his melee Q with keg poke, yet his passive heal refills faster than you can burst pre-Sheen — a true coinflip on who lands a play.","Your Cannon Barrage zones his jungler and covers roams, but his W root still threatens a collapse and R isn't a duel button — skill decides whether the dive lands.","Sheen empowers Parrrley so a chained keg detonation finally out-damages his sapling and passive regen — your first clear favour window in lane.","You out-scale him in the sidelane 1v1, but his W root onto your carry keeps him useful in fights, so the macro stays a genuine coinflip between roam and split."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"mel","win":["Mel","Mel","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Mel's biggest window: her Radiant Volley (Q) is long-range AP poke that chunks you while your Powder Kegs (E) start with low HP and a long cooldown, so eat minimal trades, last-hit with Parrrley, and freeze near tower."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"You stabilize. Extra E ranks shorten keg cooldown and bump barrel HP, so Parrrley-into-keg poke starts matching her Radiant Volley at range and trades flip even."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver online: empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation bursts a squishy, escapeless Mel in one window, faster than she can answer."},{"when":"Lvl 6+","text":"Her real threat is her Rebuttal reflect (a basic ability, not her ult) and her Golden Eclipse (R) execute on low targets, not a reflect on your kegs: don't fish a single Parrrley into the reflect window, and keep your HP up so her R can't finish you."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the level 1-3 Radiant Volley poke, protect your kegs' HP and last-hit with Parrrley, freezing near tower until your second E point","Reach the Sheen/Essence Reaver spike and burst escapeless Mel with empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation","Walk a barrel onto her and chain the slow: she has no dash or pool, so once committed she cannot leave the keg"],"foe":["Win the level 1-2 lane with Radiant Volley poke before your barrels and items come online","Time her Rebuttal reflect onto your Parrrley/barrel hits and keep you low for a Golden Eclipse (R) execute","Zone you off the wave from max range with Q and her snare so you can never walk up to last-hit"]},"early":"Mel owns these first levels: her Radiant Volley (Q) is long-range AP poke and your Powder Kegs (E) still have low base HP and a long cooldown, so she free-hits you and pops your kegs to deny them whenever you step up. Don't fight back through the poke; last-hit with Parrrley (Q) from max range and accept a freeze near tower. The saving grace is she is squishy with no dash or pool, so every point of poke she lands is a debt she pays the moment your kegs and Sheen come online.","mid":"This is where it flips. A second E point shortens your keg cooldown and raises barrel HP, so Parrrley-into-keg poke starts matching her Radiant Volley at range and trades go even, then favoured. Respect two things, neither of which is a reflect on your kegs: her Rebuttal (her reflect is a basic ability, up often, so don't fish a lone Parrrley into it) and her Golden Eclipse (R), an execute that punishes you low. Keep your HP healthy with Remove Scurvy and she has no dash to escape once your barrel slow lands.","late":"You take over hard. By Sheen/Essence Reaver your empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg explosion one-shots a squishy Mel, and unlike a true scaler (Kayle, Vlad) she does not out-pace you: she stays a fragile, immobile artillery mage all game. Cannon Barrage (R) gives you cross-map and teamfight pressure her zone tools can't answer. The only standing rule is to keep your HP up so her Golden Eclipse can't execute you, and to not waste a barrel chain into her Rebuttal reflect window.","whys":["Mel's Radiant Volley (Q) out-pokes you at range while your Powder Kegs have low HP and a long cooldown — last-hit at max Parrrley range and don't trade.","She keeps popping your kegs to deny them and chunking you at level 2 with Q — freeze near tower and protect your barrel HP until your second E point.","Around levels 4-5 trades are genuinely even: your shortened keg cooldown lets Parrrley-into-keg poke match her Radiant Volley, so it comes down to who lands cleaner.","Once your kegs are online you chain a barrel onto an escapeless Mel — your slow sticks and she has no dash or pool to leave.","Cannon Barrage (R) adds cross-map and teamfight pressure her zone tools can't kite, while she has no global answer of her own.","Sheen/Essence Reaver empowers Parrrley — one chained keg detonation bursts a squishy Mel in a single window.","You stay the premier scaling carry while she remains a fragile, immobile mage — just keep your HP up so her Golden Eclipse (R) can't execute, and don't dump a barrel into her Rebuttal reflect."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"mordekaiser","win":["Skill","Mordekaiser","Mordekaiser","Skill","Mordekaiser","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Morde's W shield and isolated-target Q (Mace of Spades) come online before your second keg, so his short auto-Q trade beats your bare Parrrley poke and out-sustains it."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Realm of Death (R) isolates you into a 1v1 box where your global Cannon Barrage and barrel zoning are useless, and the percentage of your stats he steals wins the duel."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen into the upgraded keg build: a Sheen-empowered Parrrley detonating a barrel chain finally out-bursts his W-shield sustain from outside his E (Death Grip) range."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"A chained Powder Keg detonation plus a maxed-rank Parrrley shreds him from range, and with no dash he can never reach a barrel-walled you to land an isolated Q."}],"wants":{"you":["Stall the early game and last-hit with Parrrley until your second keg lets you start a chain","Hold Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse his E pull/root so he can never set up an isolated Q on you","Pre-place Powder Kegs to wall his only walk-up angle and detonate the chain with Parrrley from range"],"foe":["Land E (Death Grip) to pull and root you, then slam an isolated Q for the bonus-damage trade","Sustain through your poke with W's shield-into-heal and grind extended walk-up trades","Hit 6 and Realm of Death (R) you into a stat-stealing 1v1 dragged away from your barrels"]},"early":"Morde out-trades me levels 1-3 and I just accept it. My barrels (E) have a long cooldown and a tiny HP bar he can free-hit to deny, and my bare Parrrley poke loses to his W shield plus an isolated-target Q. Do not stand next to a placed keg in his auto range or he gets the isolated Q on me AND pops my barrel for free. Last-hit with the tip of Q, hold W for his E pull, and concede the first few short trades.","mid":"Levels 4-5 I stabilize once I have a second keg and can Parrrley-into-keg poke him as he walks up to farm, so this stretch reads roughly even. But level 6 is his window, not mine: Realm of Death (R) yanks me into a box where my Cannon Barrage and barrel zoning mean nothing and the chunk of my stats he steals wins the straight duel. Bait his E early, then respect his realm range until my first item lands. Never burn W before his E pull, because cleansing it is what saves the all-in.","late":"Once Sheen into the upgraded keg build comes online I flip this lane and never look back. He has no dash, so a barrel-walled chain plus a maxed-rank Parrrley bursts him from a range he can't close, and my Cannon Barrage zones him off every objective. The only thing that still kills me is eating his R blind, so hold W to cleanse the E pull that sets it up, and play with vision so he never catches me alone for a realm. By 2+ items the isolated Q is the only tool he has left, and it's not enough.","whys":["Both of us are thin at level 1 with one ability, but my bare Parrrley poke and his lone Q slam roughly cancel out before kegs or his shield matter.","His W shield and isolated-target Q come online before my second keg does, so his auto-Q trade beats my single Parrrley here.","He grinds the level 2-3 short trades with W shield-into-heal sustain while my keg sits on a long cooldown and is free to deny, so the lane tilts his way.","I get a second keg and Parrrley-into-keg poke as he walks up to CS, pulling the lane back to even on his approach angles.","Realm of Death (R) drags me into a 1v1 where my global ult and barrel zoning are dead weight and the stats he steals win the box.","My Sheen-empowered Parrrley detonating a full barrel chain finally out-bursts his W-shield sustain from outside his E range.","A chained keg detonation plus a maxed-rank Parrrley deletes him from range, and with no dash he can never reach a barrel-walled me."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"nasus","win":["Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Nasus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"With two Parrrley points you tax every stack: he has to step into melee range to land Siphoning Strike, and your pistol shot out-ranges anything he can do back."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen line online (Sheen/Essence Reaver): an empowered Parrrley that detonates a Powder Keg chunks him and the chained slow lets you walk away before he reaches a stack."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage dropped on the wave zones him off his stacks, and its slow turns any jungle gank into a kill long before his Q is online."},{"when":"Late","text":"Past two items one Wither kills your kiting and a 400+ stack Siphoning Strike one-shots through your barrel chain — close the game before his Q stacks get there."}],"wants":{"you":["Parrrley him every time he reaches for a Siphoning Strike stack so his CS bleeds while yours doesn't","Land Parrrley into a Powder Keg detonation to poke and shove, denying him stacks under tower","Snowball the keg lead and end the game before his Q stacks and Fury of the Sands online"],"foe":["Free-farm Siphoning Strike stacks under tower without eating Parrrley poke","Land Wither mid-trade so you can't kite his slowed-but-empowered Q swing","Reach 2+ items and his stack threshold where one Wither all-in flips the lane"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are roughly even because your barrels aren't fully online and Nasus only wants to farm — but he has to walk into melee range to last-hit Siphoning Strike, and that step-up is free Parrrley harass. Don't dump E barrels here; their cooldown is long early and he'll just path around them. Pistol him every time he reaches for a stack, respect that his level 1 auto-and-Q poke is real, and don't get baited into extended auto trades where his stacked Q hurts.","mid":"This is your window. With a second Parrrley point and your first Sheen-line item (Sheen/Essence Reaver) you Parrrley-into-keg him every time he commits to a stack, and the empowered shot plus the chained barrel slow out-damages anything he swings back. At 6, Cannon Barrage on the wave zones him off his stacks and makes jungle ganks lethal. The one thing to dodge is Wither: if he lands it mid-trade you lose your kiting, so poke from barrel range and only all-in once it's on cooldown.","late":"Past two items the clock is his, not yours. A fully stacked Siphoning Strike plus the bonus damage and tankiness of Fury of the Sands lets him eat your barrel chain and one-shot back, and a single Wither locks your move and attack speed so you can't reposition kegs — that's the exact spot a Gangplank loses to a fed Nasus. Your job is to make sure that game never happens: snowball the lane in the mid window, take plates and use Cannon Barrage to swing objectives across the map, and end before his stacks turn the 1v1 around.","whys":["His level 1 auto-and-Q poke is real and your barrels aren't online yet — roughly even, just deny his Siphoning Strike last-hits.","With a second Parrrley point you out-range him: harass every time he steps into melee to stack, and his Q can't reach back.","Parrrley poke plus your first keg detonation starts to hurt — he either eats it or gives up the stack.","You out-trade a stackless Nasus; Parrrley-into-keg chunks him and his only answer is Wither, which you bait then punish.","Cannon Barrage on the wave zones him off his stacks and makes any jungle gank lethal before his Q scaling matters.","Empowered Parrrley off your Sheen line detonating a chained keg bursts him while his stack count is still low.","He out-scales hard: a stacked Siphoning Strike plus Fury of the Sands tanks your barrels and Wither kills your kiting — this is his window, not yours."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"nautilus","win":["Skill","Nautilus","Nautilus","Skill","Nautilus","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Nautilus's window: he hits 2 first and a Dredge Line (Q) hook into a Staggering Blow auto-root is a long lockdown your kegs can't punish back yet, so don't last-hit standing in hook range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Depth Charge (R) single-target knockup plus a jungler is a real dive, but Remove Scurvy cleanses the knockup and heals off missing HP, so hold W for the ult/gank CC, never spend it on the first hook."},{"when":"1st item (Sheen)","text":"Sheen turns the lane: a Sheen-empowered Parrrley detonating a Powder Keg chains a slow-and-burst an immobile Nautilus can't walk out of, and Naut has no Sheen spike to answer it."},{"when":"Late","text":"Chained keg explosions plus global Cannon Barrage let you zone an immobile tank off every objective; a tank Naut can peel with hook but can never burst you down in return."}],"wants":{"you":["Place Powder Kegs outside Dredge Line (Q) range and detonate with Parrrley so you poke without eating the auto-root","Hold Remove Scurvy for his Depth Charge (R) knockup or a hook-into-gank, never for the first poke","Farm even through levels 2-3, then snowball once Sheen turns your keg-chain into real burst"],"foe":["Land a blind-side Dredge Line (Q) into the Staggering Blow auto-root to lock you for a full melee combo","Use his Titan's Wrath (W) shield and Riptide (E) AoE to win extended trades while your barrels are on cooldown","Shove the wave and roam or set up a Depth Charge (R) dive with his jungler before you out-scale him"]},"early":"Naut trades you evenly at level 1, then edges you at 2-3 when he has the Dredge Line hook plus a Staggering Blow auto-root and you still have no real waveclear and brittle, free-hittable barrels. Do not last-hit standing next to a Powder Keg you've placed inside his hook range, he'll just walk up, Q you, and root-auto you off it for a long chunk trade. Last-hit with the tip of Parrrley, keep kegs back as zoning tools, and respect that his hook into auto-root is a lockdown your early kit simply can't answer back yet.","mid":"From 4-5 you stabilize: a second keg and points in Q let you poke with Parrrley-into-keg from outside Dredge Line range, and the lane settles toward even. At 6 his Depth Charge is a dive enabler more than a duel button, so the key discipline is W timing, Remove Scurvy cleanses the hook root AND the ult knockup and heals off missing HP, but always keep a cleanse for whichever lockup precedes a gank rather than burning it on poke. You won't kill a stacking tank in lane, and you don't need to, you just farm safe and reach your Sheen spike.","late":"This is where you take over. Once Sheen lands, a Sheen-empowered Parrrley detonating a full Powder Keg chain bursts and slows him, and a tank Nautilus has zero dash to escape a keg field, only his hook to peel. He can never burst you back, so your only losing condition is his perma-CC catching you out for the team, which means side-laning behind Cannon Barrage zoning and never face-checking a Dredge Line. Out-scale him, control objectives with global R pressure, and let your barrels do the rest.","whys":["Both of you trade evenly at level 1, his Dredge Line hook is single and telegraphed and the root needs a follow-up auto, so dodge the keg-side hook and last-hit from range.","Nautilus spikes at 2 with hook plus Staggering Blow auto-root before your kegs come online, so a clean Q on you is a long chunk you can't answer yet.","He still edges level 3 since your second keg is fragile and free to detonate, so place barrels outside hook range and poke with Parrrley instead of dueling his Riptide trades.","Your Parrrley-into-keg poke now matches his sustained W/E trade, so it evens out, hold Remove Scurvy to cleanse the hook root rather than spending it on poke.","His Depth Charge knockup plus a jungler makes 6 a dive threat he can convert, so this window leans Naut unless you keep W for the ult or gank CC.","Sheen-empowered Parrrley detonating a keg chain starts to burst and slow him, and a tank Naut has no dash to walk out of the AoE.","Chained keg explosions plus global Cannon Barrage let you out-scale and zone an immobile tank who can never burst you back."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"neeko","win":["Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Neeko out-pokes you early: Blooming Burst (Q) chunks you and Tangle-Barbs (E) roots you for a free follow-up before you have a single keg down. Last-hit at Parrrley range and never sit still in E range at low HP."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"With a second point in E (Powder Keg), drop a barrel where she farms and Parrrley-detonate it as she steps up — the chain slow sticks a dashless squishy in place for the whole combo."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pop Blossom (R) makes her briefly untargetable then stuns the AoE on landing — but Remove Scurvy (W) cleanses the stun and heals you, so bank W for her ult, not her E root."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Sheen spike (Essence Reaver / Trinity Force) lands: an empowered Parrrley plus a full keg chain bursts a squishy clone-mage you now hard out-scale in the 1v1."}],"wants":{"you":["Place a keg next to the wave and Parrrley-detonate it on Neeko as she walks up to farm — chain the slow so a dashless mage can't reposition out of the burst","Hold Remove Scurvy for Pop Blossom's stun, not her Tangle-Barbs root — cleansing the ult heals you and blanks her entire pick combo","Survive the level 1-3 poke window, hit your Sheen keg spike, and one-combo her squishy frame before she can re-disguise with W"],"foe":["Land Tangle-Barbs (E) to root you, then chain Blooming Burst (Q) plus passive bonus-damage autos for a free poke trade before your kegs are online","Disguise as a minion or ally with W to bait your keg detonation, then flank and Pop Blossom-stun you into her full burst","Cancel a fight she can't win 1v1 and instead roam with R to set up picks on your team mid-game"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Neeko if you're careless. Blooming Burst (Q) pokes you from range and Tangle-Barbs (E) roots you for a free follow-up, while you have no waveclear or keg pressure yet. Don't step into E-root range just to place a barrel she can free-hit and zone you off of. Last-hit at the tip of Parrrley, eat minimal poke, and respect that her root is the setup for everything — never get caught stationary at low mana. The saving grace: she has no dash, so the moment your kegs come online she can't escape the chain.","mid":"This is where you take the lane over. With a second point in Powder Keg you can drop a barrel where she farms and Parrrley-detonate it the instant she steps up, and the chained slow means a dashless squishy can't walk out of it. At 6 her Pop Blossom is the only scary beat — she goes briefly untargetable then stuns the AoE on landing — but Remove Scurvy cleanses the stun outright and heals off your missing HP, so save W for her ult and the lane swings hard. Bait her E or her clone, then punish the cooldown with a keg combo.","late":"You out-scale her cleanly: chained keg detonations plus the global zoning of Cannon Barrage outweigh a squishy pick-mage who needs a clean Pop Blossom to matter. Her threat shifts to the map — W clone-disguise flanks and R picks on your team in the mid-game — so keep Remove Scurvy up for her ult and don't facecheck brush where a Neeko clone might be sitting. In a straight 1v1 she can't kill a Gangplank who cleanses her stun, heals through her poke, and bursts her from keg range.","whys":["Neeko out-trades your keg-less level 1: Blooming Burst pokes and Tangle-Barbs roots you with no waveclear or barrel to answer — just deny her Q last-hits and ride it out.","Her E root still sets up a free Q-plus-passive poke combo and you can't punish it yet, so it stays a coinflip on positioning — farm at Parrrley range and never step up stationary.","Your second Powder Keg point comes online: detonate a barrel on her as she walks up and the chain slow pins a dashless squishy with no escape.","You out-trade a pre-item Neeko now — bait her Tangle-Barbs or W clone, then burst her on the cooldown with a keg chain she can't dodge.","At 6 it evens out: Pop Blossom is a strong AoE stun, but Remove Scurvy cleanses and heals it — the window is only even if you waste W on her E root instead of her ult.","Your Sheen spike (Essence Reaver / Trinity Force) lands: empowered Parrrley plus a full keg chain bursts her squishy frame in one combo.","You hard out-scale her — chained kegs and global Cannon Barrage beat a pick-mage who can't kill a GP that cleanses her stun and heals through her poke."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"olaf","win":["Olaf","Olaf","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Olaf's window: he throws Undertow, runs over to pick the axe back up for the move/attack speed, and walks you down with the slow before your barrels have HP or a low enough cooldown to zone him off the wave."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Olaf's Ragnarok makes him CC-immune, so Cannon Barrage's slow can't peel him off you mid-all-in; pair it with Reckless Swing (E) true damage and your W cleanse can't stop the burst once he's on top of you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Sheen/Essence Reaver spike lands: empowered Parrrley detonating a chained keg finally out-trades his axe-throws and lets you poke him out before he can stack his all-in."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Chained Powder Keg detonations zone and burst him from range as your barrel uptime climbs, but a fed Olaf can still Ragnarok through the slows and Reckless Swing you down — respect his R timer when you're alone."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 last-hitting at the tip of Parrrley (Q) range, never trading into the Undertow slow that drags you into his auto range","Lower your Powder Keg (E) cooldown and start Parrrley-into-keg poke from 4-5 so he eats chip every time he walks up to farm","Hit your first-item Sheen/Essence Reaver spike, chain kegs to out-trade his axe-throws, then scale into the global-pressure carry he can't match"],"foe":["Throw Undertow then pick the axe back up for the move/attack speed and chain the slow onto you levels 1-3","Free-hit your low-HP barrels (E) to pop them before they arm, killing your zone and poke","All-in under Ragnarok so he's CC-immune to your kegs and Cannon Barrage while Reckless Swing (E) true damage shreds you through your W cleanse"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are his — Olaf throws Undertow, runs over to retrieve the axe for the move and attack speed, and walks you down behind the slow before you have any waveclear or barrel HP to answer. Don't force a Q-into-keg trade here: your Powder Keg (E) has barely any health and he'll just free-hit it to pop it before it arms. Last-hit at the tip of Parrrley (Q) range, concede a little CS, and never let the Undertow slow stick you in his auto range — that's how you feed a level-2 all-in.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize: a second keg point and a lower Q cooldown let you start landing Parrrley-into-keg poke, so he takes chip every time he steps up to farm. At 6 respect his Ragnarok (R) — it makes him CC-immune, so Cannon Barrage's slow and your keg slows can't peel him once he ults in, and his Reckless Swing (E) deals true damage that punches through armor. Remove Scurvy (W) cleanses the Undertow slow and heals you, but it can't undo damage from a foe who's already CC-immune — so bait or trade only when his R is down.","late":"Once your Sheen/Essence Reaver and keg build come online you take over — empowered Parrrley detonating a full chained barrel bursts him from range before his axes ever reach you, and global Cannon Barrage gives you cross-map pressure his single-target kit can't match. Still respect a fed Olaf: with Ragnarok up he's CC-immune to your keg slows and his Reckless Swing true damage ignores armor, so don't get caught alone when his R is available. Keep him at barrel range, deny the pick-up axe, and let his pressure fall off while you scale into the map carry.","whys":["Olaf throws Undertow, retrieves the axe for move/attack speed, and walks you down behind the slow — you have no waveclear and your barrels aren't online to zone him.","At level 2 the Undertow slow plus auto pressure beats your short trades, and your low-HP keg gets free-hit and denied before it arms — concede CS and play safe.","Your second keg point and lower Q cooldown bring Parrrley-into-keg poke online, evening out his walk-up to farm.","At 6 Ragnarok makes him CC-immune so your kegs and Cannon Barrage can't peel, but it adds no damage and Remove Scurvy cleanses the slow — the window trades to roughly even.","Sheen/Essence Reaver-empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation finally out-trades his axe-throws — your first-item spike flips the lane in your favor.","Chained keg detonations let you zone and burst him from range before he can stack an all-in, so the mid-game farm phase tilts to you.","Kegs one-shot him from range, but a fed Olaf with Ragnarok up can still all-in through your slows and Reckless Swing you down — genuinely even by full items."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"ornn","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Ornn's strongest window. With W (Bellows Breath) to apply Brittle and E (Searing Charge) to dash a pillar into you against the wall, he can knock you up, Brittle-stun, and pop your barrel before you ever detonate it. Respect his all-in here."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ornn's R (Call of the Forge God) recast knocks up a second time and re-applies Brittle, but it's a teamfight/setup ult, not a 1v1 button. Outside a jungle dive this stage stays even and you keep poking from range."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen (Essence Reaver/Triforce) online. Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a chained Powder Keg detonation finally out-damages his Bellows Breath chunk, and he can't trade the poke back, so you start tilting the lane your way."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"You own it. Chained keg explosions plus crit Parrrley shred a tank who can only self-itemize armor through Living Forge, has no dash to catch you, and no sustain to outlast the poke. Global Cannon Barrage adds map pressure he can't match."}],"wants":{"you":["Place Powder Kegs (E) outside his Bellows Breath cone and pop them with Parrrley (Q) from range so he eats poke without Brittling you or destroying the barrel first","Hold W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse his Brittle stun or R double-knockup, then heal the missing-HP chunk back to negate his all-in","Reach your Sheen first-item spike clean; Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a keg chain is the window you flip from even to favoured"],"foe":["Land E (Searing Charge) to dash a pillar and knock you up against terrain, then W Bellows Breath Brittle so the next hit stuns and chunks you","Self-itemize armor through Living Forge passive (no recall needed) so your physical Parrrley and crit damage scale down each item","Hit R (Call of the Forge God) and recast for the second knockup plus Brittle to chain CC into a jungle dive on you"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are Ornn's, not yours. Your barrels have long early cooldowns and low HP, and Ornn can simply walk up and auto them dead before you detonate. Do NOT place a keg inside his Bellows Breath (W) cone in melee range: he Brittles you, and a follow-up hit stuns. Last-hit with the tip of Parrrley (Q) from max range, hug your side, and never get pinned against the wall. His E (Searing Charge) pillar knockup into Brittle is the only thing that can actually kill you this early.","mid":"Levels 4-6 you stabilize as you put more points into E/Q and can land Parrrley-into-keg poke from outside his Bellows Breath range, forcing him to choose between farming and taking free chip. His level 6 R (Call of the Forge God) looks scary because the recast double-knockups and re-applies Brittle, but it's a setup tool for ganks and teamfights, not a 1v1 kill button. Hold your W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse the Brittle stun or the ult knockup and heal the damage right back. Don't all-in yet; this stage is even and you just want to reach your Sheen spike with your health bar intact.","late":"Once Sheen (Essence Reaver/Triforce) lands the lane tilts to you and only gets worse for him. Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a full chained Powder Keg detonation out-damages his Bellows Breath faster than he can armor-stack through Living Forge, and he has no dash to close on you and no sustain to outlast the poke. By two items you're a keg-and-crit carry with global Cannon Barrage (R) pressure across the map, while he's a slow, immobile tank who self-itemizes but can't catch you. Just respect his engage in skirmishes: your W cleanses one knockup, but stay out of his pillar-into-R Brittle chain.","whys":["Ornn is a strong, tanky level 1 with Bellows Breath Brittle while your barrels have long cooldowns and are free-hittable. Last-hit at max Parrrley range and don't trade into his stats.","He still out-stats and out-sustains you and can walk you down. Never place a keg inside his Bellows Breath cone in melee range or he Brittles you and pops it before you detonate.","At 3 his E Searing-Charge pillar knockup against the wall plus W Brittle stun is a real all-in. This is his peak window, so hug your side and respect it.","You get more E/Q points and start landing Parrrley-into-keg poke from outside his W range. Even now, just farm safely toward your spike.","His R recast is a second knockup plus Brittle, but it's a gank/teamfight setup ult, not a duel button. Hold W to cleanse it and the stage stays even.","Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation finally out-damages his Bellows Breath chunk and he can't trade the poke back. This is where you flip favoured.","Chained keg explosions and crit Parrrley out-scale a no-mobility, no-sustain tank who can only self-itemize through Living Forge, and global Cannon Barrage adds pressure he can't match. You own the late."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"pantheon","win":["Pantheon","Pantheon","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Pantheon's Comet Spear (Q) poke plus Aegis Assault (passive) blocking your Parrrley/AA hits means he wins every short trade before you have a second Powder Keg (E) charge to zone with."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"A second point in Parrrley (Q) and Powder Keg (E) lets you start chip-poking a keg from range, so Pantheon can no longer free-hit you when he walks up to last-hit."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen (into Essence Reaver/Trinity) flips it: empowered Parrrley detonating a chained Powder Keg out-bursts Pantheon, who has no item scaling and is already falling off after 6."},{"when":"Late","text":"Chained keg detonations one-shot Pantheon's squishy frame and Cannon Barrage (R) zones him off every objective and side-lane, while his Shield Vault (W) stun no longer threatens your sustain."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 by last-hitting cannon and casters with Parrrley (Q) from max range instead of stepping into Comet Spear (Q) and his Aegis-blocked AA trades","Reach your Sheen/Essence Reaver first-item spike where empowered Parrrley detonates a chained Powder Keg (E) for a burst Pantheon cannot match","Scale into the 2+ item phase where keg chains one-shot his squishy frame and Cannon Barrage (R) controls objectives, well past his level 1-6 ceiling"],"foe":["Land Comet Spear (Q) poke into a Shield Vault (W) gap-close stun to all-in you at levels 1-3 while your Powder Keg (E) is on cooldown","Use his level 6 Grand Starfall (R) to roam or dive and snowball a lead before you reach your item spike","Block your Parrrley and basic-attack damage with Aegis Assault (passive) to win short trades and end the game before you scale"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Pantheon and you have to respect it. His Comet Spear (Q) out-pokes you, his Aegis Assault passive periodically blocks your Parrrley (Q) and basic attacks from the front so AA trades go to him, and your single Powder Keg (E) has a long cooldown and low HP he can free-hit to deny your zoning. Do not step up into Q range to last-hit with autos; secure the cannon and caster minions with Parrrley from max distance, and hold Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse his Shield Vault (W) stun and heal the chip if he commits a gap-close all-in. Eat a little poke, farm safe, and survive to your stabilizing levels.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stabilize as you pick up a second point in Parrrley (Q) and Powder Keg (E) and can start landing Q-into-keg poke, forcing Pantheon to walk into your barrel range to farm instead of free-hitting you. His level 6 Grand Starfall (R) is a roam and dive threat rather than a 1v1 win button here, so ward your flanks and don't get caught shoved in. Bait his Shield Vault (W), then poke him with Parrrley detonating a keg while it's on cooldown, and keep Remove Scurvy (W) ready to cleanse the stun if he tries to re-engage. The lane is tilting your way but he can still punish a greedy step.","late":"Once you hit your Sheen/Essence Reaver first-item spike the lane flips hard and stays yours: empowered Parrrley (Q) detonating a chained Powder Keg (E) bursts Pantheon's squishy frame faster than he can answer, because he buys no scaling and falls off a cliff after level 6. By 2+ items you own this completely. Chained keg detonations one-shot him, Cannon Barrage (R) zones him off every objective and siege, and his point-click Shield Vault (W) stun is no longer enough to all-in through your Remove Scurvy (W) heal. Just don't get griefed out of the game before you arrive.","whys":["Pantheon's Comet Spear (Q) out-pokes your level 1 and his Aegis Assault passive blocks your Parrrley and basic attacks from the front, so every short trade goes to him.","His Shield Vault (W) is a point-click gap-close stun that lets him all-in you while your single Powder Keg is on a long cooldown and easy for him to free-hit and deny.","By levels 4-5 your second Parrrley and Powder Keg points let you chip-poke a keg from range and his level 6 Grand Starfall is a roam tool not a duel-winner, but he still threatens the all-in, so it is roughly even.","Your Sheen/Essence Reaver spike flips the lane: empowered Parrrley detonating a chained Powder Keg out-bursts a Pantheon who buys no scaling to keep up.","Pantheon has no item scaling and falls off after level 6, so as your kegs and on-hit damage grow he can no longer win the trades he dominated early.","By 2+ items chained keg detonations one-shot his squishy frame and Remove Scurvy cleanses his Shield Vault stun, so his only all-in tool stops landing.","Cannon Barrage zones Pantheon off objectives, sieges, and side-lanes from across the map, giving you map control he has no answer for once he falls off."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"poppy","win":["Poppy","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Poppy walks you down: her Q (Hammer Shock) chunks any short trade and she can free-hit your barrels off cooldown before they gain enough HP to survive, denying your only ranged pressure."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"A second point in Q (Parrrley) and E lets you start Parrrley-into-keg poke from outside her E charge range, where her melee autos and short E can't trade back."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver online: a Sheen-empowered Parrrley detonating a chained keg finally out-bursts her, and W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses her E wall-stun to break her one all-in."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Chained Powder Keg detonations and global Cannon Barrage let you zone and burst from range while she stays an immobile melee tank with no gap-closer but E."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 with safe Parrrley last-hits and let your barrels age to full HP before you try to zone with them","Reach Sheen/Essence Reaver so empowered Parrrley plus a full keg chain bursts her down from outside E range","Hold W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse her E wall-stun and heal off the all-in she commits with it"],"foe":["Walk you down levels 1-3 with Q chip and free-hit your low-HP barrels off cooldown to deny your poke","Charge you into a wall with E for the long stun, then Q-slam and auto before your kegs come back up","Stay tanky and trade evenly into the lane, looking for the E pin to set up ganks before you out-scale"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Poppy and you have to respect it. Her Q (Hammer Shock) chips you in any short trade, and she'll free-hit your barrels to pop them before they ever age to enough HP to survive, denying your only ranged pressure. Don't try to zone with kegs you can't protect yet — last-hit at max Parrrley range, eat a little chip, and never get caught next to a wall where her E (Heroic Charge) carries you in for the stun and sets up her full Q-into-auto combo.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize: a second point in Parrrley and E lets you start landing Parrrley-into-keg poke from outside her E charge range, a window her melee autos and short E simply can't answer, so the trade math finally goes even. Level 6 Cannon Barrage adds zoning and dive setup but doesn't win the straight duel against a tank, so keep it roughly skill-based and farm toward your item. Bait out her E wall-pin — once she's burned her one hard engage, you're free to set up barrels safely.","late":"This is where you take over. With Sheen/Essence Reaver and a full keg build, a Sheen-empowered Parrrley detonating a chained Powder Keg out-bursts her, and by 2+ items you zone and burst from a range her immobile melee kit can never close, since her only gap-closer is E. W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses her E wall-stun and heals you, so her one hard-CC engage just fizzles, and global Cannon Barrage lets you pressure the whole map while she's stuck as a frontline tank. Don't dive into her — make her commit E to you, then make her come to your barrels.","whys":["Her Q chip and autos win every short trade while your barrels still have no HP and long cooldowns, so you can't punish her back yet.","You both want the level-2 spike, but she can free-hit your kegs to deny them and her Q-into-auto out-trades your single Parrrley.","Neither lands a clean kill yet — you trade Parrrley poke for her Q chip, and her E wall-pin near terrain is the only real all-in threat.","Your second Parrrley/E point lets you poke from outside her E range, but she stays tanky and trades evenly until your item comes online.","Cannon Barrage adds zoning and dive setup but doesn't out-duel a tank one-on-one, so the lane stays skill-based outside ganks.","Sheen/Essence Reaver makes empowered Parrrley detonate a chained keg for real burst, and W cleanses her E wall-stun to break her all-in.","Chained Powder Keg detonations and global Cannon Barrage let you burst and zone from range while she's stuck as an immobile melee tank."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"quinn","win":["Quinn","Quinn","Quinn","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Quinn's Vault (E) knocks you back and resets, interrupting your keg placement, while Harrier-marked autos chunk you every time you step up to last-hit — her hardest window before you have barrel poke."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your second E point lets you stack two Powder Kegs and detonate the chain with Parrrley (Q) from outside Vault range, so you finally trade poke without eating a Harrier proc."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen online (into Trinity Force): an empowered Parrrley auto-attack-reset into a chained keg detonation finally bursts her squishy frame faster than Heightened Senses can kite you out."},{"when":"Late","text":"Cannon Barrage (R) zones her off objectives globally and a full chained barrel detonation one-shots her — your scaling reclaims the lane she bullied in the first three levels."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 by last-hitting at Parrrley (Q) range and refusing Harrier-marked auto trades","Reach Sheen/Trinity Force so empowered Parrrley resets plus chained keg detonations out-burst her kite","Use Cannon Barrage (R) to zone her off objectives and answer the roams she runs with Behind Enemy Lines"],"foe":["Vault (E) into you to knock you back and reset, interrupting your keg setup every trade","Stack Harrier marks and empowered autos to poke you down before your barrels come online","Roam with Heightened Senses (W) move speed and Behind Enemy Lines (R) to snowball lanes off your weak early"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are hers and you have to accept it. Her Vault (E) dashes in, knocks you back, and resets if it connects, so every keg you try to set up gets interrupted, and her Harrier passive marks you for a bonus-damage empowered auto she can land and kite away from before you answer. Do not try to trade — last-hit at max Parrrley (Q) range, never walk into Vault range to place a keg, and hold Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse the Vault knockback effects and heal the poke back when she over-commits.","mid":"This is where you climb back to even. With a second E point you can drop two Powder Kegs and detonate the chain with Parrrley from outside her Vault range, so you finally poke her without eating a Harrier-marked auto. At 6 your Cannon Barrage isn't a duel-winner here — she'll just Heightened-Senses out of it — but it lets you zone her off the wave and threaten her while her Vault is down. Bait the E: once she's burned Vault to engage or disengage, that's your window to walk up and place a real keg.","late":"Now the lane flips to you. Sheen into Trinity Force turns an empowered Parrrley auto-reset plus a chained keg detonation into burst that deletes her squishy frame faster than Heightened Senses can kite you out, and by two items a full barrel chain one-shots her. Cannon Barrage zones her off every objective and punishes the roams she used to bully you with. Just respect that she's a roaming menace with Behind Enemy Lines until then — track her on the map and don't let her snowball your sidelanes while you scale.","whys":["Her Vault (E) knocks you back and resets to interrupt your keg setup, and you have no barrel poke yet to answer it.","Harrier-marked empowered autos let her chunk you on every step-up while your Powder Keg cooldowns are long and your barrels easy to deny.","She out-pokes you with Vault burst plus Heightened Senses kite before you have a second keg to chain-detonate from range.","Your second E point lets you Parrrley-detonate two chained kegs from outside Vault range, pulling the poke war back to even.","Cannon Barrage adds zoning but she kites out of it with Heightened Senses, so level 6 is a wash rather than a power spike for you.","Sheen into Trinity Force gives Parrrley an auto-attack reset so a chained keg detonation finally out-bursts her Harrier kite.","A two-item chained barrel detonation one-shots her squishy frame and Cannon Barrage zones her off every objective globally."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"renekton","win":["Renekton","Renekton","Skill","Gangplank","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Renekton owns these levels — his W (Ruthless Predator) stun and Slice-and-Dice dash let him point-click chunk you as you walk up to last-hit, and he can free-hit your lone E barrel off the wall before your poke exists."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Second points in Q and E come online: now you Parrrley-detonate a Powder Keg from range, so Renekton has to eat barrel poke just to walk up and CS."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen into the keg build lands — an empowered Parrrley plus a full chained keg detonation bursts him exactly as his early fury-bully phase falls off."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Renekton has no sustained threat left once items come in; he can't reach you through the barrel field, and global Cannon Barrage prints cross-map pressure off your lane lead."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive his levels 1-3 fury bully, then reach the level 4-5 window where Parrrley-detonated kegs out-range him","Hold W (Remove Scurvy) for his empowered-W stun, not his Q slow, and heal back the chip from his dash-in combo","Scale to your first-item Sheen keg spike where his point-click fury damage stops mattering and chained kegs zone him out"],"foe":["Snowball levels 1-3 with the empowered-W stun into a Slice-and-Dice all-in before your barrels are set up","Free-hit your lone Powder Keg off the wall so you have no poke and must walk into his range to CS","Force the all-in while his fury bar is full and dash is up, ending the lane before he hard falls off into items"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are his, full stop — I have no real waveclear, my single keg has a long early cooldown and low HP that he just free-hits off the wall, and his empowered W (Ruthless Predator) stun plus his Slice-and-Dice dash let him point-click chunk me every time I step up to last-hit. Don't try to trade here; place the keg tight to the wave so he can't pop it for free, take only the CS I can reach safely, and hold W (Remove Scurvy) for the empowered-W stun, not his Q slow. Accept I'm a bit behind on the map and just don't feed his fury bar.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are where I climb out: second points in Q and E mean I can Parrrley-detonate a keg from range, so now Renekton has to walk into barrel poke just to farm. At 6 my Cannon Barrage adds zone and dive pressure but doesn't win the raw duel into a full fury bar, so 6 is roughly even — don't all-in him while his W and dash are up. Bait the Slice-and-Dice and the stun, W-cleanse it, then detonate the keg chain while he's stuck committed.","late":"This is the payoff — once Renekton's fury phase is spent he has no sustained damage, and the moment my Sheen keg build comes online a full chained detonation bursts and zones him off everything. By 2+ items he physically can't close the gap through the barrel field, my empowered Parrrley out-trades his point-click fury, and global Cannon Barrage prints cross-map pressure. He had to kill me early; if he didn't, I run the lane and snowball the map.","whys":["Renekton's level-1 empowered W (Ruthless Predator) stun plus his point-click fury combo bully you while you have zero waveclear and a free-hittable keg.","At 2 his fury all-in out-damages anything you have, and he pops your single long-cooldown keg off the wall to deny your only poke.","By 3 you can chunk him with a Parrrley-detonated keg, but his Slice-and-Dice-into-stun all-in still trades even, so it's a knife-edge.","Your second Q and E points let you Parrrley-detonate kegs from range, so now Renekton eats barrel poke just to walk up and CS.","Cannon Barrage adds zone and dive threat but doesn't win the 1v1 into a full fury bar, so level 6 is a coin-flip outside ganks.","Your Sheen keg spike lets an empowered Parrrley plus a full chained detonation burst him exactly as his fury bully phase ends.","At 2+ items chained keg detonations and global Cannon Barrage own a Renekton who has no sustained damage left once you survive his early."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"riven","win":["Riven","Riven","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Riven's window: her Broken Wings (Q) chain dashes onto you and the third cast knocks up, she can E-dash in or out, and she free-hits your low-HP Powder Keg to pop it early and deny your detonation before you have a second keg charge."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"You stabilize as Parrrley and Keg rank up - start landing Parrrley-into-keg poke from outside her Q-dash range, chipping her down between her engage cooldowns."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen (into Trinity/Triforce on the keg build) is your flip: a Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation out-bursts her combo when she dashes onto the barrel."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"You become the carry - chained keg explosions and global Cannon Barrage (R) zoning outscale Riven, and W cleanses her CC so her dive no longer locks you down."}],"wants":{"you":["Place Powder Kegs at max range and away from Riven so she can't auto them to pop them early, and last-hit with Parrrley instead of stepping into Broken Wings range","Bait her Q-dash and E onto a keg, then Parrrley-detonate the chain into her as she commits her combo","Hold W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse her third-Q knockup or W stun and heal the burst, then turn the all-in once your kegs are up"],"foe":["Use Broken Wings' dashes and the third-cast knockup to run you down before your kegs have HP, comboing with her E-dash and W stun","Free-hit your Powder Keg to detonate it early and deny your poke, then all-in while your keg charges are on cooldown","Snowball an early lead and force fights before your first-item Sheen spike and keg scaling take over"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are hers and you know it - Riven's Broken Wings dashes close the gap, the third cast knocks you up, and she can E-dash in for a W-stun combo before your barrels have the HP to zone. Place your Powder Keg out at max range and as far from her as you can so she can't just auto it to pop it early and deny the detonation, and last-hit with Parrrley instead of stepping into her dash range. Don't try to trade autos here; your keg charges are slow to come back and you have no waveclear, so eat a little chip and farm. The one thing that bails you out is W - keep Remove Scurvy up for when she commits the full knockup-into-W combo.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you climb back toward even. As Parrrley and Keg rank up you start poking: Parrrley into a barrel from outside her Q-dash range, chipping her between her engage cooldowns and resetting the lane on your terms. The trap to set is your keg - if she E-dashes onto it to all-in, you Parrrley-detonate the chain into her combo window and W-cleanse her knockup or stun. At 6 her power is the combo, not her ult; your Cannon Barrage isn't a 1v1 button but it zones her off the wave and punishes a dive, so this stretch is a coinflip decided by who respects the other's cooldowns.","late":"Once your first item lands - Sheen into the Trinity/keg build - the lane tilts your way for good. A Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a full chained keg detonation out-bursts her combo, so every time she dashes onto a barrel she takes more than she deals. W cleanses the knockup or W stun that lets her all-in stick, and by 2+ items chained kegs and global Cannon Barrage make you the 1v9 carry while Riven's flat scaling falls off. Don't get cocky pre-item, but after Sheen you force the all-in onto your kegs and she can't answer it.","whys":["Riven's level-1 Broken Wings dash plus a free auto on your low-HP keg pops it early and denies the detonation, and you have no waveclear or trade to answer her.","Her Broken Wings third cast knocks up and she can chain E-dash into W's stun to walk you down before your barrels are online to zone.","By level 3 you've placed kegs at max range and have Parrrley to last-hit - she can still walk you down, but you can deny the free dive, so it's a coinflip.","As Parrrley and Keg rank up you poke from outside her Q-dash range - even trades while you respect her engage cooldowns.","At 6 Cannon Barrage zones her off the wave and punishes a dive but isn't a 1v1 button, so the level stays a skill matchup decided by cooldowns.","Sheen into the keg build means a Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a chained detonation out-bursts her combo, and W cleanses her knockup on the all-in.","Chained keg explosions and global Cannon Barrage make you the scaling carry while Riven falls off, and W shuts down the CC her dive needs to stick."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"rumble","win":["Skill","Rumble","Rumble","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Rumble's Flamespitter (Q) out-DPSes your autos in melee and free-hits your Powder Kegs (E) before your barrel chain exists, so he wins point-blank trades and denies your keg setup."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Equalizer (R) carpets the wave and your keg cluster, zoning you off farm; that long ult cooldown is your window to step up and poke."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver online: Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a full chained keg detonation finally out-bursts a single Flamespitter rotation if you space it from range."},{"when":"Mid-late","text":"Two-keg chains and global Cannon Barrage (R) outrange Rumble's melee-leash kit; he must walk into your barrels to deal damage while you poke from a screen away."}],"wants":{"you":["Detonate Powder Kegs (E) with Parrrley (Q) from max range so Flamespitter never touches you","Bait his Equalizer (R) or wait it out, then step up and trade while it's on cooldown","Survive to your Sheen/keg item spike and out-poke his overheat windows"],"foe":["Free-hit your low-HP barrels with Flamespitter (Q) before they can chain, then overheat for the Danger Zone burst","Land Electro Harpoon (E) to slow and stick you in Flamespitter range during his heated window","Drop Equalizer (R) on your keg cluster to deny farm and zone you off the wave"]},"early":"Rumble's Flamespitter (Q) is the early-game problem. It out-DPSes your autos point-blank and free-hits your Powder Kegs (E) before they can chain, so don't place barrels where his cone can pop them. Farm with the tip of Parrrley (Q) and stay out of Flamespitter range entirely; if he overheats into the Danger Zone his Q burn and the bonus damage will shred you. Never trade autos into a heated Rumble at levels 1-3 - your durability loses that exchange.","mid":"The lane stabilizes as your keg poke comes online. Land Parrrley into a Powder Keg from range to chunk him without eating Flamespitter, and punish his cooldowns - Rumble has no escape once Scrap Shield (W) is down, so a clean keg-Parrrley combo trades up. Remove Scurvy (W) heals you out of his poke chip, but don't rely on it to fully erase an Electro Harpoon (E) slow. At 6, respect Equalizer (R): never fight inside the zone - reposition your barrels and make him commit his ult before you step up.","late":"Once your Sheen and keg build come together you flip this lane and own the scaling. Chained Powder Keg detonations and global Cannon Barrage (R) outrange everything Rumble has, and he's a melee-range AP bruiser who must walk into your barrels to deal damage. He's not a hard scaler like Vladimir or Kassadin, so your sidelane 1v1 wins outright - just never get caught standing in his Equalizer during a fight, where his AoE burn and the slow lock you in.","whys":["Both champs are weak at level 1 and neither wants to commit - deny his last-hits and set up safe keg placement outside Flamespitter range.","Rumble's Flamespitter (Q) out-DPSes your autos in melee and free-hits your low-HP barrels before they can chain - concede the trade here.","A heated Flamespitter plus an Electro Harpoon (E) slow lets him stick and burn you while your kegs are still on a long cooldown.","You get a second Q/E point and start landing Parrrley-into-keg poke from range while Remove Scurvy heals the chip - the lane evens out.","His Equalizer (R) zones your keg setup but isn't a duel-winner, and your own Cannon Barrage answers cross-map - roughly even outside coordinated plays.","Sheen/Essence Reaver empowers Parrrley and your full chained keg detonation finally out-bursts a single Flamespitter rotation - force trades on your spike.","You out-scale a melee AP bruiser through chained kegs and a global ult, and he's no Vlad-tier scaler - your late-game sidelane 1v1 wins."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"ryze","win":["Ryze","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Skill","Ryze","Ryze"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Ryze's ranged Q out-trades your single-point Parrrley and chips you while your one Powder Keg sits on a long cooldown — last-hit from max range, don't auto into his Q."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Second points in Q and E let you Parrrley-detonate a keg for a chaining slow-AoE he has to walk through to CS — your first window to contest the wave and zone his free Q farm."},{"when":"1st item (Sheen)","text":"Sheen into Trinity Force online: an empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation bursts a pre-Tear Ryze who steps up — punish before his Archangel's/Tear stacks come in."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Tear-stacked Ryze becomes a ranged raid boss — his W root sets up the Q/E burst chain and his sustained DPS melts you faster than kegs can zone him."}],"wants":{"you":["Hit your Sheen/Trinity Force spike and burst him with an empowered Parrrley into a chained keg detonation before his Tear stacks","Use the Powder Keg slow-AoE to zone his step-up CS and deny the free Q farming his combo relies on","Pop Remove Scurvy (W) the instant his W root lands to cleanse it and heal the Q poke back, then disengage"],"foe":["Poke you down with spammy ranged Q at levels 1-3 while your kegs are on cooldown and can be destroyed before they detonate","Land the W root (set up by E) to lock you for the Q/E burst chain, then reset Q off the kill/spread","Reach 2+ items and a stacked Tear to become an unkiteable ranged raid boss who out-DPSes your barrels"]},"early":"Ryze owns levels 1-3 here — his Q is a spammable ranged nuke that out-trades your single-point Parrrley, and your lone Powder Keg is on a long cooldown and can be destroyed by the enemy before you ever detonate it. Don't walk into auto range to throw a Parrrley you'll just trade into his Q; last-hit from max distance and accept some chip. Hold Remove Scurvy (W) for his W root, not for poke — if he roots you and your cleanse is on cooldown, his full Q/E combo connects and you lose a huge chunk.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize: second points in Q and E let you Parrrley-detonate a keg for a chaining slow-AoE he has to walk through to CS, so you can finally contest the wave and zone his free Q farm. This is your first real window to push back — plant a barrel on his side and threaten the detonation so he can't freely step up. At 6, Cannon Barrage zones and helps a gank from across the map but doesn't win the straight duel, so don't flip the lane on R alone; keep stacking kegs and gold toward your Sheen spike.","late":"Your Sheen into Trinity Force spike is real — an empowered Parrrley into a full chained keg detonation bursts a pre-Tear Ryze if he steps up to CS, so force that window before his stacks come online. But be honest: he out-scales you. Once Ryze hits 2+ items and a stacked Tear/Archangel's, his W root sets up the Q/E burst chain that pins you, and his sustained ranged DPS melts you faster than your barrels can zone him. Close the game on your item spike or hand the lategame to your team — don't try to 1v1 a fully online Ryze.","whys":["His ranged Q out-pokes you while your single keg is on a long cooldown and can be destroyed before it detonates.","You're both weak here, but his Q still pokes for free at range — set up a keg safely and don't trade autos into it.","Your second Q/E points let you Parrrley-detonate a chaining keg AoE he has to walk through to CS, so you out-poke a melee-shy Ryze.","Sheen into Trinity Force empowers Parrrley, so a chained keg burst beats a pre-Tear Ryze who walks up to last-hit.","Cannon Barrage adds zone and dive pressure but doesn't win the solo duel, and his shield/W root answers your all-in — call it even.","Once his Tear stacks, his ranged poke and W-root combo out-trade you and your kegs can't close the gap — his scaling takes over.","Tear-stacked Ryze roots you with W and bursts with Q/E as a ranged raid boss faster than your kegs can zone him."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"sejuani","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Even and quiet — neither wants this stage. Last-hit at Parrrley range, and don't auto into her: every hit/Winter's Wrath stacks Frost toward her Permafrost (E) stun."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Second Q/E point lands Parrrley-into-keg poke she can't trade back — chip her down before she gets enough Frost stacks to threaten a Permafrost lockdown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her engage window: Arctic Assault (Q) knockup into Permafrost (E) stun, or a long-range Glacial Prison (R) spear to start a dive — but Remove Scurvy (W) cleanses the lockdown mid-commit and heals the burst."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen into the keg chain is your flip — empowered Parrrley plus a full barrel detonation out-damages anything a tank Sejuani can do back in a 1v1."}],"wants":{"you":["Land Parrrley-into-keg poke from level 4 so she's low before she ever connects an Arctic Assault knockup into a Permafrost stun","Hold Remove Scurvy to cleanse her Permafrost or Glacial Prison the instant she commits an engage, then heal the burst and barrel her back","Reach your Sheen keg-chain spike and scale — your barrels detonate from range where a slow tank can't reach you"],"foe":["Stack Frost with Winter's Wrath and autos, then land Permafrost (E) to lock you for a flat all-in or a jungle dive","Open with Arctic Assault (Q) knockup or a flank Glacial Prison (R) to start a fight and peel you off your barrels","Drag the game to teamfights where her AoE engage and Frost CC out-value your splitpush"]},"early":"Neither of us wants this stage, so don't force it. Sejuani has no waveclear and no reason to commit a level-1 — but I'm the weaker laner here, so I farm with the tip of Parrrley and keep my barrels placed where she can't free-hit them off cooldown. The thing to respect is her Frost: every Winter's Wrath and auto stacks me, and at four stacks her Permafrost (E) is a hard stun, so I don't sit in melee range feeding stacks. Quiet last-hitting wins this for me.","mid":"This is where I take the air out of the lane. With a second Q and E point I land Parrrley-into-keg from range — she has to walk up to farm and eats it, and once I start zoning with barrels she can only answer with Arctic Assault, which I can see coming. The whole matchup is her one engage: if she Q-knockups into Permafrost, or flanks with Glacial Prison to start a dive, I hold Remove Scurvy and cleanse the stun mid-commit, then heal the burst and detonate kegs back on her. Bait the engage, don't get baited by it.","late":"Once Sheen and the keg build come online I out-damage her flat in a 1v1 — empowered Parrrley plus a chained barrel detonation is more than a tank can answer, and I keep scaling from there. The honest risk isn't the duel, it's the map: Sejuani is built for teamfights, where Arctic Assault, Winter's Wrath Frost and a flank Glacial Prison let her lock down me and my carries. I keep Remove Scurvy for her engage, splitpush with global Cannon Barrage pressure, and never get caught alone after I've already spent W.","whys":["Even and dead — she won't commit level 1 and I'm too weak to force it, so I just last-hit with Parrrley and protect my barrels.","Still even; her autos and Winter's Wrath stack Frost toward a Permafrost stun, so I don't trade in melee range and keep poking with Q.","Neither of us spikes here — full kit isn't online yet, my barrels are still low-HP, and she has no kill pattern without Permafrost, so it stays a skill stage.","I get the edge: a second Q and E point means Parrrley-into-keg poke she can't trade back, and she can only close with a telegraphed Arctic Assault.","Even — her Q-knockup into Permafrost or a Glacial Prison dive is real, but Remove Scurvy cleanses the stun and heals the burst, so it's a wash.","My Sheen keg-chain spike out-damages a tank flat in a 1v1 — empowered Parrrley plus a full barrel detonation flips this in my favour.","I own the 1v1 with two items through chained kegs and global Cannon Barrage, but I respect her teamfight engage and never spend W early."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"sett","win":["Gangplank","Skill","Sett","Sett","Skill","Sett","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1","text":"You can poke Sett with Parrrley (Q) the instant he steps to last-hit — it applies on-hit and out-ranges everything he has, since his only ranged tool is the slow-charging tip of his Haymaker (W) and he can't farm at melee without eating shots."},{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Sett's threat window opens at 2 once he has W stored and E (Facebreaker) — he pulls you in, his passive Pit Grit fists chunk you on alternating autos, and his fully-charged W returns a chunk of the damage you've dealt as a true-damage cone you can't itemize against."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Sett's R (The Show Stopper) suppresses you, carries you, and slams for a percent-max-HP nuke that grows with his bonus health — and your W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses CC but cannot break a suppression, so respect the all-in once his E grab connects rather than trading into it."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Your keg combo flips the lane: pre-place Powder Kegs (E) and detonate them from range with Parrrley, and once you own Sheen plus a crit item the chained explosion plus empowered Q bursts Sett faster than his grit shield can refill — he has no ranged answer and no scaling to reach you."}],"wants":{"you":["Parrrley (Q) Sett every time he walks up to a minion and pre-place a Powder Keg (E) so you can detonate it from range the moment he commits a Facebreaker grab","Hold W (Remove Scurvy) for his E slow/peel, not his R — it cannot cleanse the suppression, so never sit at low HP within Facebreaker range when his R is up","Survive to Sheen plus a crit item, where a chained keg detonation and empowered Parrrley out-burst his grit shield no matter how much bonus HP he stacks"],"foe":["Land E (Facebreaker) to pull you in, then unload stored W (Haymaker) true damage while Pit Grit fists alternate-punch you before your kegs and Q are off cooldown","Win the short grit trades levels 2-5 — his sustain shield and high base damage beat your pre-Sheen autos while your kegs have long cooldowns","Hit level 6 and all-in with R (The Show Stopper) suppress-slam, which your Remove Scurvy can't break, to delete you before your keg burst comes online"]},"early":"Level 1 is genuinely yours — Sett has to walk into Parrrley (Q) range to last-hit, his Q applies on-hit and refunds gold/Silver Serpents on kills, and Sett's only ranged tool is the slow-charging tip of his Haymaker (W), so chip him every time he steps up. The catch comes at 2-3: once he has E (Facebreaker) and a stored W, he grabs you, returns your damage as a true-damage W cone, and stacks Pit Grit passive punches faster than your barrels come online. Pre-place a Powder Keg (E) and never stand where he can grab you onto a stacked keg setup — bait the grab, Parrrley the keg, and back off before he chains the smash.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are Sett's window and you have to respect it. He out-grits your short trades while your kegs still have long cooldowns and his sustain shield refills, and at 6 his R (The Show Stopper) is a suppress-slam, percent-max-HP all-in. Your W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses CC and heals off missing health, but it cannot break a suppression — so don't try to W out of his ult once it lands. Instead zone with kegs from range, only commit when his E grab is on cooldown, and use the keg slow to peel back when he engages.","late":"This flips hard once your items land. By 2+ items your Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a full chained Powder Keg detonation bursts Sett down despite his bulk — his grit shield and percent-HP R don't out-scale your keg burst, and you out-range every tool he has. Cannon Barrage (R) zones him off objectives and lets you split with impunity. Just don't gift him a fed early lead; if he snowballs off a level-2 or level-3 grab, his all-in stays lethal long enough to matter.","whys":["Sett must step into Parrrley (Q) range to farm and his only ranged answer is the slow-charging tip of his Haymaker (W), so you poke him for free at level 1.","Sett gets his second ability but still lacks the Facebreaker grab to lock you down — trades are even as you swap Q pokes for his developing W charge.","With E (Facebreaker) plus stored W online he grabs you, returns your damage as a true-damage W cone, and Pit Grit fists punch you while your barrels sit on cooldown.","Sett out-grits your short trades through 4-5 since his sustain shield refills and your kegs have long cooldowns before your Sheen spike.","His R (The Show Stopper) suppress-slam is a percent-max-HP all-in your W cannot cleanse, so the level-6 window belongs to whoever lands their setup first — a coin-flip on his E grab timing.","Sett's first-item grit spike beats your pre-Sheen barrels and his level-6 all-in still threatens you before your keg burst arrives.","By 2+ items your Sheen-empowered Parrrley and chained keg detonations out-burst his grit shield — he has zero ranged tool or scaling to reclaim the lane."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"shen","win":["Skill","Shen","Gangplank","Gangplank","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Shen's strongest window: with Twilight Assault (Q) empowering his autos he wins a pure auto-attack stand-up trade, and if he lands E taunt-dash before you have a keg placed you eat the full empowered combo. Don't melee him; keep poking from range."},{"when":"Lvl 4-6","text":"Tilts to you: with a barrel down you detonate it with Parrrley (Q) from range, and his Spirit's Refuge (W) only blocks basic attacks, not your Q-detonation, so it does almost nothing against your poke. Chip him for free while his taunt is the only real threat."},{"when":"Lvl 6 / 1st item","text":"Sheen plus your barrel chain spikes your burst hard, but respect Shen's Stand United (R): he can shield-dash to a fight across the map, so trade with Cannon Barrage pressure but expect him to leave lane and answer plays globally with his own."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your peak: a chained Powder Keg detonation plus empowered Parrrley out-bursts anything a tank Shen brings, and his W blocking basic attacks never stops a single Q-detonation. He scales as a teamfight peeler, you as a global splitpush threat."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 without getting taunted onto an empowered-Q combo, then start chunking him: place a barrel and pop it with Parrrley from outside his auto range","Remember his Spirit's Refuge (W) only blocks basic attacks — your keg detonations come from Parrrley (Q), so his block does nothing to your poke pattern","Hold Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse his E taunt rather than to heal poke, so you punish the long taunt cooldown instead of getting comboed"],"foe":["Empower his autos with Twilight Assault (Q) and win any level 1-3 melee stand-up trade before your kegs are set up","Land E taunt-dash to lock you in range of his empowered autos while you have no barrel placed to retaliate","Use Stand United (R) to roam or join fights cross-map, accepting an even lane and winning on map impact instead of dueling you"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Shen and you just survive them. Twilight Assault (Q) empowers his next autos, so he wins any melee stand-up trade before your kegs are online, and his E taunt-dash can yank you into that empowered combo if you over-extend. Crucially, do not try to fight him with basic attacks — last-hit and poke at max Parrrley range instead, because your damage comes from shooting kegs with Q, not from auto-attacking him. Never place a barrel he can simply walk up and pop with his own attack for free. Save Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse his taunt, not to heal early poke — eating the taunt with no answer is the only way you lose this lane outright.","mid":"Levels 4-6 swing toward you, and this is the part most people misplay. Once you have a barrel down, you detonate it with Parrrley (Q) from range — and Shen's Spirit's Refuge (W) only blocks basic attacks, so it does nothing to stop your Q-detonation poke. A tank Shen has no burst to punish you back, so chip him whenever you have a keg placed and only respect his E taunt window. At 6 his real threat isn't dueling you — it's Stand United, the global shield-dash that lets him answer a fight anywhere on the map, so use Cannon Barrage to zone and skirmish but assume he leaves lane to impact other lanes. Bank CS, keep barrels stocked, and the slight edge is yours.","late":"This is where you take over outright. Once Sheen and your barrel build come online, empowered Parrrley plus a full chained Powder Keg detonation bursts harder than anything a tank Shen can answer — and his Spirit's Refuge only ever blocks basic attacks, so it never eats a single Q-keg detonation. He trades evenly forever but can't threaten to kill you; his value shifts to peeling and ulting allies with Stand United while yours shifts to global splitpush with Cannon Barrage and chained kegs. Keep barrels placed before fights, kite his one E taunt, and let your scaling decide it — the lane is close but the late game is cleanly yours.","whys":["Q-poke costs nothing and refunds gold, but Shen has no level-1 commit either and you have no barrel down yet, so the opening exchanges are genuinely even.","Twilight Assault empowers Shen's autos and his E taunt can pull you into them before your first keg is placed — he wins the early melee stand-up trade.","Once you have a barrel down you detonate it with Parrrley from range, and his Spirit's Refuge blocks only basic attacks — not your Q-detonation — so your poke goes through for free.","A tank Shen has no burst to answer your keg poke, and his block whiffs against Q-detonation, so the level 4-6 chip war tilts to you.","Cannon Barrage zones but doesn't win a duel, and his global Stand United matches your map pressure — at 6 the broader game is a coin-flip.","Sheen plus a full barrel chain makes your empowered Parrrley out-burst anything the tank can soak, opening your favour window once items land.","Chained keg detonations out-scale a Shen whose W only ever blocks basic attacks and never your Q-detonation — you own the late game outright."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"singed","win":["Skill","Singed","Gangplank","Gangplank","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Singed's biggest window: he can Fling (E) you into his Poison Trail (Q) or proxy your wave behind tower while your Powder Kegs (E) are still on long cooldowns and you have no waveclear to punish back."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your second Parrrley (Q) and Powder Keg (E) points come online — set a keg at max range and Q-detonate it on him from outside Fling (E) range every time he walks up to last-hit, chipping faster than his Mega Adhesive zoning can stop you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen into your Powder Keg build flips the lane — Sheen-empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg slow-and-burst out-trades his drain-tank sustain, and Remove Scurvy (W) cleanses the Mega Adhesive (W) slow so he can't lock you for the Fling follow-up."},{"when":"Late","text":"Cannon Barrage (R) is your global answer to his proxy split — drop it on the side lane he's shoving and the artillery slow plus your team collapse out-races his move speed while you take the open objective on the far side."}],"wants":{"you":["Last-hit with Parrrley (Q) from max range so his Fling (E) never reaches you while your Powder Kegs (E) are on cooldown","Hit your level 4-5 Q-into-keg poke and detonate Powder Kegs (E) from outside Fling (E) range to out-chip his drain-tank sustain","Cleanse the Mega Adhesive (W) slow with Remove Scurvy (W) so he can't chain into a Fling, and answer his proxy splitpush with Cannon Barrage (R)"],"foe":["Fling (E) you into his Poison Trail (Q) or under his tower while your barrels are down and you have no waveclear","Proxy the wave behind your tower with Poison Trail (Q) to deny you CS and snowball off your weak early game","Build move speed and Rylai's so he runs you down through your slows and kites every keg you place"]},"early":"Singed's whole early plan is to Fling (E) you into his Poison Trail (Q) or proxy your wave, and Levels 1-3 are exactly when I'm weakest — my Powder Kegs (E) have long cooldowns, low HP he can free-hit to deny, and I have zero waveclear. Do not chase him; the second I walk up to trade he Flings me back into the trail and the poison ticks me down while he kites away on his move speed. Last-hit with Parrrley (Q) from range, respect that he wants me deep in the wave near his Mega Adhesive (W), and never facecheck for a Fling I can see coming.","mid":"This is where I take over. By Levels 4-5 my second Q and E points let me set a Powder Keg and Q-detonate it from OUTSIDE his Fling (E) range — every time he walks up to last-hit, the keg slows and bursts him and I chip faster than his drain-tank sustain heals it back. Level 6 Cannon Barrage isn't a duel-winner into his poison, so don't force a bad all-in, but it zones him off the wave and sets up my jungler. Play around his Mega Adhesive (W) — if he lands the slow to chain a Fling, Remove Scurvy (W) cleanses the slow and heals off my missing HP, then I keg-chain him while his cooldowns are down.","late":"Singed never duels me by 2+ items — chained Powder Keg detonations and Sheen-empowered Parrrley burst through any tank build he buys — but he stops trying to duel and just proxies, splitpushing a side lane I can't catch him in on his move speed. That's what Cannon Barrage (R) is for: I drop it on whichever lane he's shoving and the artillery slow plus my team's collapse out-races him while we take the free objective on the other side. Don't lane-chase a Singed with Rylai's and boots; trade the map, match his split or out-rotate it, and let my global ult tax every wave he tries to steal.","whys":["He has no kill pressure on me at level 1, but my barrels are weak and I have no waveclear either, so it's a wash — set the lane up and don't get Flung into the trail.","His Fling (E) into the Poison Trail (Q) is a real threat now while my Powder Kegs (E) are on long cooldowns and I can't punish back — this is his window.","My second Parrrley point lets me poke him from range and start chipping faster than his proxy farm pays off.","Q-into-keg detonations from outside his Fling (E) range out-chip his drain-tank sustain every time he walks up to the wave.","Cannon Barrage adds zoning but doesn't win the duel through his poison, so it stays even outside coordinated jungle plays.","Sheen empowers Parrrley and my keg chain bursts past his tank sustain, while Remove Scurvy cleanses his Mega Adhesive slow before he can chain a Fling.","He can't duel my keg burst, so he proxy-splits instead — Cannon Barrage taxes his side lane faster than his move speed can escape it."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"sion","win":["Sion","Sion","Sion","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Sion"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Sion's E (Roar of the Slayer) is a long-range shield-break that out-ranges your Parrrley, so he pokes you off the wave and can pop your kegs before they finish arming — his range owns the early setup."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage is your spike: it zones his slow, dash-less body off the wave and turns any gank into a kill since he has no escape from the sustained AoE."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen online (Sheen/Essence Reaver/Trinity) empowers Parrrley so a chained keg detonation finally bursts through his W shield in one window."},{"when":"Lvl 6+ (his R)","text":"Sion's ultimate (Unstoppable Onslaught) is a long charging knockup-stun from off-screen — combined with his Q windup it locks you for a tower dive when your W is down."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive his E poke with safe last-hits at max Parrrley range until level 4-5, then start chaining kegs once you have a second E charge","Cleanse his charged Q knockup (or his R) with W to heal and break the lock, then detonate a keg chain while his W shield is down","Use Cannon Barrage at 6 to zone his immobile body off the wave and convert any jungle gank into a kill he can't escape"],"foe":["Spam his long-range E to shield-break and poke you off the wave, denying kegs while your barrel cooldown is long","Full-charge Q for the knockup (or land his R charge) when your W is down to lock you for a tower dive or gank","Stack full tank and pop W to eat your keg chains, then scale into an unkillable frontline that survives your burst"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are Sion's. His E (Roar of the Slayer) is a long-range shield-break that out-ranges my Parrrley, so he pokes me off the wave and can pop my Powder Kegs before they finish arming while my barrel cooldown is still long. My short trades lose here, so I last-hit at max Parrrley range and refuse to walk into E range. The real threat is his charged Q knockup paired with his R: Unstoppable Onslaught is a long charging stun he can call from off-screen, and if my W is down he can lock me for his jungler. Respect both wind-ups and back off when I see the Q charging or hear his R.","mid":"Levels 4-5 I stabilize a bit — a second keg charge means I can poke with Parrrley-into-keg and make him walk into my barrels to farm, though his E range keeps it close. Level 6 is my window: Cannon Barrage zones his slow, dash-less body completely, and because he can't escape the AoE, any gank or skirmish inside my R becomes a kill. Bait his charged Q or R, cleanse it with W (which also heals my missing HP and lets my passive clear the lock), then detonate a keg chain while his W shield is down. Don't dump burst into a fresh W shield — it eats a huge chunk, so wait it out before committing the chain.","late":"First-item Sheen (or Essence Reaver / Trinity Force) is my best window — empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation finally bursts through his W shield, and his immobility means he can never dodge the explosion. But be honest: Sion builds full tank and scales into a near-unkillable frontline, so by 2+ items I can't delete him, only zone and kite. Cannon Barrage and global splits are my real value — never let his charged Q or R catch me in a teamfight, and aim chained kegs at his squishies instead of trying to chunk his health bar. Over the full game his tank scaling and lane range edge him ahead, which is why this sits as a slight loss for me.","whys":["Sion's E out-ranges my Parrrley and shield-breaks me, so he pokes me off the wave and pops kegs before they arm — I concede early and last-hit safe.","His charged Q knockup and off-screen R let him lock me while my barrels are on long cooldown and I have no waveclear to answer his poke.","He keeps zoning with E range and short trades go his way until I get a second keg charge — his early control owns levels 1-3.","I stabilize with Parrrley-into-keg poke and W to cleanse his Q/R, but his shield and E range keep mid-lane roughly even.","Cannon Barrage zones his slow, dash-less body off the wave and turns any gank into a kill he can't escape — level 6 is mine.","Sheen online lets empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg finally burst through his W shield in one window — my clearest kill threat.","He stacks full tank into an unkillable frontline that eats my kegs with W and out-scales me, so his range plus tankiness edge the lane."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"swain","win":["Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Swain's E (Nevermove) is a slow, telegraphed two-stage root — keep a Powder Keg between you so a landed root costs you a keg shove, not your health."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R (Demonic Ascension) heals him for AoE damage in extended fights — never sit in his drain field; W (Remove Scurvy) the E root that starts the combo and back off."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen into the keg build flips it — empowered Parrrley detonating a full barrel chain out-bursts his Demonic Ascension drain before it can heal through."},{"when":"Late","text":"Cannon Barrage zones his drain in a teamfight and chained keg detonations one-shot a squishy drain-mage — you out-carry a Swain who has to root before he does anything."}],"wants":{"you":["Sit at max Parrrley range and pre-place Powder Kegs so a landed Nevermove root only costs you a keg shove, not the trade","Hold W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse his E root and the slow, then heal back the Death's Hand poke","Scale to Sheen and the keg build where one empowered Parrrley detonates a full chain and bursts him out of Demonic Ascension"],"foe":["Land E (Nevermove) to root you, then dump W (Vision of Empire) and Death's Hand Q poke onto a stuck target","Drag you into an extended fight where R (Demonic Ascension) drains health and stacks Soul Fragments off you and your minions","Stack passive Soul Fragments off your wave so his Ravenous Flock healing out-sustains your barrel poke and snowballs the lane"]},"early":"Swain's whole early game is the E root (Nevermove) — it lands in two stages and flies slow, so sidestep it and his Vision of Empire W and Death's Hand Q poke have nothing to combo onto. Don't last-hit standing still in a straight line; he wants you rooted so he can dump everything. Keep a Powder Keg up between you so even if he catches the root, the worst case is you lose a keg shove, not the trade. His poke stings but he has zero kill pressure on you pre-6 if you respect that one ability and farm at Parrrley range.","mid":"This is where you take over. Parrrley-into-keg poke out-ranges his Death's Hand Q and chips him faster than his passive Soul Fragment healing restores, and the big one: your W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses his E root and the slow outright, so the combo that's supposed to lock you up just evaporates while you heal off missing health. Hold W for the root, not the poke. At 6 his R (Demonic Ascension) is a real threat in a drawn-out fight, so don't facecheck into the drain — poke, detonate, and back off rather than sitting in the AoE feeding him Soul Fragments.","late":"Once the keg build is online you own this. An empowered Parrrley detonating a full barrel chain bursts him out of Demonic Ascension before the drain can heal through it, and Cannon Barrage zones his drain so he can't freely stack Souls in a teamfight. He's a strong AoE scaler, but you out-carry his profile — chained kegs one-shot a squishy drain-mage and your global Cannon pressure beats his frontline-dependent fight. Just never get caught alone by a flank E root with your W and barrels down.","whys":["His E (Nevermove) is a slow two-stage telegraphed root and his only setup — at level 1 he just pokes, so sidestep it and last-hit at Parrrley range.","He wants the E-into-Vision-of-Empire combo, but with one barrel up a landed root only costs you a keg shove, not the trade.","Your second Q/E point lets you Parrrley-detonate kegs to poke him faster than his Soul Fragment healing restores.","Your W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses his Nevermove root and the slow, so the combo that should lock you up heals you off missing health instead.","Demonic Ascension makes extended AoE fights his — stay even by poking and backing off rather than sitting in his drain stacking Soul Fragments.","Sheen into kegs is your flip: one empowered Parrrley detonating a full chain out-bursts his drain before it can out-heal it.","Chained keg detonations one-shot a squishy drain-mage and Cannon Barrage zones his Soul-stacking — you out-carry his frontline-dependent fight."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"sylas","win":["Sylas","Sylas","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Sylas hard-shoves with Q (Chain Lash) then walks up to bully you off CS while your single Powder Keg has a long cooldown and can't threaten a detonation chain yet."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Putting points in E (Powder Keg) shortens its cooldown and lets you keep a keg up to zone him, so you can Parrrley-detonate for a chained slow whenever he steps in to drain."},{"when":"1st item (Sheen)","text":"Sheen turns every keg-detonated Parrrley into a burst hit; with Trial by Fire DoT stacked on top you out-trade his Q/W sustain in the keg zone."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R (Hijack) STEALS your Cannon Barrage, so if you ult first he gets a second global zone — hold R or force his cooldowns before you commit it."}],"wants":{"you":["Set up Powder Keg zones and Parrrley-detonate the chain so the slow lands before he can E-dash onto you to drain","W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse his E stun and heal back the Q/W damage in the middle of a trade","Avoid ulting first — hold Cannon Barrage or bait his cooldowns so his R can't Hijack a second global off you"],"foe":["Q (Chain Lash) you for AoE poke and W-heal it back, sustaining through your early keg cooldowns","E-dash in, land the chain stun, and drain you with Q/W before your keg setup is online","Hijack your Cannon Barrage with R in the teamfight to copy your global zone"]},"early":"Sylas owns the first three levels — he hard-shoves with Q (Chain Lash), heals it back with W, and walks up to bully you off CS while my single Powder Keg sits on a long cooldown and can't threaten a detonation chain yet. Don't try to fight in the keg zone at level 1; if I overstep he E-dashes onto me, lands the stun, and drains me out with Q/W. Farm with the tip of Parrrley, hold W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse his E stun rather than burning it on poke, and concede this window.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are where I stabilize — extra points in E (Powder Keg) shorten its cooldown so I can keep a keg standing to zone him and Parrrley-detonate the chain whenever he walks up to drain. At 6 it's even and dangerous: my Cannon Barrage adds map pressure, but his R (Hijack) steals it outright, so I never ult first into him. Bait his E stun, W-cleanse it, then punish the window while his dash is down.","late":"This stays close into the late game, but it tilts my way once Sheen comes online — keg-detonated Parrrley hits for a burst, and with Trial by Fire DoT stacked on top I out-trade his Q/W sustain inside the keg zone. The danger never leaves: every fight where I drop Cannon Barrage, he can Hijack it for a second global, so coordinate ult timing and make him burn his R reactively. Out-trade him in the keg zone, respect the stolen ult.","whys":["His Q (Chain Lash) shoves and pokes, W heals it back, and my lone early keg is on too long a cooldown to punish him.","He E-dashes onto me, stuns, and drains with Q/W before my keg zone is set up to threaten a detonation.","It's close once I get a second E point, but he still out-sustains short trades with W — I farm and hold cleanse.","My extra E points shorten the keg cooldown so I can zone him and Parrrley-detonate the chain as he walks up.","My Cannon Barrage adds zone pressure but his R Hijacks it, so neither of us wins the duel outright at 6.","Sheen plus Trial by Fire on a keg-detonated Parrrley out-trades his Q/W sustain inside the keg zone.","I out-scale through chained kegs and Sheen burst, beating his drain in a sustained fight once I'm itemized."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"tahmkench","win":["Tahm Kench","Tahm Kench","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Tahm Kench's window: he stacks his An Acquired Taste passive (3 marks = a stun) with autos and Q, then Devours (W) for percent-HP burst. He can flash onto you, land the stun, and W you toward his turret before your kegs have HP or a short cooldown to answer."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Parrrley-into-Powder-Keg poke comes online: place a keg, Q-detonate it for the chaining slow-AoE, and chunk him from range. His grey-health and Devour only matter if he walks up, and you never do."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver into the keg build: an empowered Parrrley plus a full chained keg detonation bursts through his grey-health faster than his passive can heal it back. This is your power flip."},{"when":"Late","text":"By 2+ items chained keg explosions delete him before grey-health regenerates, but respect his R, Abyssal Voyage, a long-range channeled teleport he uses to roam or save allies. Shove and Cannon Barrage cross-map the second he leaves lane."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 without eating his An Acquired Taste stun into a Devour all-in or tower dive, farming with Parrrley at range while his marks are off your bar","Reach your Parrrley-into-keg poke at 4-5 and burst his grey-health faster than it heals back with chained detonations he can't trade into","Scale to the first-item keg spike and beat his Abyssal Voyage roams by shoving and matching cross-map with global Cannon Barrage"],"foe":["Stack his passive to 3 marks for the stun, then Devour you for percent-HP burst to all-in or carry you under his turret for a dive","Build pure HP so grey-health and percent-HP Devour out-sustain your early keg poke through any extended trade","Use Abyssal Voyage to leave an even lane and snowball elsewhere, since he can't win the straight scaling 1v1 into your kegs"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to him and you know it: your barrels have long cooldowns and low base HP that he can free-hit to deny, and once he stacks his An Acquired Taste passive to 3 marks the stun lets him Devour (W) you for percent-HP burst, even flashing you toward his turret for a dive before you have a keg up to peel. Do not walk up to last-hit inside his range while he has marks on you; farm with Parrrley (Q) at max range and accept the CS you miss. His grey-health passive means short trades just feed his sustain, so don't poke into a fight you can't burst out. The one thing to dodge above all is the 3-stack stun into Devour, because that combo is his entire kill threat this lane.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are where you stabilize and pull even, then 6 starts handing you the lane. With a second Q and an E point you land Parrrley-into-keg poke: drop a Powder Keg, Q-detonate it for the chaining slow-AoE, and chunk him from a range his percent-HP Devour can never answer because you never step in. The trick versus his grey-health is that your barrels are burst, not sustained DPS: a clean chained detonation removes a chunk faster than the passive heals it, whereas trickling autos just let it refill. Cannon Barrage (R) at 6 adds zoning and dive pressure but won't duel-win on its own here, so use it to set up a keg burst or deny an Abyssal Voyage roam rather than as a standalone all-in.","late":"This is yours outright: Tahm Kench is a utility drain-tank, not a scaling carry, and your chained keg detonations off an empowered Parrrley delete him through grey-health before the passive matters once you hit two items. He has no way to win the straight 1v1, so his only out is leaving lane: respect his R, Abyssal Voyage, the long-range channeled teleport he uses to roam, and the Devour he can still use to peel or relocate teammates. Shove the wave and match his cross-map pressure with your own global Cannon Barrage, collapse the instant he channels away, and never let a fed lead slip by facechecking into a 3-stack stun. Close side lanes fast: your barrels 1v9, while his kit only enables others.","whys":["He owns level 1: your kegs have long cooldowns and low HP he can free-hit to deny, and once his An Acquired Taste stacks to 3 marks the stun beats any short trade you can make.","His early power spike is real: a 3-mark stun into Devour (W) deals percent-HP and can flash you under his tower for a dive before your single keg can peel it.","By level 3 you can start poking with Parrrley but his grey-health heals back through trickle damage, so it's even until your keg combo lands. Play it as Skill.","With a second Q and an E you Q-detonate a Powder Keg for chaining slow-AoE poke from range, chunking him faster than his percent-HP Devour can punish you back.","Cannon Barrage adds zoning and dive setup, and your keg poke now out-damages his grey-health sustain, so you control the lane even though R isn't a duel-winner alone.","Sheen/Essence Reaver plus a full chained keg detonation bursts through his grey-health faster than the passive heals it, and he can't trade back into your range. This is the flip.","Two items in, chained keg explosions delete him before grey-health matters and he has no 1v1 answer; only respect his Abyssal Voyage roam and shove to match it."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"teemo","win":["Teemo","Teemo","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Teemo's Blinding Dart (Q) makes your next Parrrley and autos miss, so he free-hits your low-HP kegs and chips you with poison — his strongest window before your barrel chain is online."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"A second point in Powder Keg (E) lets you place a barrel out of his Q range and detonate it with Parrrley from afar — poke his passive move speed can't kite cleanly."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen empowers your Parrrley keg-pops, so a barrel chain bursts him through his poison faster than he can blind-and-kite away."},{"when":"Late","text":"Chained keg detonations plus a Cannon Barrage (R) dropped on his escape path own the 1v1 — but clear his Noxious Trap shrooms before pathing through brush near objectives."}],"wants":{"you":["Place Powder Keg (E) outside his Blinding Dart range and pop it with Parrrley for un-kiteable, barrel-amplified poke","Reach your Sheen first-item spike so empowered Parrrley keg-pops burst him faster than his poison out-trades","Cleanse his poison and heal off missing HP with Remove Scurvy (W), then re-commit on your barrel cooldown"],"foe":["Blind your Parrrley and autos (Q) every time you step up, denying your keg detonations and your CS","Kite with passive move speed and stack Toxic Shot (E) poison on you before your barrel chain is up","Plant Noxious Trap shrooms (R) on chokes and objectives, then splitpush and stall the lane into his scaling"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are Teemo's. Blinding Dart (Q) makes your next Parrrley and autos miss, so he can free-hit your low-HP kegs to deny them and chip you with poison while your barrels sit on long cooldowns — you have no answer to his poke yet. Don't throw a Parrrley he can just blind, and don't place a keg he'll walk up and pop. Last-hit at max Parrrley range, eat a little poison, and cleanse the worst of it with Remove Scurvy (W) when your missing-HP heal is worth it. His chip can't kill through your W sustain — just deny him a snowball.","mid":"This is where it turns. At 4-5 a second point in Powder Keg (E) lets you place a barrel outside his Blinding Dart range and detonate it with Parrrley — un-kiteable poke he can't fully escape, since his only mobility is passive move speed and he has no dash. Bait the Q blind on a throwaway auto, then commit your Parrrley-into-keg chain. At 6 Cannon Barrage (R) adds zone control — drop it on his retreat path or use it to set up a jungle dive on his flank.","late":"Your Sheen first-item spike makes empowered Parrrley plus a full barrel chain burst him, and from 2+ items chained keg detonations plus global Cannon Barrage own the straight 1v1 and zone him off every objective. The catch is map-wide: Teemo answers with Noxious Trap shrooms and splitpush, so never facecheck brush near drake or baron and clear his shrooms off chokes before you path through. Press your lead into towers so his scaling and vision game never get the chance to matter.","whys":["His Blinding Dart (Q) makes your Parrrley and autos miss while your barrels sit on long cooldowns — you can only farm and soak poison here.","He free-hits your low-HP kegs to deny them and chips you with Toxic Shot (E) poison before you have any answer — concede the trade.","You get a second E point but he can still blind your detonation auto and kite the barrel with passive move speed — roughly even now.","A keg placed outside Q range and popped by Parrrley finally gives you poke his passive move speed can't kite — you take over.","Cannon Barrage (R) dropped on his retreat cuts off the kite — he has no dash to escape a keg chain into the bombardment.","Sheen empowers your Parrrley so a keg-into-Q chain bursts him faster than his poison can out-trade.","Chained keg explosions plus global Cannon Barrage own the duel and zone him off objectives — just clear his shrooms in brush first."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"trundle","win":["Trundle","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Trundle's only window — his Chomp (Q) steals your AD on every walk-up and Frozen Domain (W) gives him the speed to chase you off the wave, so last-hit with Parrrley and don't auto-trade into him."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your second E point comes online: drop a Powder Keg at max range and detonate it with Parrrley to poke him through the slow from outside Chomp range — the first stage you actually win."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen (Sheen/Essence Reaver/Trinity) online — empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation chunks him faster than his Q drain heals and pushes the lane clearly FAVOURED."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Subjugate (R) steals your armor/MR and heals him in a point-blank all-in — never get walked into Pillar of Ice (E) and dueled when his ult is up; keg him from range instead."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 last-hitting with Parrrley (Q) from range so you never feed his Chomp the AD-steal trade","Hit your Sheen-line spike and chain Powder Keg detonations to burst him faster than his Q/R drain can heal","Fight at max range and use Cannon Barrage to zone — Trundle's whole drain-tank kit does nothing if he can't reach you"],"foe":["Land Chomp (Q) to steal your AD and win the short trade whenever you step up to last-hit early","Catch you with Pillar of Ice (E), pop Frozen Domain (W) speed, and Subjugate (R) to drain-tank the all-in","Walk up and break your low-HP Powder Kegs with autos to deny the poke before it chains"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Trundle, full stop — his Chomp (Q) steals a chunk of your attack damage every time you walk up to last-hit, and Frozen Domain (W) gives him the move-speed to chase you off the wave while your Powder Kegs are still on a long cooldown and have little enough HP that he can just auto them down. Don't try to trade autos here; you lose the AD-steal exchange flat. Last-hit with the tip of Parrrley (Q), keep one keg back for spacing only, and never let him drop Pillar of Ice (E) on you against your tower while his Chomp is up.","mid":"This is where it turns. At 4-5 your second Powder Keg charge lets you place a barrel at range and detonate it with Parrrley for the slow before he ever bites you — poke him while he walks through it, because his only sustain answer is drain-tanking and you're not feeding him autos to drain off. Respect his level 6: Subjugate (R) steals your armor and magic resist and heals him through a brawl, so don't duel on top of his Pillar of Ice when his ult is up. Bait the pillar, step around the terrain, then keg-chain him from the side.","late":"You own the late game cleanly — Trundle is a drain-tank duelist, not a scaling carry, so he never reclaims a window the way a Vlad or Kayle would. Once you have two items your chained Powder Keg detonations and empowered Parrrley burst faster than his Chomp drain and Subjugate resist-steal can heal back, and you can shove and Cannon Barrage him off a sidelane or zone him out of a fight entirely. Just keep fighting at range and never get cornered where Frozen Domain speed lets him close — Trundle's whole kit is built on reaching you, and at distance it does nothing.","whys":["Trundle's Chomp (Q) steals your attack damage on every level-1 walk-up while your kegs aren't charged yet — you lose the early auto trade flat.","Roughly even at 2-3: his bite-and-chase pressure with Frozen Domain (W) is real, but you can last-hit safely with Parrrley instead of contesting, so it's spacing-on-spacing.","Your second Powder Keg charge lets you detonate a keg with Parrrley from outside Chomp range, poking him through the slow while he can't AD-steal you.","Max-range Parrrley-into-keg poke chips him faster than his drain sustains, and you control whether he ever gets to reach you — the lane tilts your way.","About even at 6: Cannon Barrage adds zone and dive pressure, but Subjugate (R) drain-tanks a committed all-in, so don't gift him the bite-plus-ult brawl.","Sheen-line empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation bursts him faster than his Q drain and R heal can recover — the spike flips it clearly to you.","You out-scale a drain-tank outright: chained keg detonations and global Cannon Barrage pressure beat his resist-steal, and at range his whole drain kit is dead."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"tryndamere","win":["Tryndamere","Gangplank","Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Tryndamere free-hits your Powder Kegs to pop them before they arm, then E-dashes in and out-DPSes your autos with crit-charged spin while you have no waveclear or barrel poke yet."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage is your one real swing — drop it on yourself to break his spin all-in, deny his tower dive, and zone him off the wave instead of dueling his Fury-fed autos raw."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver finally makes empowered Parrrley-into-keg-chain burst, but dump a full barrel combo into his Undying Rage and he just spin-kites for 5 seconds at min HP and walks away."},{"when":"Late","text":"His crit spin-kite, E reposition and R reset let him survive your keg detonations and splitpush; you win through global Cannon Barrage pressure and teamfight zoning, not a 1v1."}],"wants":{"you":["Hold W (Remove Scurvy) for the exact moment he Mocking-Shout slows you for a spin combo — cleanse the slow and heal the spin chunk","Place kegs behind you or against a wall so he can't walk up and free-hit them before you arm and Parrrley-detonate","Save Cannon Barrage to break his level-6 spin all-in and deny his tower dives rather than spending it for poke"],"foe":["Pop your barrels early with a free auto or spin pass so your keg poke and Parrrley burst never come online","E gap-close into Mocking Shout slow to stick on you and spin you down before your Remove Scurvy is back up","Bait your full keg-chain combo into Undying Rage, ride out the 5 seconds at min HP, and reset the duel on you"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are his. You have no waveclear and your barrels arm slowly on long cooldowns, so he simply walks up and free-hits a keg to pop it before you ever land the Parrrley detonation. Don't try to trade through his spin — a Fury-charged Tryndamere out-DPSes your autos, and his E (Spinning Slash) gap-close means you can't poke and run. Hold W (Remove Scurvy) for when he commits E into a Mocking Shout slow; cleansing the slow and healing the spin chunk is your only real out this early. Farm with the tip of Parrrley and concede some CS rather than feeding an early kill.","mid":"Levels 4-5 stabilize as extra E points let you place a keg behind you and threaten Parrrley-into-keg poke before he closes — keep the barrel out of his auto range so he can't pop it for free. At 6, Cannon Barrage is your real swing: drop it on yourself to break his spin engage, deny his tower dive, or zone him off the wave. Don't dump a full keg chain into him while Undying Rage is up — he can't drop below minimum HP for 5 seconds and spin-kites away with the whole combo wasted. Bait the R, then burst the window the instant it ends.","late":"By two items you're a scaling carry, but so is he — and his crit spin-kite plus E reposition and Mocking Shout slow let him chase you through your barrels while Undying Rage hard-counters every burst window you set up. This is not a lane you win by out-dueling him 1v1 late; he splitpushes and survives everything you detonate. Lean on global Cannon Barrage to pressure other lanes and objectives, save your chained keg detonations for teamfights where he can't simply spin away, and let your team body-block his dive. You out-zone five people, not one immortal spin.","whys":["Tryndamere free-hits your slow-arming keg to deny it and out-trades your autos with Fury-charged crit spin before you have any waveclear.","Level 6 Cannon Barrage is Gangplank's one window of control — drop it on yourself to break his spin all-in, deny the tower dive, and zone him off the wave.","His E (Spinning Slash) gap-close lets him jump you the instant you step up to farm, and your barrels can't punish him yet.","Extra E points let you poke with safe Parrrley-into-keg and W cleanses his Mocking Shout slow — neither of you clearly owns the level 4-5 window.","Undying Rage hands him 5 seconds at minimum HP, so even a Sheen-empowered keg-chain burst gets spin-kited and reset rather than killing him.","He out-sustains your detonations with crit spin-kite and resets the duel with R, so he wins the prolonged late 1v1 you'd need to punish him.","Cannon Barrage's global pressure and teamfight zoning vs his splitpush is decided by which player reads the map better, not the lane itself."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"urgot","win":["Urgot","Urgot","Urgot","Skill","Gangplank","Skill","Urgot"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Urgot's Q (Corrosive Charge) is a long-range physical-damage shockwave that out-ranges your Parrrley and free-pokes you and your fresh barrels off the wave — his strongest window before you can build a keg chain."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage zones his W-shotgun walk-up and answers a dive; his R only executes you below the threshold and needs the E-flip first, so artillery + a keg detonation is your one clean stage to flip a trade."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver plus a chained keg detonation lets you finally burst back, but his W (Purge) shreds you with rapid shots while shielding him, so trades land even rather than in your favor."},{"when":"Late","text":"Chained kegs out-DPS most bruiser-tanks, but Urgot's E-flip into R can suppress-execute you the instant you drop low — never commit without a Powder Keg up to burst and slow before he closes the gap."}],"wants":{"you":["Last-hit with Parrrley at max range where Urgot's Q is the only thing that reaches you, and rebuild kegs only when he steps up to CS so he can't free-pop them","Hit Level 6 and use Cannon Barrage to zone his W walk-up and deny the E-flip all-in, saving Remove Scurvy for the flip-stun and his R window","Scale to a chained keg detonation with Sheen so you can burst him before his percent-HP W shotgun grinds you down"],"foe":["Land long-range Q shockwaves to chip you and your barrels from outside Parrrley range while you have no waveclear answer","Catch you with the E (Disdain) flip-stun to drag you in and open his W shotgun-knee DPS dump","Drop you below his R (Fear Beyond Death) execute threshold so any lost trade becomes a guaranteed suppress-kill"]},"early":"Urgot owns these levels and you have to respect it. His Q (Corrosive Charge) is a long-range physical-damage shockwave that reaches past your Parrrley, so he can chip you and detonate-deny your fresh barrels off the wave before they ever come online. Last-hit at max Q range, place kegs only when he steps up to CS so he can't free-pop them, and stay off the center of the wave where his E (Disdain) can flip-stun you into W (Purge) shotgun-knee range. Hold Remove Scurvy — it cleanses the flip-stun and heals — but don't waste it early; you want it for his level-6 commit.","mid":"At 6 you finally get a window: Cannon Barrage lets you zone his W walk-up and punish a dive, since his kill pattern needs an E-flip to land before his shotgun knees can dump damage, and his R only executes you once you're already below the threshold. Drop Barrage on his approach when he commits, cleanse the flip with W, and Parrrley-detonate a keg to slow and peel out. Don't straight-duel him — Purge out-sustains your poke until your first item — so use the ult to deny the all-in and keep farming, not to force a fight his W shield wins.","late":"Once your keg build comes online a full chained detonation out-DPSes him, but Urgot is the wrong bruiser-tank to face carelessly — his W (Purge) scales partly off your max HP so stacking armor doesn't fully save you, and an E-flip into R will suppress-execute you the instant you drop low with a barrel on cooldown. Always keep a Powder Keg up before you engage so you can burst and slow before he closes; if your kegs are down, kite with Parrrley poke and let Cannon Barrage zone him off objectives rather than feeding his shotgun knees a sustained fight.","whys":["Urgot's long-range Q shockwave out-ranges your Parrrley and lets him chip you and free-detonate your barrels off the wave before they come online.","He keeps poking with Q while you still have no waveclear and your kegs sit on long cooldowns, so the lane stays his to dictate.","His W shotgun-knee sustain out-trades anything you throw pre-item, and a single E-flip drags you into a fight you can't win yet.","It's roughly even here — a second keg point helps you poke, but his Q range and flip threat still trade in his favor before items, so call it skill on detonation timing.","Cannon Barrage zones his W walk-up and answers the E-flip dive — your one clean stage, since his entire all-in needs to physically reach you first.","With Sheen and a keg chain online both sides can burst, so the trade outcome comes down to whether you land the detonation before his W shield soaks it.","Chained kegs out-DPS most tanks, but his max-HP W shotgun and R suppress-execute keep tipping it his way the moment a barrel is on cooldown."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"vayne","win":["Vayne","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Vayne's window. Her Tumble (Q) repositions for a free auto and her Silver Bolts (W) third-hit chunks you before any barrels are placed, so eat minimal autos and never walk up to trade."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your Parrrley-into-keg (Q+E) poke comes online: detonate a barrel on her from outside auto range and she has zero sustain to heal the chunk back."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Sheen-item Parrrley (Trinity/Essence Reaver) plus a chained keg detonation bursts a squishy Vayne who only has Tumble (Q) as an escape — force the all-in when it's down."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Vayne's threat window. Silver Bolts (W) percent-max-HP true damage plus Condemn (E) stunning you against a wall let her kite your kegs and out-DPS you no matter how tanky you build."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 with full barrel charges, then start landing Parrrley-into-keg (Q+E) poke from outside her auto range","Hit your first Sheen item (Trinity/Essence Reaver) and all-in when her Tumble (Q) escape is on cooldown","Use Cannon Barrage (R) to zone her off the wave and set up jungle dives before she reaches two items"],"foe":["Free-hit your freshly-placed kegs and stack Silver Bolts (W) on you with safe autos before level 4","Tumble (Q) to dodge your keg detonations and reset her auto rhythm, kiting back the moment you commit","Reach 2+ items so her percent-HP true damage and a Condemn (E) wall-stun let her kite and out-duel you"]},"early":"Vayne owns the first few levels and you have to respect it. Her Tumble (Q) sets up a free auto and her Silver Bolts (W) third hit chunks you, and worse, she can shoot your Powder Kegs (E) to pop them before they're armed since fresh barrels have low HP. Don't place kegs where she can free-hit them, stay out of her auto range, and last-hit with the tip of Parrrley (Q) when melee isn't safe. You have no real trade pattern until you stack ability points, so just survive and keep your barrel charges banked.","mid":"This is where you flip it. With more points in Q and E you can land Parrrley-into-keg (Q+E) — detonate a barrel on her from range for the slow plus burst, and she has no sustain to heal that poke off. She has to walk up to farm, so punish every CS attempt. At 6, Cannon Barrage (R) lets you zone her off the wave and set up your jungler for a dive, since her only escape is Tumble (Q) and she dies fast if caught out of position.","late":"Be honest with yourself: Vayne reclaims the game if it goes long. Her Silver Bolts (W) deal percent-max-HP true damage that shreds you no matter how tanky you build, and her Condemn (E) knocks you into a wall for a stun the moment you try to chain kegs on her. Make the late game never matter — snowball your first-item lead, take towers and grubs with Cannon Barrage (R), and end before she has two items. If a fight breaks out at 3 items, don't dive her: let your team peel and use your global R to apply pressure in another part of the map.","whys":["Vayne's Tumble (Q) auto plus Silver Bolts (W) third-hit out-trades your level-1 with no kegs online, and she can free-hit your barrels to deny them.","You stabilize slightly as you bank ability points, but you still have no answer to her ranged auto-poke, so it stays a coin-flip on her aggression.","Your second points in Q and E bring Parrrley-into-keg (Q+E) poke online from range, and she has no sustain to heal the chunk off.","Your keg-chain poke now out-damages her auto harass and forces her to walk into a wave you control.","Cannon Barrage (R) adds zoning and dive setup, and her only escape is Tumble (Q), so a coordinated play kills her.","Your Sheen item (Trinity/Essence Reaver) turns an empowered Parrrley plus a chained keg detonation into a one-combo burst on a squishy Vayne.","She out-scales hard: Silver Bolts (W) true damage and a Condemn (E) wall-stun let her kite your kegs and out-DPS you, so close the game before this window."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"vladimir","win":["Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Skill","Gangplank","Vladimir"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Vlad trades HP (not mana) to cast, so every Parrrley plus keg detonation chips a health bar he is also burning himself to last-hit with — pre-pool he has no way to disengage your poke."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen or Essence Reaver makes your empowered Parrrley detonate a barrel chain for real burst — this all-in lands before Vlad's Rylai's/Riftmaker come online and is your cleanest kill window."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage chunks him and denies a free recall, but Sanguine Pool can ride out the worst of it untargetable — use R to deny CS/recall or set up your jungler, not as a solo execute."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"With Rylai's and Riftmaker online Vlad pools your keg detonation, drains the chip back with Transfusion, and his slow kites your barrels — the lane flips to him here."}],"wants":{"you":["Place Powder Kegs behind your minions and pop them with Parrrley so he eats the chip every time he steps up to last-hit, and can't free-hit the barrels to deny them","Reach your first-item Sheen/Essence Reaver spike and force the all-in while his Sanguine Pool is on its long cooldown and before his AP items land","Exploit that he trades his own HP to cast — stack Parrrley + keg poke so his Transfusion sustain can't keep pace before he scales"],"foe":["Use Sanguine Pool (W) to go untargetable through your keg detonation and Cannon Barrage, then drain the trade back to even with Transfusion","Farm safely, take HP-cost trades only when winning, and stack AP items toward his unkillable late-game power spike","Survive your first-item all-in window untouched so his Rylai's + Riftmaker hyperscaling outpaces your barrel burst"]},"early":"Vlad is a famously weak laning phase: he pays health (not mana) for every Q (Transfusion) and E (Tides of Blood), and he has zero escape until Sanguine Pool at 6. You don't have to win a raw poke war — you have to punish the HP he's already spending. Place Powder Kegs behind your minion line and detonate them with Parrrley every time he walks up to last-hit, so your chip stacks on a health bar he's also draining himself to farm. Don't let him free-auto your kegs to pop them early — space them where his E can't reach. His Transfusion sustain is real, but it can't out-heal repeated Q + keg detonations layered on his own HP costs.","mid":"This is your window. With a second point in Parrrley and Powder Keg your detonation poke out-damages a pre-Rylai's Vlad, and once you hit Sheen or Essence Reaver an empowered Parrrley plus a full barrel chain genuinely bursts him. Bait the Sanguine Pool — once he blows W to go untargetable through a detonation it's on a long cooldown, so re-engage immediately with a fresh keg chain and drop Cannon Barrage on top. Force the all-in here, before his Rylai's and Riftmaker flip the lane out of your hands.","late":"Once Vlad has two AP items the lane inverts and you cannot win the straight 1v1. He pools through your keg detonation untargetable, drains the chip back with Transfusion, and his Rylai's slow lets him kite your barrels while Riftmaker burst eats you. Don't chain your kegs into him while he can just W out — you'll waste your whole detonation on an untargetable champ and lose the cooldown war. Take your scaling to a sidelane, use global Cannon Barrage to pressure other lanes and objectives, and let your team peel him; never trade your keg cooldowns straight into a full-AP Vlad who out-drains you.","whys":["Vlad has one of the weakest laning phases and so do you — the lane opens even, so deny his last-hits and lock in your keg spacing first.","Vlad pays HP (not mana) to cast, so your Parrrley + keg poke out-trades his Transfusion before he has the bars to absorb it.","He has no Sanguine Pool escape until 6, so a keg chain detonated with Parrrley chips him for free every time he steps up to farm.","You out-trade a pre-Rylai's Vlad — bait the pool, then re-engage with a fresh barrel chain while his W is on its long cooldown.","Cannon Barrage chunks and zones but Sanguine Pool rides out the worst untargetable — it's even outside a jungler collapse or a baited pool.","Your Sheen/Essence Reaver keg-burst spike out-paces his first AP item — this is your last clean all-in window, so take it.","He out-scales hard: a 2-item Vlad pools your detonation, drains it back, and kites your barrels with Rylai's — play safe and let your team handle him."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"volibear","win":["Skill","Volibear","Volibear","Gangplank","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Volibear's biggest window: empowered-Q (Thundering Smash) dash-in plus its stun and his W bite blow you up before your Powder Kegs are online, so hug the wave and never step into auto range to throw a Parrrley."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Second Powder Keg (E) and Parrrley point come online, so you start landing Q-into-keg poke from outside his Q dash range, flipping the lane back to you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver into your keg build is the peak: empowered Parrrley plus a chained barrel detonation bursts a Volibear who has to walk through the keg slow to reach you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Hold Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse his Q stun mid-engage and heal the W-bite damage, then keg-poke him off before his R leap (tower-disable + shield) can set up a dive."}],"wants":{"you":["Land Parrrley-into-keg chains from max range so he eats the slow before his Q dash can close the gap","Hold Remove Scurvy (W) to cleanse his Q stun and heal his W bite, denying his all-in","Survive his level 2-3 dive window, then take over from first item onward with empowered Parrrley plus chained keg bursts"],"foe":["Hit his level 2-3 spike: empowered-Q dash-in with the stun and W bite before your kegs are online","Bait or eat your W early so his Q stun lands clean on the follow-up all-in","Brawl on top of you inside the wave where your kegs can't be detonated at safe range, sustaining through trades with W bite"]},"early":"Volibear's early is genuinely scary for you here: at 2-3 his empowered Q (Thundering Smash) dashes in and stuns, and his W bite chunks plus heals him before a single Powder Keg is set. Your barrels have long cooldowns and low HP, so he can walk up and free-hit one to deny it. Don't place kegs aggressively where he can pop them by walking through, and don't step into Q-dash range to throw a Parrrley. Last-hit from the back, accept some poke, and respect that his W bite heals him so short trades go his way. Hold W (Remove Scurvy) for his Q stun, not for poke.","mid":"This is where it flips to me. Once I have a second Powder Keg (E) and Parrrley point I start landing Q-into-keg poke from outside his Q dash range, and a Volibear whose dash is on cooldown has to eat the keg slow to reach me. At 6 I use Cannon Barrage (R) to zone the all-in, but the real edge is W: I cleanse his Q stun the instant he dashes onto me, heal the bite, and walk away from a blown engage. Bait the dash, keg-poke on its cooldown, and never trade into a fresh empowered Q.","late":"I own this long-term. Volibear scales as a diving bruiser-tank, but he has no answer to a full keg chain — chained Powder Keg detonations and empowered Parrrley burst him through his bulk, and my W cleanses the one piece of hard CC (his Q stun) he brings to a fight. His R leap disables a tower and shields him for the dive, so don't get caught alone under turret, but in a straight side-lane 1v1 my barrels and global Cannon Barrage pressure beat his all-in every time. Close it out before he stacks six items of tank stats and just chunks through me.","whys":["You are both weak at level 1, but his W bite out-sustains your auto poke in a short trade, so it is a coin-flip you should not start.","Volibear hits his dive spike first: empowered-Q dash plus its stun lands before your kegs are online and he heals the trade with W bite.","Still his window — your kegs have long cooldowns and low HP he free-hits to deny, and his Q-dash all-in beats you while you have no real waveclear.","Second keg and Parrrley point let you Q-into-keg from outside his dash range, so a dashless Volibear eats the slow before he reaches you.","Level 6 is roughly even — his R leap disables a tower and shields the dive, but your Cannon Barrage zones it, so neither ult wins the straight duel outright.","Sheen/Essence Reaver empowers Parrrley and your chained barrel burst starts melting him through his tank stats — force every trade here.","Chained keg detonations burst him faster than he scales, and W cleanses his only hard CC (the Q stun) — just avoid dying under his R-disabled tower."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"warwick","win":["Warwick","Warwick","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Warwick's window — his Eternal Hunger passive heals extra when you're under half HP, his Q heals off your max HP, and a fresh keg sits at low durability he can free-hit to deny it, so any walk-up out-sustains your Parrrley chip."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Infinite Duress (R) suppresses you in place — but Remove Scurvy (W) cleanses the suppression mid-channel and heals off your missing HP, so holding W for his ult, not wasting it earlier, is the single play that decides his all-in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen into the keg build is your flip — an empowered Parrrley detonating a chained barrel finally bursts faster than his drain heals, opening your favour window before he can itemize sustain."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-scale outright — chained keg explosions plus global Cannon Barrage delete a Warwick whose drain stops mattering once one combo bursts him; just keep W up so his R can't lock you alone in a sidelane."}],"wants":{"you":["Hold Remove Scurvy (W) for his R suppress, not to negate his Blood Hunt chase — cleansing the lock-on mid-channel and healing off your missing HP turns his entire all-in into a free counter-trade","Survive levels 1-3 without feeding keg denies, then reach your Sheen/keg spike where a chained Parrrley detonation finally out-bursts his drain heal","Place kegs back from the wave so he can't free-hit them at low durability, and slot anti-heal (Executioner's) early so his passive and Q can't out-sustain your poke"],"foe":["Walk you down at levels 1-3 while his passive heals hardest under your half-HP threshold and a fresh keg sits at free-hit durability","Chase you with Blood Hunt move speed onto the kegs you're hiding behind, denying your detonation setup before you can chain them","Land R suppress before your W is up so the lock holds and his passive drains you out before you can cleanse"]},"early":"Warwick owns the first three levels and there's no pretending otherwise — his Eternal Hunger passive heals hardest exactly when he's drained you under half HP, his Q heals off my max health on top, and my kegs come up on long cooldowns at low durability he can just free-hit to deny before they're useful. Don't throw a Parrrley and then step into auto range to follow it up; he'll Blood Hunt onto me with the move speed and out-sustain the trade every time. Last-hit with the tip of Q, place kegs back from the wave so he can't free-detonate or deny them, and accept I'm conceding this phase. The one thing to bait: an early Q leap onto a keg — if he commits it for nothing, he's out of position with it on cooldown.","mid":"This evens out as my second Q/E point lands and I can start chaining Parrrley-into-keg poke from outside his walk-up range — he has to eat chip to farm now, and his drain can't heal what it can't reach. At 6 his R suppresses me in place for the lock his passive feeds on, but Remove Scurvy (W) cleanses the suppression mid-channel and heals me off missing HP, so the entire all-in hinges on me holding W for the ult, not burning it on his Blood Hunt chase. Bait the R, cleanse it, and the fight flips. Outside of a jungler collapsing on the suppress, this stage is a genuine coin-flip on who respects the other's cooldown.","late":"My Sheen into the keg build is where I take over — an empowered Parrrley detonating a chained barrel finally bursts faster than his drain heals, and from there I'm the scaling carry. By two items chained keg explosions and global Cannon Barrage zoning beat a Warwick whose sustain stops being relevant once a single combo bursts him; his HP stacking just gives my barrels a bigger target and anti-heal caps his drain. The only late danger is getting caught sidelaning alone — his R is still a point-and-click lock that holds long enough for his team if my W is down, so keep Remove Scurvy for his ult and fight near my barrels, never out in the open.","whys":["Warwick's passive heals hardest under your half-HP threshold and a level-1 keg sits at low durability he free-hits to deny — any walk-up out-sustains your Parrrley chip, so concede and last-hit safe.","His Q heals off your max HP and Blood Hunt move speed walks you down before kegs are online — keep them back from the wave and don't follow a Parrrley into his auto range.","Your second Q/E point lets you start Parrrley-into-keg poke from range, so he has to eat chip to farm — the lane levels out as your drain-proof poke begins, and his R all-in is a coin-flip if you save W.","His R suppresses you but Remove Scurvy cleanses the lock mid-channel and heals off missing HP — hold W for the ult, not his chase, and the all-in is a coin-flip you can win.","Sheen into the keg build flips it: an empowered Parrrley detonating a chained barrel finally bursts faster than his drain can heal it back.","You out-scale outright — chained keg explosions and global Cannon Barrage burst him through any sustain, and anti-heal caps his passive and Q drain.","Once you're ahead on items his HP stacking just feeds your barrels a bigger target — keep W for his R so he can't lock you alone, and you delete him in any open fight."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"wukong","win":["Wukong","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Wukong's biggest window: Crushing Blow (Q) lowers your armor and lands an empowered crit-auto, and Stone Skin gives him bonus resists standing next to you — your single barrel has a long cooldown and is low-HP, so he can pop it early and walk you down."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your second Q and E points come online — Parrrley into a Powder Keg chain finally pokes him as he walks up to CS, and you can place a keg behind your own line so his Nimbus Strike (E) dash has no safe entry."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Cyclone (R) spin is a free all-in knockup, but Remove Scurvy cleanses the airborne and heals off your missing HP — pop W on the lift and walk out rather than trading the whole combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver online: empowered Parrrley plus a full keg chain bursts him before his W clone or E dash can reset the fight, flipping the lane to you."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm levels 1-3 at the tip of Parrrley so his Crushing Blow (Q) and autos never catch you in melee range where Stone Skin and his armor-shred do the most damage","From level 4 place kegs behind your minions and detonate Parrrley-into-keg chains as he walks up to CS, so his Nimbus Strike (E) dash has no clean entry","Hold W (Remove Scurvy) for his Cyclone (R) knockup, then hit your Sheen spike and bait his E-dash out before committing a keg-chain all-in"],"foe":["Open with Crushing Blow (Q) to lower your armor and land the empowered auto, then walk you down before your single barrel arms","Use Warrior Trickster (W) clone to bait your Parrrley keg detonation onto the decoy while he repositions","Land Cyclone (R) as a 6+ all-in or gank setup while your kegs and W are on cooldown"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are his — Wukong's Crushing Blow lowers my armor and lands an empowered crit-auto, his passive Stone Skin hands him free resists standing next to me, and I have one low-HP barrel on a long cooldown that he can pop before it ever arms. Don't place a keg in melee expecting it to live; set it back behind the wave and last-hit with the tip of Parrrley. Respect his Nimbus Strike dash — if he E's in with Q ready I lose that short trade every time, so I give ground and farm safe.","mid":"This is where I claw it back to even. With a second Q and E point I land Parrrley-into-keg poke as he walks up to farm, and his clone (Warrior Trickster) is the trap — don't blow my keg detonation on the decoy or I waste the whole zone. At 6 his Cyclone knockup looks scary, but Remove Scurvy cleanses the airborne and heals off my missing HP, so I cleanse on the lift, right-click out of the spin, and walk away. Bait his E-dash before I ever commit a chain.","late":"Once my Sheen/Essence Reaver lands I flip this — empowered Parrrley plus a full barrel chain bursts him before his W clone or E can reset, and Cannon Barrage zones him off objectives and sieges from across the map. He builds bruiser resists, so I lean into the keg burst instead of trying to out-auto him through Stone Skin. He stays even and item-dependent rather than a true hard scaler, so as long as I survived the early I own the back half — just never face-check for the clone near objectives.","whys":["Wukong's Crushing Blow lowers my armor for an empowered auto and Stone Skin gives him free resists in melee, while my single barrel is low-HP and pop-able before it arms — this is clearly his window.","It evens out as his Q comes off cooldown, but I still have no waveclear and lose melee trades, so I farm at Parrrley range and don't contest the wave.","My full kit is up but his Nimbus Strike dash still punishes any over-step — I keep the wave back and only trade Parrrley pokes when his Q is down.","Second Q and E points let me chain Parrrley-into-keg as he walks up, and placing kegs behind my line denies his E entry — that pulls the lane back to even.","His Cyclone knockup is a real engage, but Remove Scurvy cleanses the airborne and heals off my missing HP, so the level-6 all-in is roughly a coin flip rather than his win.","Sheen/Essence Reaver online: empowered Parrrley plus a full keg chain bursts him before his W clone or E dash resets the fight — my power window.","He's even and item-dependent rather than a hard scaler, so my chained-keg burst keeps pace through his resists and Cannon Barrage out-pressures him across the map at objectives."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"yasuo","win":["Skill","Yasuo","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Yasuo"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Yasuo's E (Sweeping Blade) lets him dash off your minions to close, eat one keg with an auto to deny it, and chip you with Steel Tempest pokes while your barrel charges are still scarce — his strongest window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen into the keg build is where you flip it: an empowered Parrrley detonating a full barrel chain bursts him through a single Windwall and outranges his Q poke before his crit comes online."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage zones the dash lanes Yasuo needs to flow through your wave — drop it behind him on his escape path, not on his current tile, so his only out is into your barrels."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Yasuo takes over once he has crit: Windwall eats your Parrrley keg-detonates outright, he Sweeping-Blades past the barrel slow, and his R knockup chains off your team's CC — close the lane before this or group up."}],"wants":{"you":["Hit your level 4-5 Parrrley-into-keg poke and your first-item Sheen spike before Yasuo's crit and flow-shield come online","Bait Windwall with a single Q or a throwaway keg-detonate, then commit the real chained barrel burst once the wall is on cooldown","Detonate kegs from outside his E-dash range so he can't Sweeping-Blade through the wave onto you while the slow is up"],"foe":["Use E off your minions and Steel Tempest pokes to chip you and deny lone kegs before your charges are stocked","Hold Windwall for your Parrrley keg-detonate to negate the entire barrel chain in one cast","Scale to 2-3 crit items so Windwall, Sweeping Blade and the R knockup let him kite and burst you late"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are dangerous for you: Yasuo dashes off the minion wave with Sweeping Blade to close, can eat a lone keg with an auto to deny it, and chips you with Steel Tempest while your barrel charges are scarce and the barrels themselves die to a single hit. Don't drop a keg where his E can reach it and pop it for free; last-hit with Parrrley from max range and respect his level 2-3 E-Q-auto trade. Never throw a Q he can simply Windwall — make him spend the wall on a minion or a throwaway poke before you commit anything that matters.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are where you take over: your second E point stocks more keg charges, and Parrrley-into-keg poke chains a slow he can't farm under, since he has to walk into the wave to last-hit. Force trades when Windwall is down — it's a long cooldown and he carries only one charge. At 6, Cannon Barrage zones the dash lanes Yasuo flows through; drop it on the path behind him so he can't Sweeping-Blade out, then detonate the chain on the slow. This is your spike, not his — punish every walk-up before his crit lands.","late":"Late game flips to him hard — that's the scaler tax. Once Yasuo has 2-3 crit items, Windwall blocks your Parrrley keg-detonates outright, he Sweeping-Blades past the barrel slow, and his R knockup chains off any ally CC to delete you. Your win condition is to have already snowballed this lane shut on your first-item Sheen spike so his scaling never matters. If it goes even, group with your team and never duel him 1v1 — make your own CC land before he can Windwall and dash through your kegs.","whys":["Both are weak at level 1, but Yasuo can E off a minion to threaten an auto trade — deny his Q last-hits and don't over-extend placing an early keg.","At 2-3 his E-Q-auto poke and free keg-denial outpace your barrels before your charges are stocked — concede the short trades and farm Parrrley at range.","He has to walk into the wave to last-hit and his Windwall is single-charge on a long cooldown, so your Parrrley-into-keg poke starts landing unanswered.","Your second E point stocks more charges and turns the keg chain online — empowered poke plus the chaining slow out-trade his pre-crit Steel Tempest.","Sheen into the barrel chain bursts him through one Windwall before his crit comes online — this is your hardest all-in window, force it now.","Cannon Barrage zones his Sweeping-Blade escape and traps him in the barrel slow, giving you the skirmish and dive pressure his pre-6 kit lacks.","Yasuo out-scales you outright: at 2-3 crit items Windwall blocks your detonates, his E dashes past the slow, and his R knockup one-shots you — play safe and group."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"yone","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Yone's Q3 dash-knockup into W cleave is his only real all-in before your kegs are stocked, so respect it and keep Remove Scurvy up to wash off the knockup."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Second Parrrley rank and a second Powder Keg charge come online, letting you set a keg he has to walk through to last-hit and chain-poke him off the wave."},{"when":"6 + 1st item","text":"Cannon Barrage zones his R re-engage angle, and a Sheen-empowered Parrrley detonating a full keg chain bursts harder than his W shield and E-rewind health can recover."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Chained keg detonations plus global Cannon Barrage outscale Yone's two-item duelist spike — you zone him from a range his Q3 dash and R cannot close cleanly."}],"wants":{"you":["Hold Remove Scurvy for his Q3 or R knockup so the all-in cleanses off and he is stranded in melee with E on cooldown","Set a keg on the wave at level 4-5 and detonate with Parrrley so he eats chip every time he steps up to farm","Scale to your Sheen keg spike and 6 — out-burst his W shield and use Cannon Barrage to cut his E-rewind exit"],"foe":["Open with R (Fate Sealed) or a Q3 dash into W cleave to all-in before your kegs and W cooldown are ready","Use E (Soul Unbound) to commit damage from his spirit form, then snap back to the body to undo the health and distance","Hit his two-item duelist spike and dash on top of you with Q3 while your Powder Kegs are on cooldown"]},"early":"Yone is even here, not a hard bully, and you hold the one tool that wrecks his combo: Remove Scurvy hard-cleanses CC, so when he Q3-dashes in (or ults with Fate Sealed) for the knockup-into-W cleave, you wash it off and he is left in melee range with nothing while his E body-rewind ticks down. The danger is your kegs early — they have long cooldowns and low HP, so never place a Powder Keg where he can free-hit it to deny you, and do not E into auto range to plant one while his Q is charged. Last-hit on the tip of Parrrley, concede a little CS since you have no waveclear yet, and know he cannot snowball this lane.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are where it tilts your way: a second Parrrley rank and a second keg charge let you plant on the wave and force him to walk through the explosion to farm, chipping him every step. Bank Remove Scurvy for his commitment — the instant he Q3-knockups or ults in, cleanse it, heal back the missing HP, and detonate your keg chain on him while his E-rewind is his only exit. At 6 Cannon Barrage adds zoning, not a duel kill, so drop it to deny his E-rewind escape angle or block his R re-engage rather than expecting it to finish him on its own.","late":"This is your lane to take over. Your first-item keg spike — Sheen or Essence Reaver into the barrel build — turns an empowered Parrrley plus a full chained detonation into burst that beats what his W shield and E-rewind health can recover, and by two items you own it. Unlike the hard scalers that reclaim this window, Yone caps as a mid-game duelist, so your chained kegs and global Cannon Barrage outpace him: zone him out of fights from a range his Q3 dash and R cannot reach cleanly, and answer any all-in with a pre-set keg ring plus Remove Scurvy to cleanse the knockup. Just keep your Powder Kegs off cooldown whenever he is looking to commit.","whys":["He is even at level 1 and no bully, and Remove Scurvy cleanses his Q3 dash-knockup or R if he commits early.","Both of you are scaling here — trade with Parrrley and keep your low-HP kegs from being free-hit and denied.","His Q3-into-W cleave is his cleanest all-in before your kegs are up, but cleansing the knockup with W keeps it a coinflip, not a loss.","Your second Parrrley rank and keg charge bring poke online — make him walk through the keg explosion to farm.","Cannon Barrage adds zoning past 6 and cuts his E-rewind or R re-engage angle, tipping skirmishes to you.","Your Sheen keg spike makes a chained detonation outburst his W shield and E-rewind health — force the all-in on your timing.","Chained kegs and global Cannon Barrage outscale his two-item duelist spike from a range his Q3 dash cannot answer."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"yorick","win":["Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Gangplank","Yorick"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Parrrley-into-keg poke comes online and Yorick has no dash to escape the blast — every time he steps up to last-hit behind a ghoul, Q the keg and chip him before his Mourning Mist can sic ghouls back on you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage drops on the wave to deny his Maiden push and zone him off any all-in — your global R answers the only real lane pressure he has before he scales."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen plus a Powder Keg chain bursts him through his ghouls before Maiden can swarm — empowered Parrrley off the barrel detonation is your cleanest all-in window."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Yorick's window: Maiden of the Mist plus a full ghoul wave and his W ring let him out-splitpush you and trap you in side lane — stop trying to solo-hold against him."}],"wants":{"you":["Land Parrrley-into-keg poke every time he walks up to last-hit behind a ghoul, since he has no dash to escape the keg slow","Use Cannon Barrage to delete his Maiden/ghoul push wave and zone him off any all-in or the Dark Procession ring","Hit your first-item Sheen keg-chain spike and snowball the lead before his Maiden splitpush takes over the map"],"foe":["Drop Dark Procession (W) to ring you in, then Mourning Mist (E) to slow you and sic his ghouls and Maiden onto you","Trade only with a full ghoul stack and Maiden up so the minion DPS covers his weak personal damage","Shove with Maiden and ghouls, then leave to a side lane and out-splitpush you for the rest of the game"]},"early":"Level 1 is a coin flip — your barrels have long cooldowns and low HP he can free-hit to deny, and his ghoul summons give him cheap last-hits, so just farm with the tip of Parrrley and don't hand him a free keg. From level 2 it tilts your way: every time he steps up to CS behind a ghoul, hit Q into a placed keg and chip him, because he has no dash to slip the detonation slow. Respect his Mourning Mist (E) — it slows you and commands his ghouls to leap on you, so don't stand on a keg where he can E you and pile the swarm on. Dodge the mark and his short trades have no real follow-up; the W ring (Dark Procession) is what he wants to trap you in for the kill, so never get walled onto your own keg.","mid":"This is your window. With a second Q/E point your keg chains zone him completely off the wave he desperately wants to shove for Maiden, and Parrrley's gold refund means you out-item him fast. At 6, drop Cannon Barrage straight on his pushing minion wave to delete the Maiden setup and zone him off any all-in — your R is the direct answer to his only lane pressure. Bait his E mark and the W ring, then once they're down step in and Q-keg-chain him through his ghouls before Maiden gets a stack on you.","late":"You've snowballed lane, but Yorick is a hard scaler and this is where he reclaims the matchup. A 2-item Maiden of the Mist plus a full ghoul wave shoves any side lane, and his Dark Procession ring traps you while the swarm grinds you down — you don't win that 1v1 split anymore. Don't try to solo-answer his side push; rotate, group, and use global Cannon Barrage to make plays elsewhere while your team handles the Maiden lane. Close the game on the lead you built, because the longer it goes the more his split outscales your duel.","whys":["Both of you are weak at level 1 — your barrels have long cooldowns he can free-hit to deny, and his ghoul gives him easy last-hits, so neither side wins the short trade.","Your level-2 Parrrley-into-keg poke chips him as he steps up, and with no dash he can't dodge the detonation slow to retaliate.","Keg poke plus Parrrley's gold refund lets you out-econ him while his single-target ghoul trades can't punish you back.","Your barrel chains zone him off the wave he needs to shove for Maiden, starving his whole scaling plan.","Cannon Barrage clears his Maiden/ghoul push and zones his all-in — your global R neutralizes the only lane threat he has.","Your Sheen keg-chain spike bursts him through his ghouls before Maiden can swarm you — force the all-in in this window.","He out-scales you: a 2-item Maiden plus ghoul wave and his Dark Procession ring out-splitpush and trap you, so group and don't duel his side lane."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"zac","win":["Skill","Zac","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Zac's Elastic Slingshot (E) is a charged leap-knockup he can fire from a brush or fog line, starting an all-in while your single early Powder Keg is still on its long cooldown and easy for him to free-pop. His cleanest kill window."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Second E/Q point lets you Parrrley a keg into him as he walks up to last-hit; your tip-range poke chips him back to even because his only answer is to facetank it or sling in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Essence Reaver into the keg build flips it -- empowered Parrrley plus a full chained detonation finally out-damages his Cell Division blob regen."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Chained kegs and global Cannon Barrage outscale a pure tank -- he can Slingshot in and CC you but can't kill you, and you delete the squishies he engages for."}],"wants":{"you":["Hold a keg at max range and Parrrley-detonate it so he eats poke before he can charge E and sling onto you","Stack anti-heal (Executioner's/Oblivion Orb) early so the blobs his Cell Division passive drops stop refunding your chip","Build MR, W-cleanse his knockup, and survive to your first-item keg spike, then force fights and out-scale the tank"],"foe":["Charge Elastic Slingshot (E) from fog to knock you up and open an all-in while your single keg is on cooldown","Walk over the blobs his passive drops on ability casts to heal back any Parrrley poke you land","Use Unstable Matter (W) and Stretching Strike (Q) to grab and burst you once his Slingshot has you pinned"]},"early":"Zac is an off-meta top pick, so most opponents won't pilot the lane cleanly, but the threat is real early: he has no waveclear pressure on you, yet his Elastic Slingshot (E) is a charged leap-knockup that starts a full all-in while your Powder Kegs are still on their long cooldown and easy for him to free-hit and pop. Don't place a keg right next to you and stand on it -- he'll Slingshot in, grab you with Q (Stretching Strike) and stack blobs faster than you can detonate. Last-hit with the tip of Parrrley, keep a keg at max range for zoning, and never facecheck a bush or fog line where he can charge E.","mid":"Levels 4-5 even it back out: a second Q and E point let you Parrrley a barrel into him every time he steps up to farm, and your poke beats his because his only answer is to walk into your keg range or eat it. The trick is anti-heal -- without Executioner's, every blob he scoops off the ground (dropped whenever he casts a spell) refunds the chip you just landed, and the lane stalls forever. At 6 your Cannon Barrage adds dive and skirmish pressure but doesn't win the straight duel, so it's still skill-matched; use R to zone him off blobs or punish his jungler, not to 1v1.","late":"This is where you pull ahead for good. Zac is a tank, not a hyperscaler -- once your first keg-build item lands, an empowered Parrrley into a chained detonation out-damages his Cell Division regen, and by two items you simply own the matchup. He can still Slingshot in and knock you up, so respect the engage and W-cleanse the CC, but he can't actually kill you anymore, while your chained kegs and global Cannon Barrage delete the squishies he dives for across the map. Close fights around your barrel cooldowns and let his tankiness become irrelevant.","whys":["Q-poke pays you gold and costs him nothing he can't lick back with blobs -- a true even start where you just bank last-hits and watch his E charge up.","A fog-charged Elastic Slingshot knockup into Q grab can chain an all-in before your single early keg can detonate -- this is his one real kill window.","Your full kit is online so you can keg-zone again, but he can Slingshot out of a chain and heal the trade with passive blobs -- it nets to skill.","A second keg point lets you Parrrley-poke him as he walks up to farm, but anti-heal decides it -- without it his blob regen erases your chip and the lane stays even.","Cannon Barrage adds zone and dive pressure but isn't a duel-winning spike on its own, so the straight 1v1 against his sustain stays roughly even.","Sheen/Essence Reaver into the keg build is your flip -- empowered Parrrley plus a full chained detonation finally out-damages his Cell Division regen.","Two items on, chained kegs and global Cannon Barrage outscale a pure tank -- he can engage you but can't kill you, and you erase the backline he dives for."]},
  {"a":"gangplank","b":"ziggs","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Ziggs' Q bounces over the wave and out-ranges your Parrrley, chunking you for free, and a stray bomb or one of his autos pops your low-HP Powder Keg before it arms to deny your whole zone."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"A second E point lets you set a keg, back off, and Parrrley-detonate it from range to trade without facetanking his bomb; Remove Scurvy heals the chip and cleanses his E minefield slow."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cannon Barrage drops on his retreat path when your jungler shows. Ziggs has no dash, only his W Satchel knockback to self-peel, so bait that out and he is an immobile artillery target."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once Sheen (Trinity Force / Iceborn line) is online, one empowered Parrrley into a chained keg detonation bursts a squishy Ziggs if he ever steps inside your barrel range."}],"wants":{"you":["Spread your Powder Kegs wide so a single Parrrley detonation chains out far enough to reach Ziggs behind his minefield","Hold Remove Scurvy to cleanse his E Hexplosive Minefield slow and heal back the bomb poke (it will NOT cancel his W knockback)","Shove and roam with Cannon Barrage to punish his dash-less, escape-light body when your jungler collapses"],"foe":["Bounce Q bombs over the wave to poke you and free-hit your low-HP kegs before they arm","Save Satchel Charge (W) to knock you back the instant you step up to place or hit a keg","Lay E Hexplosive Minefield on your keg spots so you can't path in to detonate a chain on him"]},"early":"Ziggs owns the opening levels. His Q bomb bounces over the minion wave and out-ranges your Parrrley, so every time you walk up to last-hit or place a keg you eat a bomb you can't answer. Worse, your Powder Kegs spawn with low HP, and he can destroy one with an auto or a stray bomb before it arms, denying your entire trading zone. Don't try to trade Q-for-Q here: last-hit at max range, place kegs to body-block his Q line, and accept the chip. Hold Remove Scurvy for sustain when the poke threatens a setup, not as a panic button.","mid":"This is where you claw back to even. With a second E point you can finally set a keg, step back, and Parrrley-detonate it from range to trade without facetanking his bomb, and Remove Scurvy heals the chip he stacks plus cleanses his E minefield slow (it will not save you from his W knockback, so don't rely on it for that). At 6 your Cannon Barrage isn't a duel button, it's a map button: drop it on his retreat path when your jungler shows, because Ziggs has no dash and only the W Satchel to self-peel. Bait that Satchel, and once it's down he's an immobile artillery turret you or a ganker can run down.","late":"Once your Sheen build (Trinity Force or the Iceborn line) is online the lane flips on any misposition: an empowered Parrrley into a chained keg explosion bursts a squishy Ziggs from across the lane, and your global Cannon Barrage lets you swing fights he can only poke from the backline. The catch is that Ziggs scales hard too, and if he's even on items his bomb poke and minefield zone still chunk you before you ever close, so you can't just walk in. Play it as a siege war: match his poke with keg detonations, threaten the all-in only when his Satchel is down, and use Cannon Barrage to take the map his immobile kit can't contest.","whys":["His Q bomb bounces over minions and out-ranges Parrrley, so he pokes you for free while you can't trade back and have no answer to the range gap.","He keeps the range edge and can free-hit your low-HP Powder Keg to destroy it before it arms, denying your only ranged trading tool.","Your second E point lets you Parrrley-detonate a keg from distance to finally trade back, and Remove Scurvy heals his chip and cleanses his minefield slow, so it evens out.","You stabilize with keg poke and the cleanse-heal, but his bomb range still matches your detonation reach, so neither side takes over the lane.","Cannon Barrage adds gank and zone pressure on his escape-light body, but his W Satchel knockback answers the dive, keeping it down to skill.","Once Sheen is online, one empowered Parrrley into a chained keg detonation bursts a mispositioned Ziggs, your clearest favour window in the lane.","You both hyperscale: your keg chain one-shots if he slips, but his poke and minefield still zone you out on even items, so it stays even."]}
